    '{"id":"01KE7HPWCAM0BJVJFGFS9838KH","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Updates and Branding**\n\nThe team is finalizing mobile adjustments and aligning creative branding to support a cohesive user experience.\n\n- **The mobile version of the carousel slider requires a centering fix on INSPEC Mobile**, which Kate flagged with a screenshot for the team to address before the live launch (05:01).  \n    - The slider update was completed last week following Greg’s direction to narrow LinkedIn target industries.  \n    - Colin highlighted that the **2025 date placeholder** still shows on the site, expected to update by year-end.  \n    - The creative direction is leaning toward a clean, tight branding style similar to Zero Fox, focusing on fraud news relevance rather than generic hacker imagery, pending Greg’s input per Kate’s request.  \n    - This branding approach aims to strengthen thematic consistency across the podcast and website, improving audience recognition and engagement.\n\n- **The Nicola Harding podcast episode is in production and expected to be ready by week’s end** (06:10).  \n    - The team is aligning content strategy with keyword positioning to better match ThreatMark’s market language versus internal jargon, following Colin’s insights on Zero Fox’s success with searchable intent.  \n    - Feedback on the fraud disruption white paper from Mikal is minimal and forthcoming today, supporting refinement of marketing materials.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Budgeting**\n\nRecent ad campaigns show strong improvements but require budget realignment toward higher-performing channels.\n\n- **Post-holiday Google Ads traffic increased by 240% week-over-week, and clicks rose 337% to 35 clicks, while cost per click decreased** (13:06).  \n    - Despite gains, Colin noted Google Ads’ search intent mismatch reduces its efficiency against ThreatMark’s niche audience.  \n    - LinkedIn remains the strongest channel, delivering high-quality leads and justifying increased budget allocation there.  \n    - Kate confirmed the final budget breakdown is still pending, delaying immediate reallocations.\n\n- **Lead generation improved with nine new leads and a cost per lead of $66.72, showing a significant efficiency gain** (14:17).  \n    - The US and Canada campaigns show a $95.32 cost per lead, while the Q2 campaign is even more efficient at $55 per lead.  \n    - The AI versus fraud white paper and fraud liability ads drive most performance in EMEA markets.  \n    - AdRoll programmatic display ads achieved a **33% click-through rate increase at $5.72 cost per click**, mainly supporting brand awareness rather than direct conversions.\n\n- **Colin recommended shifting some Google Ads budget to LinkedIn instead of increasing AdRoll spend to maximize lead quality** (15:32).  \n    - The team is monitoring competitor bid adjustments on Google Ads as part of the ongoing strategy refinement.\n\n## **Event Planning and Design Coordination**\n\nEvent preparation is advancing, with a near-finalized list ready to guide design work and sponsorship planning.\n\n- **Iulia will share a close-to-final event list today, covering about 11 events: 5 in the US, 4 in the UK, and 2 in the Nordics** (09:34).  \n    - The list currently includes high-level sponsorship details but lacks granular design requirements like banners or tablecloths.  \n    - Colin requested a breakdown of design needs per event to begin mockups and ensure timely delivery by the end of January.  \n    - The team plans to revisit interactive booth elements, such as the quiz game used last year, to boost engagement.\n\n- **Responsibility for finalizing event design specs rests with ThreatMark’s team, coordinated with Greg, with follow-up expected soon** (10:29).  \n    - This coordination aims to ensure smooth preparation aligned with overall event marketing strategy.\n\n## **Website Migration and IT Collaboration**\n\nThe Banking Fraud Summit website migration is approved with a clear plan for IT support and timeline communication.\n\n- **Colin secured approval to gift 35 points, equivalent to $3,500, toward the Banking Fraud Summit website migration project** (12:00).  \n    - This commitment aims to secure management of ThreatMark’s own website migration when ready, leveraging project momentum.  \n    - Colin will draft a simple timeline and plan document to outline migration steps and key dates for internal and IT teams.  \n    - Kate’s IT team will need to add DNS records to point the Banking Fraud Summit website to the HubSpot-hosted site, replicating past email setup processes.\n\n## **Lead Management and Data Consistency**\n\nLead source data is being standardized to improve reporting accuracy and campaign tracking.\n\n- **Lists from past events like TG Connect 2024 and 2025 were uploaded with lead owner set to Garrett from the US sales team** (16:32).  \n    - Colin will update lead source fields across these contacts to uniformly reflect whether they came from sponsored or hosted events, specifying the exact event name for clarity.  \n    - This cleanup supports better attribution and follow-up processes, enhancing sales and marketing alignment.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn marketing","website migration","event planning","ad performance","content strategy","propensity integration"],"overview":"- **Website Updates:** Mobile carousel slider fix needed before launch, 2025 placeholder to be updated by year-end for branding consistency.\n- **Podcast Production:** Nicola Harding episode expected end of week; content strategy aligning with market language for better engagement.\n- **Ad Campaign Metrics:** Google Ads traffic up 240%, but intent mismatch noted; LinkedIn delivering high-quality leads, budget shift recommended.\n- **Event Planning:** Final event list to include 11 total events, with sponsorship details; design needs to be specified for timely delivery.\n- **Migration Approval:** $3,500 approved for Banking Fraud Summit website migration; clear timeline and IT coordination required for successful transfer.\n- **Lead Management:** Standardizing lead source data to enhance attribution; past event lists uploaded for clearer follow-up tracking.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDocument and communicate plan and timeline for Banking Fraud Summit website migration, including IT dependencies for DNS adjustments (11:38)\nNote mobile carousel slider alignment issue and assign to team for fix prior to live push (05:18)\nUpdate HubSpot lead source fields for event contacts to ensure consistency with lead source detail and lead source spec (16:00)\nFollow up with Greg on Central Europe account list timing and event design requirements (09:00)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nShare Mikal’s feedback on Fraud Disruption white paper with Colin (08:14)\nCoordinate internally for pitch deck content delivery post-SKO at end of the month (08:28)\nAssist with IT team support for website domain and DNS changes for the migration project (13:06)\n\n**Iulia Lungu**\nProvide Colin with the near-final event calendar list including US, UK, and Nordic events (09:34)\nBegin compiling detailed event design requirements after sharing initial list (18:15)\nConfirm and relay timeline or updates from Greg on propensity integration (10:49)\n"},"duration":19.079999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":2,"name":"Iulia Lungu"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":153.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":1,"end_time":179.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hello.","index":2,"end_time":227.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":229.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not bad.","index":4,"end_time":231.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":230.73,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":5,"end_time":233.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":6,"end_time":233.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":7,"end_time":237.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.81,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Still under the weather, but I''ve started medicine, so hopefully that helps.","index":8,"end_time":242.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry to hear you''re not great.","index":9,"end_time":244.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You''re well?","index":10,"end_time":244.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s just what happens.","index":11,"end_time":246.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I know.","index":12,"end_time":250.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg is not joining today.","index":13,"end_time":251.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is Julia joining?","index":14,"end_time":252.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know, actually, but I imagine some of the questions might be for her with the account, so maybe give her a minute.","index":15,"end_time":264.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":16,"end_time":264.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nina is out today, so it''ll just be me from our side.","index":17,"end_time":267.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":18,"end_time":268.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is there anything we can go through before Julia joins anyway?","index":19,"end_time":285.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.86,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, so a few updates.","index":20,"end_time":288.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg sent a note about narrowing the Target Industries on LinkedIn, so that was done last week.","index":21,"end_time":294.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also updated the slider on the test website.","index":22,"end_time":297.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Nina sent that over.","index":23,"end_time":298.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you guys have had a chance to review it.","index":24,"end_time":300.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I did review it, actually.","index":25,"end_time":303.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It looks great.","index":26,"end_time":304.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It works really well.","index":27,"end_time":305.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I did have.","index":28,"end_time":306.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m not on the vpn, so I can''t show my screen, but I did have on INSPEC Mobile.","index":29,"end_time":314.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It did seem a little bit off center.","index":30,"end_time":316.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I have a screenshot I can share.","index":31,"end_time":317.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, screenshot would be great, but I''ll also just write that down for a team.","index":32,"end_time":321.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But other than that, if that can be fixed as it''s like pushed to live, I think we''re good to go with that.","index":33,"end_time":329.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":334.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.53,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I keep writing that it''s 2025 still, and I''m wondering when that''s going to change.","index":35,"end_time":347.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably at the end of the year.","index":36,"end_time":349.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hey, everyone.","index":37,"end_time":350.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.81,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Hello.","index":38,"end_time":351.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":39,"end_time":352.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so just make sure that mobile''s good.","index":40,"end_time":357.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":41,"end_time":358.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.22,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right?","index":42,"end_time":358.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I can.","index":43,"end_time":363.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I wasn''t able to hear you for a second.","index":44,"end_time":364.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.26,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Can you hear us now?","index":45,"end_time":366.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can hear you.","index":46,"end_time":367.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":366.86,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think the headset is just not working.","index":47,"end_time":369.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.78,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":48,"end_time":374.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just got started, so we were just going over some things.","index":49,"end_time":377.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":50,"end_time":377.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the audience, the.","index":51,"end_time":380.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll look at the mobile version of the carousel for the slider and then get that live.","index":52,"end_time":385.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also the Nicola Harding episode is under production, so that''ll be ready later this week.","index":53,"end_time":391.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did go through the zero Fox branding that you guys had referenced as an example.","index":54,"end_time":401.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, it really kind of lines up directly with the Behind Enemy Lines podcast branding.","index":55,"end_time":407.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think that''ll be pretty easy for a team.","index":56,"end_time":409.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s less of like the generic, like hackers and hoodies in an underground subway station with a computer lab for some reason, and more of a pretty tight branding that we can connect the show to the Website to like the.","index":57,"end_time":425.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The news of fraud.","index":58,"end_time":426.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So does that.","index":59,"end_time":429.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":428.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that the direction that we want to go in for all future creative.","index":60,"end_time":432.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s table like the actual decision on that for the moment because I would want Greg to be involved with that.","index":61,"end_time":441.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.5,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Plus I think he''s thinking larger as well.","index":62,"end_time":447.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":447.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":64,"end_time":449.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And same with their content strategy.","index":65,"end_time":453.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They share a lot of technical expertise.","index":66,"end_time":456.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously they''re in the cyber threat space, but they match that very well with searchable intent like we''ve talked about.","index":67,"end_time":463.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, I know that you had a writer on staff and we were talking about how to use the keywords that we''re providing.","index":68,"end_time":469.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Connect it to threatmarks positioning.","index":69,"end_time":471.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not always the same terminology or jargon that the fraud fighters are using that the people who need that service are using.","index":70,"end_time":479.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what zero Fox does really well.","index":71,"end_time":481.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, a few updates.","index":72,"end_time":487.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just I still haven''t seen any feedback from.","index":73,"end_time":489.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mentioned Mikal''s feedback for the fraud disruption white paper.","index":74,"end_time":493.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I have that ready to share with you today.","index":75,"end_time":496.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s pretty minimal then.","index":76,"end_time":498.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":496.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":77,"end_time":500.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys also mentioned a new pitch deck that you would be sending over some content for that we could help just make more attractive.","index":78,"end_time":507.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not ready this week?","index":79,"end_time":509.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":508.62,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t think it might be towards next week.","index":80,"end_time":512.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":509.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We actually saying that we have our SKO next week.","index":81,"end_time":517.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I imagine it will come out after that towards the end of the month.","index":82,"end_time":520.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.74,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":83,"end_time":521.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":84,"end_time":522.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Greg mentioned Central Europe account list.","index":85,"end_time":525.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You slacked about that this week.","index":86,"end_time":531.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m wrong.","index":87,"end_time":532.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think that''s towards.","index":88,"end_time":533.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think we''re aiming towards Q2 for that.","index":89,"end_time":536.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"He said we have target accounts for Central Europe.","index":90,"end_time":539.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d like to transition our focus.","index":91,"end_time":541.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":541.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.47,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I also have noted for Q2.","index":93,"end_time":543.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.83,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":545.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":95,"end_time":548.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":547.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is that maybe.","index":96,"end_time":549.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys need to regroup with Greg on that?","index":97,"end_time":550.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, leave that one with us.","index":98,"end_time":553.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":99,"end_time":553.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know that we''re also talking through the.","index":100,"end_time":558.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I''ll say that for last, actually.","index":101,"end_time":561.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we were also talking through the event calendar that you guys have and a lot of them being in March and we wanted to get those designs sort of out of the way by the end of this month.","index":102,"end_time":570.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have that list to share so we can start mocking some designs up?","index":103,"end_time":574.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve got a list.","index":104,"end_time":575.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.36,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I can share it with you.","index":105,"end_time":578.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":575.88,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I mean it''s.","index":106,"end_time":578.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.08,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"It''s still not like a final, final one, but it is like close to the final one.","index":107,"end_time":583.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.84,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I see.","index":108,"end_time":585.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.37,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":109,"end_time":586.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.81,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think I can share.","index":110,"end_time":587.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.93,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think I can share it with you.","index":111,"end_time":588.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.61,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"There are like about 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 events in the US four events in the UK and two events in in Nordics.","index":112,"end_time":599.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.37,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So I think I can share it with you today.","index":113,"end_time":601.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.89,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, that''d be great.","index":114,"end_time":603.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know Greg had mentioned it''ll be a mix of different design elements that you need for those.","index":115,"end_time":610.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some you may need a banner, some you might need more.","index":116,"end_time":612.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have that sort of note or breakdown in that table?","index":117,"end_time":616.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s just like the high level, like what are the sponsorships and basically why it''s a good fit for us.","index":118,"end_time":624.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":617.73,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"But I know we haven''t started like planning so I don''t have that yet.","index":119,"end_time":628.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.689,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":120,"end_time":630.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, it would be great if you could just share the table with us just so we have a heads up and then.","index":121,"end_time":634.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be on your guys action items list just to square that away with Greg.","index":122,"end_time":638.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, awesome.","index":123,"end_time":640.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys also mentioned a propensity integration that you were checking into.","index":124,"end_time":645.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How has that been going?","index":125,"end_time":646.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, we haven''t onboarded them yet.","index":126,"end_time":651.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.32,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Right, Kate?","index":127,"end_time":652.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.72,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think it''s, it''s just going to take a while.","index":128,"end_time":655.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.84,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So I don''t have a timeline for this but it''s definitely not happening in Jan.","index":129,"end_time":661.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.6,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So I''m not sure.","index":130,"end_time":662.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":661.88,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Not sure exactly.","index":131,"end_time":664.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.84,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Again, a question to to Greg.","index":132,"end_time":667.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.12,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"It is coming soon.","index":133,"end_time":669.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.59,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I just don''t know when exactly.","index":134,"end_time":671.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.71,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":135,"end_time":672.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":136,"end_time":672.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think based on what your plan was earlier, it was like towards the end of Q1 already.","index":137,"end_time":678.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"By Q1, so onboarded by Q1, correct?","index":138,"end_time":682.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":678.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, that''s true, that''s true.","index":139,"end_time":685.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.87,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"By Q1 but I don''t have like a specific date.","index":140,"end_time":690.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.79,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"When exactly is it like.","index":141,"end_time":691.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":690.23,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s say towards the end of Q1.","index":142,"end_time":694.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.03,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":694.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.03,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Okay.","index":144,"end_time":698.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t believe we''re already so far through January.","index":145,"end_time":700.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":146,"end_time":702.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.02,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Unbelievable.","index":147,"end_time":703.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.5,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":706.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was in annual planning for two days last week so my like first week of January was cut even shorter.","index":149,"end_time":712.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a bad week to have an annual planning session.","index":150,"end_time":717.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Note for the future always feels like it''s bad timing though.","index":151,"end_time":720.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":720.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":153,"end_time":723.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so I, I talked to Kate, you know Justin and Tristan, the owners of the of marketers in demand.","index":154,"end_time":730.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are going to gift 35 points which is 3, $500 for the banking Fraud Summit website migration.","index":155,"end_time":738.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I sent that over to Greg so fought hard to to get that cleared.","index":156,"end_time":743.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy that we can move forward with that and hoping that that locks in that we can manage the Threatmark website migration as well when that project is available.","index":157,"end_time":750.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s awesome.","index":158,"end_time":752.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you for that.","index":159,"end_time":753.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":160,"end_time":753.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''m going to do for next steps there then is to just put together a light hearted or a light document that outlines the timeline and everything that''s going to happen the migration.","index":161,"end_time":766.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, we will need some help from your IT team just because we don''t have domain access so they''re going to same with when we had to set up like sending emails from HubSpot.","index":162,"end_time":776.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re just gonna have to add DNS records for the Banking Fraud Summit website.","index":163,"end_time":780.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it points to the HubSpot site that we build.","index":164,"end_time":782.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":780.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":165,"end_time":785.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":166,"end_time":787.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":167,"end_time":790.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We saw some great increases in ad performance after the holidays which is to be expected even on the Google Ad side.","index":168,"end_time":799.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"240% increase week after week in traffic and 337% increase week over week in clicks.","index":169,"end_time":807.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":799.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is 35 clicks.","index":170,"end_time":808.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So obviously not a huge amount but definitely higher than what was going on on the holidays.","index":171,"end_time":813.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per click also decreased and it does seem like competitors are starting to drop their bids again as was listed in our recommendation.","index":172,"end_time":821.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure that Google Ads is the best channel for threatmarks efforts.","index":173,"end_time":825.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s largely informative search that people are looking for and you guys operate in such a niche that people really don''t know the terminology.","index":174,"end_time":834.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so if they look up something like phishing 99 times out of 100 it seems like they are looking for a service that is not yours.","index":175,"end_time":841.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just always things to keep in mind.","index":176,"end_time":844.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn has definitely been the best performer and I think that deserves more of the budget.","index":177,"end_time":848.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":849.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I know you guys are working on the exact budget breakdown as well.","index":179,"end_time":854.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t got anything to share with you actually on that either.","index":180,"end_time":857.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":181,"end_time":858.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":859.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did see a significant increase.","index":183,"end_time":861.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got nine leads and this is actually I didn''t even count the ones that came over this weekend.","index":184,"end_time":865.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got a few more leads over the weekend as well.","index":185,"end_time":867.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that was a good increase in leads.","index":186,"end_time":871.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The cost per lead is at $66.72 which is significant improvement.","index":187,"end_time":876.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the US and Canada campaign is at a $95.32 cost per lead.","index":188,"end_time":882.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So operating very low compared to our competitors in those markets.","index":189,"end_time":886.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the Q2 campaign is very, very efficient.","index":190,"end_time":889.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"$55 cost per lead.","index":191,"end_time":890.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re playing in a great playground there as far as the ads that are performing the best.","index":192,"end_time":896.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is the AI versus fraud white paper and the fraud liability ads that are driving the bulk of performance in the EMEA markets.","index":193,"end_time":903.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did See also a 33% click through rate increase on the ad roll which is those programmatic display advertising pieces and that''s at a $5.72 cost per click as well, which we don''t see conversions often from those, but they are great for brand awareness.","index":194,"end_time":921.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a small portion of the budget dedicated to that.","index":195,"end_time":923.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have any recommendations around that budget moving any more to AdRoll if it is doing well?","index":196,"end_time":931.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I think AdRoll is just great for brand awareness.","index":197,"end_time":935.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that we''re at a really good clip right now with the budget and the amount of clicks that we''re seeing.","index":198,"end_time":940.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I honestly think that I would rather take some Google Ads budget and move it towards LinkedIn instead of moving anything towards AdRoll.","index":199,"end_time":949.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn has just been the top performer.","index":200,"end_time":951.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even after narrowing the audiences, we''re still seeing great conversions, you know, seeing very high quality companies coming into HubSpot from downloading the white papers and everything else.","index":201,"end_time":960.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was going through HubSpot and one question that I have is it looks like a list was uploaded or a few lists for different events.","index":202,"end_time":975.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you guys upload those?","index":203,"end_time":978.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":204,"end_time":983.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because the lead owner is set to Garrett.","index":205,"end_time":989.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Garrett.","index":206,"end_time":992.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.13,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, he.","index":207,"end_time":994.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.13,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"He''s part of the US sales team.","index":208,"end_time":996.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.77,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"But we didn''t have any event.","index":209,"end_time":1001.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1000.45,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Right.","index":210,"end_time":1002.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.89,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So like not sure what that could be.","index":211,"end_time":1004.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1002.29,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Well, yeah, it''s from past events, so it''s.","index":212,"end_time":1007.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s TG Connect 2025, 2024, a few different events lists that were updated it looks like.","index":213,"end_time":1016.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''m going to do is just make sure that they''re following our rules for lead source detail or lead source specific.","index":214,"end_time":1030.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the table breakdown we had, it would either be a sponsored event or hosted event as the lead source and then lead source Spec be the actual event name.","index":215,"end_time":1042.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m just going to go ahead and update those across the board so that we''re uniform in how we''re managing contacts.","index":216,"end_time":1046.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":217,"end_time":1047.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.18,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":218,"end_time":1048.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.66,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":219,"end_time":1049.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1049.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did we lose Kate or is my computer just freaking out?","index":220,"end_time":1053.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, I don''t see her.","index":221,"end_time":1054.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.26,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Kate, are you here?","index":222,"end_time":1055.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.5,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Maybe she.","index":223,"end_time":1057.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.18,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Maybe her connection is bad.","index":224,"end_time":1059.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.86,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t see her.","index":225,"end_time":1060.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.38,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Okay.","index":226,"end_time":1061.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just wish you would have joined.","index":227,"end_time":1065.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, give her another minute.","index":228,"end_time":1067.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1065.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other than that, that is largely everything that I had to cover.","index":229,"end_time":1070.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it seems like we''re still just waiting on some things before we can move forward with like designs and everything, but in the meantime we''ll start putting that plan together for the Banking Fraud Summit website migration.","index":230,"end_time":1081.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":231,"end_time":1083.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.55,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"And in terms of events, you said like you need the list of events to start planning and then the, the what will be the exact requirements?","index":232,"end_time":1091.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1083.27,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Whether it''s banner or what.","index":233,"end_time":1093.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.07,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"What else you mentioned.","index":234,"end_time":1094.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.76,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, whether it''s banners or tablecloths or leave behinds or if we wanted to do any sort of.","index":235,"end_time":1102,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, last year we did a game, like a quiz that we built to.","index":236,"end_time":1108.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To try and draw more people to the.","index":237,"end_time":1110.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To the booth, things like that.","index":238,"end_time":1111.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":1112.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.68,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Engagement.","index":240,"end_time":1112.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.08,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1113.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.8,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"So basically, you need more details.","index":242,"end_time":1114.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.12,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Let me just share the list as of now, and then I will start working on the.","index":243,"end_time":1118.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.6,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"On the rest.","index":244,"end_time":1119.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.88,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, that''d be perfect.","index":245,"end_time":1121.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I don''t see Kate.","index":246,"end_time":1123.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1122.52,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"I think I can just drop her message that we are done, basically.","index":247,"end_time":1129.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.12,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Okay.","index":248,"end_time":1130.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":249,"end_time":1130.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If anything else pops up, just feel free to shoot me a slack or anything, but.","index":250,"end_time":1135.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, great talking to you.","index":251,"end_time":1136.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":1137.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":253,"end_time":1137.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.4,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Likewise.","index":254,"end_time":1138.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1137.84,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Bye.","index":255,"end_time":1138.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.36,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"},{"text":"Bye.","index":256,"end_time":1138.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.6,"speaker_name":"Iulia Lungu"}],"dateString":"2026-01-12T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE7HPWCAM0BJVJFGFS9838KH","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Completed LinkedIn targeting refinements and test site carousel update; minor mobile issue flagged for fix.","Kate confirmed fraud disruption white paper feedback is minimal; Colin to proceed with revisions.","Event list near-final; Iulia committed to providing details to enable timely creative development.","Granted 35 bonus credits to enable Banking Fraud Summit migration; ThreatMark IT to assist on DNS.","Ads performed strongly post-holidays; LinkedIn leads dominate with decreased CPC and increased CTR."],"highlights":[{"quote":"LinkedIn has just been the top performer... seeing very high quality companies coming into HubSpot","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"It looks great. It works really well.","speaker":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"quote":"We are going to gift 35 points... for the banking Fraud Summit website migration.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","launch","events","ads","website"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-12T14:25:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Updates and Branding**\n\nThe team is finalizing mobile adjustments and aligning creative branding to support a cohesive user experience.\n\n- **The mobile version of the carousel slider requires a centering fix on INSPEC Mobile**, which Kate flagged with a screenshot for the team to address before the live launch (05:01).  \n    - The slider update was completed last week following Greg’s direction to narrow LinkedIn target industries.  \n    - Colin highlighted that the **2025 date placeholder** still shows on the site, expected to update by year-end.  \n    - The creative direction is leaning toward a clean, tight branding style similar to Zero Fox, focusing on fraud news relevance rather than generic hacker imagery, pending Greg’s input per Kate’s request.  \n    - This branding approach aims to strengthen thematic consistency across the podcast and website, improving audience recognition and engagement.\n\n- **The Nicola Harding podcast episode is in production and expected to be ready by week’s end** (06:10).  \n    - The team is aligning content strategy with keyword positioning to better match ThreatMark’s market language versus internal jargon, following Colin’s insights on Zero Fox’s success with searchable intent.  \n    - Feedback on the fraud disruption white paper from Mikal is minimal and forthcoming today, supporting refinement of marketing materials.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance and Budgeting**\n\nRecent ad campaigns show strong improvements but require budget realignment toward higher-performing channels.\n\n- **Post-holiday Google Ads traffic increased by 240% week-over-week, and clicks rose 337% to 35 clicks, while cost per click decreased** (13:06).  \n    - Despite gains, Colin noted Google Ads’ search intent mismatch reduces its efficiency against ThreatMark’s niche audience.  \n    - LinkedIn remains the strongest channel, delivering high-quality leads and justifying increased budget allocation there.  \n    - Kate confirmed the final budget breakdown is still pending, delaying immediate reallocations.\n\n- **Lead generation improved with nine new leads and a cost per lead of $66.72, showing a significant efficiency gain** (14:17).  \n    - The US and Canada campaigns show a $95.32 cost per lead, while the Q2 campaign is even more efficient at $55 per lead.  \n    - The AI versus fraud white paper and fraud liability ads drive most performance in EMEA markets.  \n    - AdRoll programmatic display ads achieved a **33% click-through rate increase at $5.72 cost per click**, mainly supporting brand awareness rather than direct conversions.\n\n- **Colin recommended shifting some Google Ads budget to LinkedIn instead of increasing AdRoll spend to maximize lead quality** (15:32).  \n    - The team is monitoring competitor bid adjustments on Google Ads as part of the ongoing strategy refinement.\n\n## **Event Planning and Design Coordination**\n\nEvent preparation is advancing, with a near-finalized list ready to guide design work and sponsorship planning.\n\n- **Iulia will share a close-to-final event list today, covering about 11 events: 5 in the US, 4 in the UK, and 2 in the Nordics** (09:34).  \n    - The list currently includes high-level sponsorship details but lacks granular design requirements like banners or tablecloths.  \n    - Colin requested a breakdown of design needs per event to begin mockups and ensure timely delivery by the end of January.  \n    - The team plans to revisit interactive booth elements, such as the quiz game used last year, to boost engagement.\n\n- **Responsibility for finalizing event design specs rests with ThreatMark’s team, coordinated with Greg, with follow-up expected soon** (10:29).  \n    - This coordination aims to ensure smooth preparation aligned with overall event marketing strategy.\n\n## **Website Migration and IT Collaboration**\n\nThe Banking Fraud Summit website migration is approved with a clear plan for IT support and timeline communication.\n\n- **Colin secured approval to gift 35 points, equivalent to $3,500, toward the Banking Fraud Summit website migration project** (12:00).  \n    - This commitment aims to secure management of ThreatMark’s own website migration when ready, leveraging project momentum.  \n    - Colin will draft a simple timeline and plan document to outline migration steps and key dates for internal and IT teams.  \n    - Kate’s IT team will need to add DNS records to point the Banking Fraud Summit website to the HubSpot-hosted site, replicating past email setup processes.\n\n## **Lead Management and Data Consistency**\n\nLead source data is being standardized to improve reporting accuracy and campaign tracking.\n\n- **Lists from past events like TG Connect 2024 and 2025 were uploaded with lead owner set to Garrett from the US sales team** (16:32).  \n    - Colin will update lead source fields across these contacts to uniformly reflect whether they came from sponsored or hosted events, specifying the exact event name for clarity.  \n    - This cleanup supports better attribution and follow-up processes, enhancing sales and marketing alignment.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn marketing","website migration","event planning","ad performance","content strategy","propensity integration"],"overview":"- **Website Updates:** Mobile carousel slider fix needed before launch, 2025 placeholder to be updated by year-end for branding consistency.\n- **Podcast Production:** Nicola Harding episode expected end of week; content strategy aligning with market language for better engagement.\n- **Ad Campaign Metrics:** Google Ads traffic up 240%, but intent mismatch noted; LinkedIn delivering high-quality leads, budget shift recommended.\n- **Event Planning:** Final event list to include 11 total events, with sponsorship details; design needs to be specified for timely delivery.\n- **Migration Approval:** $3,500 approved for Banking Fraud Summit website migration; clear timeline and IT coordination required for successful transfer.\n- **Lead Management:** Standardizing lead source data to enhance attribution; past event lists uploaded for clearer follow-up tracking.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nDocument and communicate plan and timeline for Banking Fraud Summit website migration, including IT dependencies for DNS adjustments (11:38)\nNote mobile carousel slider alignment issue and assign to team for fix prior to live push (05:18)\nUpdate HubSpot lead source fields for event contacts to ensure consistency with lead source detail and lead source spec (16:00)\nFollow up with Greg on Central Europe account list timing and event design requirements (09:00)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nShare Mikal’s feedback on Fraud Disruption white paper with Colin (08:14)\nCoordinate internally for pitch deck content delivery post-SKO at end of the month (08:28)\nAssist with IT team support for website domain and DNS changes for the migration project (13:06)\n\n**Iulia Lungu**\nProvide Colin with the near-final event calendar list including US, UK, and Nordic events (09:34)\nBegin compiling detailed event design requirements after sharing initial list (18:15)\nConfirm and relay timeline or updates from Greg on propensity integration (10:49)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"439d598f-6a05-488e-8ebe-891ef0431f4c","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
