-- Meeting: GSS // MID Weekly Meeting (2026-01-07 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6061d0c2-de11-40b9-8824-1ccd80a970d6',
    '2026-01-07 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE098Y68WF16KGM5MZQES1G0',
    'GSS // MID Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Guille Santana","Nick S (GSS)","Will Fleming"}'::text[],
    1349,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81010350325?pwd=qJCrbL10kdxdmKpMcLq7aanFQIBZ5h.1',
    '{"id":"01KE098Y68WF16KGM5MZQES1G0","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Development**\n\nThe team is advancing targeted content to drive engagement and lead capture with a new gated ebook planned for Q1 2026. \n\n- **Guille Santana proposed creating a gated ebook titled \"The Restaurants’ Cash Playbook 2026\" to capture leads by requiring form submissions for downloads** (05:35)  \n    - The ebook will focus on cash flow management for restaurant operators, a pressing concern given current market pressures.  \n    - Will Fleming emphasized the importance of specificity and relevance, recommending the addition of the year 2026 to signal freshness and relevance.  \n    - The content team will leverage existing resources and internal designers and developers to produce the ebook efficiently, targeting a Q1 release.  \n    - Optimizing for large language models like ChatGPT was suggested to boost SEO and capture emerging search trends.\n\n- **Ongoing blog content includes a post titled \"The Ghost of CFO Turnover,\" scheduled for review and publishing this week** (06:32)  \n    - This piece builds on prior interviews and aligns with the theme of CFO challenges in the restaurant sector.  \n    - The last blog was published on December 30th, focusing on the restaurant CFO talent crisis, with no current blockers.  \n    - These posts support SEO and nurture leads by addressing timely operational finance topics.  \n    - Will Fleming committed to reviewing the draft promptly to maintain publishing momentum.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Performance**\n\nThe ABM campaign was restarted on January 2nd and is showing early engagement signs, with ongoing monitoring planned to optimize lead flow.\n\n- **Since reactivation, the ABM campaign has generated seven accepted connections from a workflow targeting 60 to 70 prospects** (13:50)  \n    - Initial low reply volume is attributed to the early stage of the campaign cycle post-holiday pause.  \n    - Guille Santana will track campaign metrics this week to ensure normal engagement levels resume.  \n    - Will Fleming highlighted the campaign as a primary outbound channel to generate qualified leads amid a tough market.  \n    - The campaign supports the broader strategy to fuel sales pipelines despite discretionary spending challenges in the restaurant industry.\n\n- **Will Fleming contextualized the current market environment as cautious but still offering demand for finance and CFO services** (14:49)  \n    - He underscored that economic uncertainty causes decision delays but stressed that inaction is ultimately costlier for clients.  \n    - The 30-day trial offer is positioned as a low-risk entry point to convert hesitant prospects.  \n    - Marketing messaging will focus on building trust and demonstrating measurable short-term impact.  \n    - Fleming sees content and direct outreach as complementary paths to open conversations and identify client needs.\n\n## **Sales and Revenue Target Planning**\n\nSales leadership is preparing to align marketing efforts with revenue goals for 2026, aiming for clearer accountability and direct results from campaigns.\n\n- **Nick S committed to presenting a detailed 2026 sales target split by channel, including marketing-generated leads, direct sales, client expansion, and referrals, at the next meeting** (20:15)  \n    - He plans to share historical sales trends tracked during his tenure to set realistic expectations.  \n    - Nick expressed urgency for marketing activities to yield measurable leads and pipeline growth soon.  \n    - This alignment will enable better resource allocation and performance tracking across teams.  \n    - Bailey’s involvement in the next meeting will ensure cross-functional agreement on targets and strategies.\n\n## **Market and Competitive Context**\n\nThe team recognizes the restaurant sector’s current financial pressure and is adjusting marketing focus to reflect client concerns and market sentiment.\n\n- **Will Fleming noted that 2025 began with optimism but deteriorated due to tariff news and economic uncertainty, influencing buyer behavior** (18:40)  \n    - This uncertainty has suppressed decision-making, creating a window where marketing must build confidence and urgency.  \n    - He emphasized the need to position offerings as timely, practical solutions for restaurants facing cash flow challenges.  \n    - Messaging will highlight how the company’s CFO services can quickly impact financial health within a 30-day window.  \n    - Fleming expects that as market clarity returns, demand will rise, and the team must be ready to capture that momentum.\n\n- **The gated content strategy and ABM efforts are tailored to capture attention in this cautious environment by offering value and trust upfront** (09:22)  \n    - Integrating SEO optimization for emerging AI search tools aims to reach prospects earlier in their decision process.  \n    - The playbook and associated marketing materials will reinforce the company’s expertise and differentiated approach.  \n    - These tactics address competitive pressures by focusing on practical, actionable insights rather than general financial advice.  \n    - The team is mindful of balancing broad reach with quality lead generation to maximize ROI.\n\n## **Process and Operational Improvements**\n\nThe team is streamlining content production and marketing execution to accelerate lead generation and improve campaign responsiveness.\n\n- **Content production leverages existing interviews and internal design/development resources for faster turnaround on gated assets** (05:35)  \n    - Using an ebook over a quiz reduces development time and simplifies rollout while still capturing qualified leads.  \n    - Will Fleming agreed that the ebook is a practical first step, with the quiz potentially explored in a later quarter.  \n    - The ABM campaign workflow is actively monitored for engagement metrics to catch and resolve any issues promptly.  \n    - This iterative approach ensures marketing activities remain responsive to real-time data and market feedback.\n\n- **Coordination across marketing, sales, and leadership is planned to solidify targets and ensure alignment on deliverables and timelines** (20:15)  \n    - Regular reviews of campaign results and sales metrics will enable course corrections and reinforce accountability.  \n    - The team prioritizes clear communication and transparency to maintain momentum in a challenging market.  \n    - Guille Santana is responsible for shepherding content reviews and campaign monitoring to keep projects on track.  \n    - This disciplined approach aims to maximize the impact of limited resources and improve overall marketing ROI.","outline":null,"keywords":["Restaurant CFO","gated content strategy","ABM campaign","cash flow","marketing budget","2026 sales targets"],"overview":"- **Gated Ebook Launch**: A new ebook, \"The Restaurants’ Cash Playbook 2026,\" is planned for Q1 2026 to boost lead capture.  \n- **ABM Campaign Performance**: Seven accepted connections generated from the reactivated ABM campaign targeting 60-70 prospects since January 2nd.  \n- **Sales Target Planning**: Detailed 2026 sales targets by channel will be presented next meeting to align marketing with revenue goals.\n  - Sales targets will be divided by channel, including marketing, direct sales, current clients, and referrals.  \n  - The presentation will include historical sales data to identify trends and set realistic targets for 2026.  \n  - Alignment between marketing efforts and revenue goals will be emphasized to ensure effective resource allocation and strategy execution.  \n- **Market Conditions**: Economic uncertainty impacts decision-making; focus on building trust and urgency in marketing messaging.  \n- **Streamlined Content Production**: Utilizing internal resources for efficient content creation, prioritizing quick turnaround on gated assets.  \n- **Cross-Team Coordination**: Regular reviews planned to ensure accountability and alignment on deliverables among marketing, sales, and leadership.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nResend the blog post \"The ghost of CFO turnover\" for Will Fleming’s review and feedback (07:21)\nBegin production of the gated eBook titled \"The 2026 Restaurant Cash Playbook\" as prioritized gated content (12:51)\nContinue monitoring ABM campaign metrics and report next week on leads and engagement (13:53)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nReview the \"The ghost of CFO turnover\" blog post and provide feedback within the day of the meeting (07:18)\n\n**Nick S**\nPrepare and present the 2026 marketing budget and sales target, including sales channel breakdown and historical trends, at the next weekly meeting with possible Bailey participation (20:15)\n"},"duration":22.479999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":1,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"id":2,"name":"Will Fleming"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam.","index":0,"end_time":202.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.95,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sa.","index":1,"end_time":204.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.48,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Hi, Will.","index":2,"end_time":256.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good to see you.","index":3,"end_time":257.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":258.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":257.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":5,"end_time":260.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":6,"end_time":261.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Same to you.","index":7,"end_time":262.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hi, Nick.","index":8,"end_time":265.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hi.","index":9,"end_time":266.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How are you?","index":10,"end_time":267.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Good, Good.","index":11,"end_time":269.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":12,"end_time":270.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.54,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are the holidays?","index":13,"end_time":272.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.9,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"They''re fantastic.","index":14,"end_time":274.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I love my holidays.","index":15,"end_time":276.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How are yours?","index":16,"end_time":277.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.78,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Great, Great.","index":17,"end_time":279.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Like, can''t complain.","index":18,"end_time":280.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.54,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m Mexican.","index":19,"end_time":282.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.78,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We eat a lot.","index":20,"end_time":283.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.58,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":21,"end_time":288.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But I''m glad.","index":22,"end_time":289.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m glad to hear that.","index":23,"end_time":291.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.29,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"What is, like, the traditional Mexican dish on Christmas time?","index":24,"end_time":296.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":292.21,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Well, depends.","index":25,"end_time":299.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m from the south, so we eat this thing called sandwich on, which is, like, a thick sandwich full of, like, different stuffing.","index":26,"end_time":308.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s.","index":27,"end_time":309.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s great.","index":28,"end_time":309.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sounds delicious.","index":29,"end_time":312.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":312.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It is.","index":30,"end_time":313.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It is.","index":31,"end_time":314.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Just thinking about it, like, there''s something in my brain, but.","index":32,"end_time":321.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.34,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":322.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.78,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Quick note.","index":34,"end_time":324.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Bailey won''t be joining us today.","index":35,"end_time":326.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"She''s traveling, but she''s fully looped on everything we''re covering today.","index":36,"end_time":332.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Just.","index":37,"end_time":333.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.9,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":38,"end_time":333.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.3,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right, let me start sharing my screen.","index":39,"end_time":342.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.46,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One second.","index":40,"end_time":348.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.71,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Nope.","index":41,"end_time":350.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"There we go.","index":42,"end_time":354.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":43,"end_time":357.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''m gonna have to show it like this.","index":44,"end_time":360.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well, today should be pretty straightforward.","index":45,"end_time":367.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We''re going over some content updates, proposed gated content strategy that I have for you guys, and we''re also going over the ABM campaign, which we turned on this week again, so we can start getting some.","index":46,"end_time":384.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Some leads.","index":47,"end_time":385.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.08,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And feel free to interrupt me if you guys have questions.","index":48,"end_time":390.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.92,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":49,"end_time":391.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.89,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right, so starting with the content updates, we have a blog post in progress that''s based on the interview that we did with you.","index":50,"end_time":404.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.89,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s how restaurant operations can regain control of cash flow without adding headcount.","index":51,"end_time":411.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And that''s the one that we have in progress.","index":52,"end_time":415.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I did send one for review.","index":53,"end_time":418.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think that was yesterday, so we can post it this week.","index":54,"end_time":422.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s the ghost of CFO turnover.","index":55,"end_time":425.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s very similar to the one we already published.","index":56,"end_time":428.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.66,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":57,"end_time":429.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Because it''s based on the same interview, but we just want to focus on that.","index":58,"end_time":433.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.82,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"On that topic now that it''s, like, super relevant.","index":59,"end_time":437.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.3,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":60,"end_time":438.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":438.3,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Just so you know, that''s.","index":61,"end_time":440.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I saw a.","index":62,"end_time":442.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.02,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"A lot of meetings, but I don''t know if I.","index":63,"end_time":449.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":443.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Let me just double check.","index":64,"end_time":450.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.39,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You sent that when?","index":65,"end_time":451.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.55,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that was yesterday or the day or Monday.","index":66,"end_time":458.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, let me just make sure I have that now.","index":67,"end_time":466.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.55,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Can you resend that?","index":68,"end_time":467.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.55,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t see that.","index":69,"end_time":468.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.75,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I saw.","index":70,"end_time":469.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, wait, here it is.","index":71,"end_time":471.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.47,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I have it.","index":72,"end_time":471.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.34,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":472.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I will review this today and respond today.","index":74,"end_time":478.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it.","index":75,"end_time":480.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.9,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All righty.","index":76,"end_time":481.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And just so you know, the last published blog post that was on December 30th.","index":77,"end_time":486.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s.","index":78,"end_time":488.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.82,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"What is the restaurant CFO talent crisis?","index":79,"end_time":490.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s.","index":80,"end_time":491.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":491.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Your review of it is already up There no major blockers here.","index":81,"end_time":498.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I just wanted to show you where everything.","index":82,"end_time":500.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Like, where it stands.","index":83,"end_time":502.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":84,"end_time":503.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.76,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":85,"end_time":503.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then the main thing I wanted to, like, spend time today is on this proposed gated content strategy that we have.","index":86,"end_time":514.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I was talking to Bailey, and we were thinking a good move will be to create some gated content.","index":87,"end_time":521.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So, like an ebook, a guide, a white paper, basically something.","index":88,"end_time":526.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.24,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Basically a piece of content that''s behind a form so that operators that actually care about whatever we''re writing, they will have to fill a form to get it right.","index":89,"end_time":539.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And that will let us capture leads from people who are already in this mindset.","index":90,"end_time":545.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I was also thinking we could optimize it for LLMs, so put it on, like, queries that people will ask on chat GPT, because that''s trending right now in terms of SEO.","index":91,"end_time":561.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So.","index":92,"end_time":562.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.63,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sure, I think it''s a great idea.","index":93,"end_time":564.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":566.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So these are the.","index":95,"end_time":567.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I did my research, and these are, like, three good ebooks that we could do, but they all serve, like, a different.","index":96,"end_time":578.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.11,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Slightly different purpose.","index":97,"end_time":580.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But I would love to know what your gut reaction here is.","index":98,"end_time":586.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.24,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Which one feels more aligned to what we do?","index":99,"end_time":590.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"What could lead the conversation this year?","index":100,"end_time":593.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And which one do you think would be more useful for your sales team?","index":101,"end_time":598.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.88,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And this will be pretty easy to do because we have designers, we have developers.","index":102,"end_time":604.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s.","index":103,"end_time":604.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s just like writing a big blog post.","index":104,"end_time":606.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":105,"end_time":607.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.98,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But out of these three, do you think one will work or do you think something else would work?","index":106,"end_time":614.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.26,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s this three.","index":107,"end_time":616.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.06,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think the last one''s good.","index":108,"end_time":619.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know if it makes sense just to get a little bit more specific.","index":109,"end_time":625.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it says here, is it time for a CFO or just a better finance team or something like that?","index":110,"end_time":633.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Because it''s just.","index":111,"end_time":634.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.25,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Or better finances is.","index":112,"end_time":637.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":113,"end_time":639.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.97,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Or just.","index":114,"end_time":642.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.77,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Just a better finance team.","index":115,"end_time":644.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":642.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Something like that.","index":116,"end_time":647.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, that''s.","index":117,"end_time":648.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That I think is clear.","index":118,"end_time":651.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.69,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think.","index":119,"end_time":654.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.45,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The second one is good.","index":120,"end_time":660.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that''s.","index":121,"end_time":661.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"People will be drawn to that.","index":122,"end_time":667,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.12,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The first one, I don''t know if they''re the same.","index":123,"end_time":672.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, you know, there''s enough difference between the two of them, the first one and the second one.","index":124,"end_time":679.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think the second one is good.","index":125,"end_time":680.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know if it makes sense for the first one to be specific.","index":126,"end_time":685.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, general ebooks, because that one seems more general, whereas the next two seem specific.","index":127,"end_time":695.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think people.","index":128,"end_time":698.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":696.63,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think for these types of things, something that''s really important and specific and not just a limited topic, I think you can ultimately, like the.","index":129,"end_time":709.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.47,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The clarity that restaurants want is around cash Or, I mean, you can, but if we had the word cash in the first one, maybe financial, you know, restaurants, you know, cash playbook or something like that.","index":130,"end_time":731.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think it can be the same.","index":131,"end_time":733.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like, you can use some of the same information.","index":132,"end_time":736.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, obviously we''ll have to be specific to cash, but I think you probably want to take out the word financial.","index":133,"end_time":743.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The restaurant cash playbook.","index":134,"end_time":747.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, but just make it so.","index":135,"end_time":749.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.96,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The restaurants cash playbook.","index":136,"end_time":753.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So it would be possessive.","index":137,"end_time":755.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So restaurants.","index":138,"end_time":756.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":139,"end_time":758.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"With apostrophe before the S before.","index":140,"end_time":763,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":141,"end_time":765.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.41,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think that will get people''s attention.","index":142,"end_time":768.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that the label will be nice to start with.","index":143,"end_time":776.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And maybe for next quarter or anytime soon, we could do the quiz.","index":144,"end_time":783.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It will be a good idea to see how it behaves.","index":145,"end_time":787.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":784.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If people actually download it, we can put it in the newsletter.","index":146,"end_time":791.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And since it''s an ebook, so it will be easier to do than the quiz, because the quiz will need our developers to build it.","index":147,"end_time":799.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Not that that takes more time.","index":148,"end_time":802.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right.","index":149,"end_time":803.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":802.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I guess we''ll start working on this one.","index":150,"end_time":808.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.49,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":151,"end_time":811.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then the ABM campaign, it was turned off for the holidays.","index":152,"end_time":819.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It was just turned on this week on the second.","index":153,"end_time":821.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So so far we have seven connections accepted, and there''s around 60 to 70 people in the workflow.","index":154,"end_time":830.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.56,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So that''s why you''re not seeing replies.","index":155,"end_time":833.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Connection sent, email sent.","index":156,"end_time":835.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"But we''ll monitor it this week just so that.","index":157,"end_time":838.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That we know that people are coming in, that nothing.","index":158,"end_time":843.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Nothing''s wrong with them, and we should be seeing, like, the right numbers next week.","index":159,"end_time":848.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":160,"end_time":849.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":849.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yep.","index":161,"end_time":851.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And last but not least, we can go over bolts.","index":162,"end_time":856.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.37,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This is what it looks like, what we''re working on right now.","index":163,"end_time":865.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And this is your points.","index":164,"end_time":869.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.37,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Balance points in working.","index":165,"end_time":870.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.53,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":166,"end_time":872.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":167,"end_time":874.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And honestly, that''s it from me.","index":168,"end_time":878.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys have any questions.","index":169,"end_time":881.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Want to talk about, like, this year, what you guys want to do, if you''re fine with what we''re doing.","index":170,"end_time":888.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the content''s been very good.","index":171,"end_time":893.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Obviously, the ABM campaign, we started it last year.","index":172,"end_time":900.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, we''re really looking forward to that being, you know, offering leads.","index":173,"end_time":906.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, we''re.","index":174,"end_time":907.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s a challenging market right now, just with the.","index":175,"end_time":912.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, this generally discretionary income, like, you know, money that it''s available in households to go out and be in a rest.","index":176,"end_time":925.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You know, spend money in a restaurant is not a good.","index":177,"end_time":929.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The best time for that.","index":178,"end_time":930.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think restaurants are feeling a lot of pressure.","index":179,"end_time":934.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.14,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think we can help them with the finance CFO services.","index":180,"end_time":938.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I mean, so, I mean, what we would.","index":181,"end_time":943.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"What we''re really hopeful for is to get a lot of activity, whether it''s through the SEO with the content or through the direct campaign really being our primary outbound marketing activity.","index":182,"end_time":965.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I don''t think last year was, because we started it just before the holidays, was a good enough test, but we think the demand is still very strong for the services.","index":183,"end_time":981.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":965.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I think it''s a more difficult decision to make because if you''re not sure about what''s coming, it can be hard to make changes.","index":184,"end_time":995.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.14,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And as you know, with the offering, we''re offering 30 days and I think that we can make a real impact even in that short period of time.","index":185,"end_time":1007.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So, you know, we want to be heard and we think the demand is still there.","index":186,"end_time":1014.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We know it''s going to be a little bit more difficult to get people''s attention or to engage in a discussion with us.","index":187,"end_time":1022.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.31,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I mean, I think that that gated content is a good approach to try to get people, you know, up coming because, I mean, ultimately it''s, it''s.","index":188,"end_time":1039.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, people want to save money, but they, they really need the answer like, what''s, you know, what is the, what can we say to them that makes, that allows them to think more confidently about 2026?","index":189,"end_time":1055.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that''s, I mean, that''s what we want to convey in the marketing.","index":190,"end_time":1061.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"A, A sort of a.","index":191,"end_time":1066.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1062.57,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Our expertise or that we''re trusted and we can, it''s, it''s a good use of their time to come to us.","index":192,"end_time":1073.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1067.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Even if, you know, they''re not ready, they want the 30 days or whatever or just, I mean, I think anything we can do to open people up to conversations, we can find more about them and then it''s easier for us to, to find a way to help them.","index":193,"end_time":1091.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1073.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think it''s going to be very important this year, the content, the message and how we are perceived.","index":194,"end_time":1100.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.47,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":195,"end_time":1102.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I was thinking with what you said, maybe to the playbook, we could add the year so the 2026 playbook, so that people know it''s relevant, it''s new.","index":196,"end_time":1112.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And since you said so, like, it''s challenging times right now.","index":197,"end_time":1116.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, that could be a good one to live with.","index":198,"end_time":1120.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.79,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I think so.","index":199,"end_time":1121.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.51,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, it''s, if we look back in 2025, there was a lot of, there was a lot of hope.","index":200,"end_time":1132.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1121.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There was like, I guess from January, February, March there, there was a lot of optimism.","index":201,"end_time":1138.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.15,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Our pipeline was, was very active.","index":202,"end_time":1141.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.67,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then when the tariff news came out, that kind of changed things and people got a little bit more nervous and that sentiment is continuing.","index":203,"end_time":1152.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I also believe that at some point, confusion in the marketplace causes people to wait.","index":204,"end_time":1161.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They don''t want to make a decision.","index":205,"end_time":1163.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But also at the same time, at some point, you just.","index":206,"end_time":1168.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Life has to continue and people have to make decisions and things have to continue.","index":207,"end_time":1173.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1168.15,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think you''re in that moment.","index":208,"end_time":1175.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like you.","index":209,"end_time":1177.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.99,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s.","index":210,"end_time":1177.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.35,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s.","index":211,"end_time":1178.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1177.75,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Maybe it''s not the.","index":212,"end_time":1179.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.39,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You never like.","index":213,"end_time":1181.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.59,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Nobody wants to make it a difficult decision at the wrong moment, but at some point, no decision is worse.","index":214,"end_time":1187.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think we''re in the moment where people are going to start making decisions, and I think the market.","index":215,"end_time":1192.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1187.43,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hopefully we''ll improve some.","index":216,"end_time":1195.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1193.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we want to be there when they decide it''s time to move.","index":217,"end_time":1201.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1197.94,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it.","index":218,"end_time":1203.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.5,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":219,"end_time":1203.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1203.38,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let go soon.","index":220,"end_time":1204.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.02,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Those are my thoughts on 26.","index":221,"end_time":1209.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So.","index":222,"end_time":1209.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think your point about the year is good.","index":223,"end_time":1212.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":224,"end_time":1213.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":225,"end_time":1214.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1214.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well, can I say something real quick?","index":226,"end_time":1218.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yay.","index":227,"end_time":1219.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.7,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yes.","index":228,"end_time":1219.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And will.","index":229,"end_time":1220.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.31,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So we put a budget together for 2026.","index":230,"end_time":1225.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1222.39,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"A sales target.","index":231,"end_time":1226.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.91,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And what I''ve always done is I''ve split the budget into a percentage of the channels and how we do sales.","index":232,"end_time":1238.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1228.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Get them via marketing.","index":233,"end_time":1240.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Via direct.","index":234,"end_time":1241.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Via current clients, adding stores or upgrading services and then referrals.","index":235,"end_time":1249.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And what I like to do at the next meeting.","index":236,"end_time":1252.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.34,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I have it now, but I''ll wait.","index":237,"end_time":1255.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.7,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe Bailey would join us too.","index":238,"end_time":1256.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Is next week meeting and share what I had in mind, as in the total amount of revenue that should come in from being effort.","index":239,"end_time":1268.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like Bill said, the content has been great.","index":240,"end_time":1272.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Everything''s been going really well.","index":241,"end_time":1275.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.83,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Being on the sales and development side, I''m getting a little antsy.","index":242,"end_time":1279.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I want some direct results from the good content and from the good campaigns.","index":243,"end_time":1285.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And what I''ll do is.","index":244,"end_time":1288.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":245,"end_time":1290.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.509,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"His connection didn''t sound so good.","index":246,"end_time":1294.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.47,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Maybe he''ll come back.","index":247,"end_time":1295.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1294.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But he manages the.","index":248,"end_time":1299.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.63,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Oh, here he is.","index":249,"end_time":1303.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know where I cut off.","index":250,"end_time":1306.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.14,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":251,"end_time":1307.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1306.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I was talking about the.","index":252,"end_time":1310.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.9,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"The sales target for marketing.","index":253,"end_time":1311.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Next year we could talk about that.","index":254,"end_time":1312.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1313.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.3,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then I''ll share with, like, the results that I have been keeping since my tenure here at gss and to show you the trend and what I''m looking for for 2026, if that''s old.","index":256,"end_time":1325.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1315.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, Sounds good.","index":257,"end_time":1327.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326.08,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Great.","index":258,"end_time":1330,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.6,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":259,"end_time":1330.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s it for me.","index":260,"end_time":1332.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"All right.","index":261,"end_time":1333.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Nice to see you and we''ll be in touch.","index":262,"end_time":1338.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1335.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thanks so much.","index":263,"end_time":1338.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":264,"end_time":1339.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.96,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":265,"end_time":1340.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1339.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"See you next week.","index":266,"end_time":1341.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.44,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Bye.","index":267,"end_time":1341.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.359,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"}],"dateString":"2026-01-07T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81010350325?pwd=qJCrbL10kdxdmKpMcLq7aanFQIBZ5h.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE098Y68WF16KGM5MZQES1G0","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Proposed gated content strategy aims to capture leads through high-intent downloadable assets.","Will approved optimizing content for SEO with LLM queries to boost discoverability.","Recent blog post published Dec 30; no blockers flagged with content pipeline.","ABM campaign reactivated Jan 2; early engagement includes 7 connections accepted.","Nick to present 2026 marketing revenue targets and historical trends in next week’s meeting."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think the content''s been very good.","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"There no major blockers here.","speaker":"Guille Santana"},{"quote":"Everything''s been going really well.","speaker":"Nick S (GSS)"}],"topics":["content","ABM","leadgen","budget"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Development**\n\nThe team is advancing targeted content to drive engagement and lead capture with a new gated ebook planned for Q1 2026. \n\n- **Guille Santana proposed creating a gated ebook titled \"The Restaurants’ Cash Playbook 2026\" to capture leads by requiring form submissions for downloads** (05:35)  \n    - The ebook will focus on cash flow management for restaurant operators, a pressing concern given current market pressures.  \n    - Will Fleming emphasized the importance of specificity and relevance, recommending the addition of the year 2026 to signal freshness and relevance.  \n    - The content team will leverage existing resources and internal designers and developers to produce the ebook efficiently, targeting a Q1 release.  \n    - Optimizing for large language models like ChatGPT was suggested to boost SEO and capture emerging search trends.\n\n- **Ongoing blog content includes a post titled \"The Ghost of CFO Turnover,\" scheduled for review and publishing this week** (06:32)  \n    - This piece builds on prior interviews and aligns with the theme of CFO challenges in the restaurant sector.  \n    - The last blog was published on December 30th, focusing on the restaurant CFO talent crisis, with no current blockers.  \n    - These posts support SEO and nurture leads by addressing timely operational finance topics.  \n    - Will Fleming committed to reviewing the draft promptly to maintain publishing momentum.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Performance**\n\nThe ABM campaign was restarted on January 2nd and is showing early engagement signs, with ongoing monitoring planned to optimize lead flow.\n\n- **Since reactivation, the ABM campaign has generated seven accepted connections from a workflow targeting 60 to 70 prospects** (13:50)  \n    - Initial low reply volume is attributed to the early stage of the campaign cycle post-holiday pause.  \n    - Guille Santana will track campaign metrics this week to ensure normal engagement levels resume.  \n    - Will Fleming highlighted the campaign as a primary outbound channel to generate qualified leads amid a tough market.  \n    - The campaign supports the broader strategy to fuel sales pipelines despite discretionary spending challenges in the restaurant industry.\n\n- **Will Fleming contextualized the current market environment as cautious but still offering demand for finance and CFO services** (14:49)  \n    - He underscored that economic uncertainty causes decision delays but stressed that inaction is ultimately costlier for clients.  \n    - The 30-day trial offer is positioned as a low-risk entry point to convert hesitant prospects.  \n    - Marketing messaging will focus on building trust and demonstrating measurable short-term impact.  \n    - Fleming sees content and direct outreach as complementary paths to open conversations and identify client needs.\n\n## **Sales and Revenue Target Planning**\n\nSales leadership is preparing to align marketing efforts with revenue goals for 2026, aiming for clearer accountability and direct results from campaigns.\n\n- **Nick S committed to presenting a detailed 2026 sales target split by channel, including marketing-generated leads, direct sales, client expansion, and referrals, at the next meeting** (20:15)  \n    - He plans to share historical sales trends tracked during his tenure to set realistic expectations.  \n    - Nick expressed urgency for marketing activities to yield measurable leads and pipeline growth soon.  \n    - This alignment will enable better resource allocation and performance tracking across teams.  \n    - Bailey’s involvement in the next meeting will ensure cross-functional agreement on targets and strategies.\n\n## **Market and Competitive Context**\n\nThe team recognizes the restaurant sector’s current financial pressure and is adjusting marketing focus to reflect client concerns and market sentiment.\n\n- **Will Fleming noted that 2025 began with optimism but deteriorated due to tariff news and economic uncertainty, influencing buyer behavior** (18:40)  \n    - This uncertainty has suppressed decision-making, creating a window where marketing must build confidence and urgency.  \n    - He emphasized the need to position offerings as timely, practical solutions for restaurants facing cash flow challenges.  \n    - Messaging will highlight how the company’s CFO services can quickly impact financial health within a 30-day window.  \n    - Fleming expects that as market clarity returns, demand will rise, and the team must be ready to capture that momentum.\n\n- **The gated content strategy and ABM efforts are tailored to capture attention in this cautious environment by offering value and trust upfront** (09:22)  \n    - Integrating SEO optimization for emerging AI search tools aims to reach prospects earlier in their decision process.  \n    - The playbook and associated marketing materials will reinforce the company’s expertise and differentiated approach.  \n    - These tactics address competitive pressures by focusing on practical, actionable insights rather than general financial advice.  \n    - The team is mindful of balancing broad reach with quality lead generation to maximize ROI.\n\n## **Process and Operational Improvements**\n\nThe team is streamlining content production and marketing execution to accelerate lead generation and improve campaign responsiveness.\n\n- **Content production leverages existing interviews and internal design/development resources for faster turnaround on gated assets** (05:35)  \n    - Using an ebook over a quiz reduces development time and simplifies rollout while still capturing qualified leads.  \n    - Will Fleming agreed that the ebook is a practical first step, with the quiz potentially explored in a later quarter.  \n    - The ABM campaign workflow is actively monitored for engagement metrics to catch and resolve any issues promptly.  \n    - This iterative approach ensures marketing activities remain responsive to real-time data and market feedback.\n\n- **Coordination across marketing, sales, and leadership is planned to solidify targets and ensure alignment on deliverables and timelines** (20:15)  \n    - Regular reviews of campaign results and sales metrics will enable course corrections and reinforce accountability.  \n    - The team prioritizes clear communication and transparency to maintain momentum in a challenging market.  \n    - Guille Santana is responsible for shepherding content reviews and campaign monitoring to keep projects on track.  \n    - This disciplined approach aims to maximize the impact of limited resources and improve overall marketing ROI.","outline":null,"keywords":["Restaurant CFO","gated content strategy","ABM campaign","cash flow","marketing budget","2026 sales targets"],"overview":"- **Gated Ebook Launch**: A new ebook, \"The Restaurants’ Cash Playbook 2026,\" is planned for Q1 2026 to boost lead capture.  \n- **ABM Campaign Performance**: Seven accepted connections generated from the reactivated ABM campaign targeting 60-70 prospects since January 2nd.  \n- **Sales Target Planning**: Detailed 2026 sales targets by channel will be presented next meeting to align marketing with revenue goals.\n  - Sales targets will be divided by channel, including marketing, direct sales, current clients, and referrals.  \n  - The presentation will include historical sales data to identify trends and set realistic targets for 2026.  \n  - Alignment between marketing efforts and revenue goals will be emphasized to ensure effective resource allocation and strategy execution.  \n- **Market Conditions**: Economic uncertainty impacts decision-making; focus on building trust and urgency in marketing messaging.  \n- **Streamlined Content Production**: Utilizing internal resources for efficient content creation, prioritizing quick turnaround on gated assets.  \n- **Cross-Team Coordination**: Regular reviews planned to ensure accountability and alignment on deliverables among marketing, sales, and leadership.","action_items":"\n**Guille Santana**\nResend the blog post \"The ghost of CFO turnover\" for Will Fleming’s review and feedback (07:21)\nBegin production of the gated eBook titled \"The 2026 Restaurant Cash Playbook\" as prioritized gated content (12:51)\nContinue monitoring ABM campaign metrics and report next week on leads and engagement (13:53)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nReview the \"The ghost of CFO turnover\" blog post and provide feedback within the day of the meeting (07:18)\n\n**Nick S**\nPrepare and present the 2026 marketing budget and sales target, including sales channel breakdown and historical trends, at the next weekly meeting with possible Bailey participation (20:15)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"95c5fbfe-ed50-44a3-9a68-121dc035d19e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
