WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ff2ef389-756d-4ece-b525-93fab32170d6',
    '2026-01-08 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE83814EHHRY5JCHPW4N7H9T',
    'New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Dan Rényi","Lauren Poirier"}'::text[],
    2127,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KE83814EHHRY5JCHPW4N7H9T","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Shift from Awareness to Lead Generation**\n\nThe campaign focus will move from broad brand awareness to targeted lead generation, aiming for quality leads that sales can engage effectively (02:22).\n\n- **Completed awareness campaign used three senders with three domains**, enabling delivery despite initial pauses, which helped secure new contacts and distribute materials broadly.\n    - The team segmented contacts into **seven new categories** to better tailor lead generation messaging.\n    - Taylor emphasized the need to shift away from awareness messaging to a **faster, more focused lead generation approach** due to a tight timeline ending in **April**.\n    - Lauren agreed this shift should concentrate on a **smaller, more qualified lead pool** that sales can actively pursue.\n    - This pivot aligns with the marketing roadmap and leverages insights from prior outreach to optimize impact.\n\n- **Taylor and Dan reviewed Lauren’s proposed messaging sequence and found it too similar to previous brand awareness efforts** (04:28).\n    - They recommended adopting new messaging focused on **lead qualification and conversion speed** rather than broad awareness.\n    - Lauren confirmed the prior messaging lacked sufficient title-specific tailoring but agreed to pivot toward outcome-driven messaging to meet lead generation goals.\n\n## **Lead Qualification, Buyer Insights, and Revenue Context**\n\nUnderstanding lead quality, buyer roles, and contract values is critical for campaign targeting and sales alignment (05:09).\n\n- **Lauren clarified the average contract value for university clients is in the six-figure range**, with recurring revenue also likely in that range, varying by deployment model (on-premise vs. cloud) (06:13).\n    - This underscores the **high-value nature of each contract**, necessitating precise targeting and longer sales cycles.\n\n- **Dan probed the buying group composition for universities, revealing three main drivers for purchase decisions** (07:12).\n    - Facilities managers and directors lead on asset and maintenance management.\n    - Space optimization is critical due to enrollment declines and funding cuts.\n    - IT teams focus on consolidating disparate point solutions into integrated systems.\n    - Lauren will confirm typical buying paths with sales to refine campaign targeting.\n\n- **Warm leads often come from content engagement but rarely convert immediately** as they require extended nurturing (10:28).\n    - Lauren indicated warm leads usually gather information but are not ready for demos or sales conversations.\n    - The sales team sees low response rates from these leads despite strong open and click rates.\n    - Dan suggested mining nurture stream data to identify which touchpoints contribute to eventual closed deals, enabling optimization of nurturing efforts.\n    - Lauren can share lead source breakdowns showing events and direct web visits among top sources, but lacks detailed tracking of nurture effectiveness tied to closed deals.\n\n## **Campaign Process Improvements: Sandbox Testing and Intent-Based Outreach**\n\nIntroducing a sandbox test environment and intent-based outreach will accelerate learning and improve targeting precision (17:53).\n\n- **Dan proposed a sandbox testing approach focusing on a limited set of accounts (e.g., 200) where the team can rapidly test and adjust campaigns without lengthy approvals** (17:53).\n    - This approach could triple decision speed and reduce delays seen in prior LinkedIn campaign launches.\n    - Lauren likes the idea but anticipates leadership concerns over trust and brand control.\n    - She will seek leadership buy-in and requested supporting slides with expected outcomes and scope for approval.\n    - Dan committed to delivering these materials to aid internal advocacy.\n\n- **Intent-based outreach will target accounts showing multiple high-intent signals across channels like email and LinkedIn ads to improve hit rates** (21:43).\n    - This method narrows outreach to engaged prospects, contrasting with broad mass campaigns.\n    - Running ads alongside cold emails is planned to generate these signals.\n    - Taylor confirmed intent data and ad integration are included in upcoming campaign plans.\n\n## **Strategic Discovery Research to Inform Messaging and Sales**\n\nA research-driven outreach will gather insights from target prospects, improving messaging and enabling tailored sales conversations (23:21).\n\n- **Dan suggested conducting an expert research study titled something like “State of Facilities Operations at American Universities 2026”**, engaging facility managers in qualitative interviews to gather buying journey insights and pain points (23:21).\n    - The study would involve **15 to 20 expert interviews** to establish credibility and provide valuable content.\n    - Follow-up emails would reference individual pain points raised, creating warm sales leads.\n    - Lauren strongly supported the idea, noting alignment with LinkedIn connection messaging and the potential need for a new report asset.\n    - Dan described the final deliverable as a polished 20+ page report, usable as a gated asset or exclusive sales collateral.\n\n- **Lauren recalled a similar 2018 survey of higher ed leaders remaining a popular nurture asset**, indicating the power of this approach.\n    - She will locate and share that asset as a reference.\n    - Lauren will assess her team’s capacity to conduct the prospecting conversations required.\n    - Dan and Taylor will provide written summaries of this and sandbox ideas for sharing with leadership.\n\n## **Next Steps, Contract Status, and Documentation**\n\nClear planning documents and contract updates will support campaign execution and leadership alignment (34:46).\n\n- **Lauren requested a written four-month plan detailing activities, goals, and expected outcomes to present to leadership** (34:46).\n    - Taylor agreed to deliver a month-by-month plan once the campaign approach is finalized.\n    - The plan will incorporate feedback and provide clarity on resource allocation and timelines.\n\n- **Lauren noted the contract extension is still under legal review, delayed by holidays** (33:57).\n    - She will continue following up to expedite completion.\n\n- **Taylor and Dan committed to sharing all discussed ideas, including the sandbox and research proposals, in writing to facilitate internal discussions** (29:21).\n    - This documentation aims to secure leadership buy-in for new agile approaches and research-driven campaigns.\n    - Lauren will gather feedback and relay it back to the team.\n\n- **Lauren emphasized targeting the 395 R1 universities identified as best fits for Planon** (30:45).\n    - Even limited targeting within this group would provide valuable insights and lead generation opportunities.\n    - Dan confirmed the list can be leveraged for both sandbox testing and research outreach.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","Lead Generation","Nurturing","Sandbox Testing","Intent-based Outreach","Discovery Research"],"overview":"- **Campaign Shift:** Move from brand awareness to targeted lead generation, focusing on quality leads for sales engagement.  \n- **Lead Categorization:** Contacts are now segmented into seven categories to tailor messaging for lead generation effectively.  \n- **Contract Value Insight:** Average contract value for university clients is six-figure, emphasizing need for precise targeting and longer sales cycles.  \n- **Sandbox Testing Proposal:** Test approach with 200 accounts to improve campaign adjustments and decision speed without lengthy approvals.  \n- **Research Study Initiative:** Conduct interviews with facilities managers to gain insights and prepare a report on buying journeys in universities.  \n- **Planning Documentation:** Request for a four-month plan detailing activities and goals to align with leadership for campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nConfirm with sales team the typical buying group composition and decision-making process for university clients to ensure alignment on campaign targeting (09:40)\nVerify with sales whether demos are recorded and if sales team captures lead source info during demos; evaluate opportunities for improvement (17:00)\nPresent the sandbox testing approach and discovery research study concepts to internal marketing leadership and Jay’s team to gauge interest and capacity; provide feedback to Taylor and Dan (20:50)\nFollow up with legal on contract extension status and update marketing partners accordingly (33:50)\nShare prior survey asset from 2018 related to higher education leaders with Taylor and Dan for potential reuse or inspiration (28:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nPrepare and deliver slides and written talking points detailing sandbox approach, benefits, goals, and target accounts to Lauren to assist in internal pitching (21:30)\nDraft a comprehensive, month-by-month 4-month campaign plan detailing activities, goals, outcomes aligned with leadership expectations; send to Lauren for leadership review (34:50)\n"},"duration":35.45000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Dan Rényi"},{"id":2,"name":"Lauren Poirier"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Just be us today.","index":0,"end_time":0.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good ideas.","index":1,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Sandbox.","index":2,"end_time":5.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":9.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":4,"end_time":11.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":5,"end_time":12.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have a bunch of snow, which is awesome.","index":6,"end_time":14.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":7,"end_time":17.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":8,"end_time":17.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, Lauren, just want to introduce you.","index":9,"end_time":19.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is one of our senior strategists, Dan here.","index":10,"end_time":22.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"He''s knows a lot about ebm, so we''re going to bring him into discussion today to kind of walk through some things.","index":11,"end_time":27.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But just a brief introduction, but did you have a good Christmas, Lauren?","index":12,"end_time":31.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did, yeah.","index":13,"end_time":33.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":31.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It was a nice break.","index":14,"end_time":34.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":33.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Definitely a hectic first week back.","index":15,"end_time":36.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":34.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it''s always the hardest Monday of the year is what they call it, so.","index":16,"end_time":40.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":36.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But it was a nice break.","index":17,"end_time":42.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.31,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How was yours?","index":18,"end_time":43.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It was all right.","index":19,"end_time":44.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Me and my whole family pretty much got sick, so that wasn''t fun.","index":20,"end_time":47.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we released together, so I''ll take that.","index":21,"end_time":50.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But you''re like the fifth person I hear that from.","index":22,"end_time":53.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How was Christmas?","index":23,"end_time":54.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Oh, the whole family was out sick.","index":24,"end_time":56.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Blow.","index":25,"end_time":57.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I feel like it''s going around.","index":26,"end_time":59.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like everybody''s kind of getting it right now, so.","index":27,"end_time":62.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think our entire headquarters has the flu right now, so.","index":28,"end_time":65.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":62.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, it makes sense that time of year.","index":29,"end_time":69.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":30,"end_time":70.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ve never been more thankful to work from home, to be honest.","index":31,"end_time":73.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":71.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I know, right?","index":32,"end_time":75.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It sucks when you have to, like, go into the office and you''re not feeling good.","index":33,"end_time":78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"At least here you have, like, your drinks, everything.","index":34,"end_time":80.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You can take medicine and.","index":35,"end_time":82.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":36,"end_time":83.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But anyway.","index":37,"end_time":85.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":38,"end_time":87.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, yeah, I just wanted to jump in with you for abm.","index":39,"end_time":90.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me share my screen here.","index":40,"end_time":91.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I kind of wanted to give, like, an overview of kind of where we''re at now and where we''re, like, hoping to shift into.","index":41,"end_time":97.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just to start out, obviously our original goal when we first started working together was an awareness campaign, which has now been run through and complete, which is really great.","index":42,"end_time":106.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Something I wanted to note, too, is just having the three different senders and each of them having three different domains was super helpful to be able to get through that because I know we started it, paused it, and then restarted it.","index":43,"end_time":119.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it''s good that we were able to get that awareness sequence out, so we were still able to get those new names to you guys and at least get a lot of the materials that we had created out to the contacts.","index":44,"end_time":128.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So now that that''s complete, obviously we want to shift our attention and focus out of that idea of the new names.","index":45,"end_time":136.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know this.","index":46,"end_time":136.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I pulled this from our marketing roadmap that we had originally talked about.","index":47,"end_time":139.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we''ve talked about this a few times now how we.","index":48,"end_time":142.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to shift our to Lead generation.","index":49,"end_time":144.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just kind of gave, like, an example here of how we can show that we''ll get into, like, the specifics of what qualifies our lead.","index":50,"end_time":152.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we want to obviously create those separate messaging for.","index":51,"end_time":156.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To obviously cater to different audiences and break them down into different groups.","index":52,"end_time":161.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":156.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I sent you yesterday afternoon the revamp spreadsheet.","index":53,"end_time":165.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we had our team go through and do the separation that you asked for with the seven new categories.","index":54,"end_time":170.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":55,"end_time":170.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that is complete.","index":56,"end_time":171.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s just good to have in our back pocket with.","index":57,"end_time":173.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"With whatever way we go for the lead generation.","index":58,"end_time":175.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we wanted to just make sure we are aligned in the sense that this is not going to be about brand awareness anymore, like, specifically new names, since we''ve already done that.","index":59,"end_time":185.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This will be more specific to getting your team leads, what specific leads you''re looking for.","index":60,"end_time":192.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I know you sent us a lot of great information over teams, so I have that incorporated in the next slide here.","index":61,"end_time":198.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, does that all sound good to you?","index":62,"end_time":201.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And corrective?","index":63,"end_time":202.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of like the trajectory of how we''re going to go now and shift?","index":64,"end_time":205.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":202.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":65,"end_time":205.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":66,"end_time":206.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I agree.","index":67,"end_time":207.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Focusing more on lead gen.","index":68,"end_time":209.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Probably a smaller number of people that are, you know, coming out of that, but yeah, I agree.","index":69,"end_time":216.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Leads that can be passed off to sales, for sure.","index":70,"end_time":219.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":71,"end_time":220.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":72,"end_time":221.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so something I just wanted to mention, too is I know you had sent me kind of like an idea for a new messaging sequence, and I was going through it, but it''s super, super similar to what we''ve already done in the sense that it''s kind of more brand awareness.","index":73,"end_time":234.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It does cater to the groups a little bit better, but I think instead of reworking that same messaging, we should kind of use like a.","index":74,"end_time":241.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A faster way to kind of drive that outreach and get the leads that we need.","index":75,"end_time":245.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we also kind of have that time crunch now, only till April, and it''s tougher to kind of learn each, you know, campaign with a smaller time frame.","index":76,"end_time":253.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So in that case, we have a couple of ideas that we''re going to present and get to.","index":77,"end_time":257.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I just want to let you know, I think it''d be better to shift out of that same kind of messaging and, and change our approach just so that we can get some lead gen out of it.","index":78,"end_time":266.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Does that sound good to you?","index":79,"end_time":267.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It does, yeah.","index":80,"end_time":269.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"My only goal with updating that messaging sequence at that point was tailoring the messaging more for the individual titles, since I know we kind of started out just sending everybody pretty much the same thing.","index":81,"end_time":281.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that was.","index":82,"end_time":282.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":281.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was the goal there.","index":83,"end_time":283.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But no, I Completely agree.","index":84,"end_time":284.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If we need to pivot our messaging to be a little more focused on the outcome, I''m definitely agreement there.","index":85,"end_time":290.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":86,"end_time":291.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":87,"end_time":292.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just incorporated some of your feedback.","index":88,"end_time":295.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I kind of just condensed it here that you had sent us.","index":89,"end_time":298.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll pass over to Dan though.","index":90,"end_time":300.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know Dan had a couple of additional outstanding questions before we get into the specific ideas, but this is just a reiteration of what you had sent us.","index":91,"end_time":307.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s great that you have MQLs and SQLs like so well defined because it makes life easier.","index":92,"end_time":316.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":318.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So Lauren, I just, I, I was just wondering and I don''t know if you''ve talked about this but like whereabouts is your average contract value?","index":94,"end_time":328.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So when a university site, like specifically with universities.","index":95,"end_time":333.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So what are we looking at in terms of annual revenue from, from your clients?","index":96,"end_time":339.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I don''t have that data offhand.","index":97,"end_time":343.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s ballpark.","index":98,"end_time":344.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":99,"end_time":344.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So is it like in the 1020s, 30s or the 100, 150, 200 or so?","index":100,"end_time":351.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Just a rough idea.","index":101,"end_time":352.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Well, depends a little bit.","index":102,"end_time":359.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Let me think here.","index":103,"end_time":360.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I tend to think of things based on contract value, not necessarily ARR.","index":104,"end_time":366.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"When we close a deal.","index":105,"end_time":371.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":369.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Six figures.","index":106,"end_time":373.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Six figures, right.","index":107,"end_time":374.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":375.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":109,"end_time":375.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":375.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"The recurring revenue is probably, probably still in the six figure range.","index":110,"end_time":380.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":111,"end_time":381.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, so when you say when you close a contract, is that, is that not an annual contract?","index":112,"end_time":386.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Is it shorter or.","index":113,"end_time":387.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"It depends.","index":114,"end_time":388.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Some universities want to host everything on their own, we call it on premise.","index":115,"end_time":393.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Others have everything stored in the cloud, which is an annual recurring revenue model.","index":116,"end_time":399.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So it just depends a little bit on the customer.","index":117,"end_time":402.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":118,"end_time":403.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.32,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":119,"end_time":404.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":120,"end_time":405.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":121,"end_time":405.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":406.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, Lauren, the other thing is we were, we are pretty much focusing on like as far as I saw in this campaign, facility managers.","index":123,"end_time":417.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I was just wondering like who else is usually in the deals in the, in the buying group.","index":124,"end_time":424.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":418.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So who has to be convinced in order to get a signature on the dotted line?","index":125,"end_time":431.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"It''s a good question.","index":126,"end_time":433.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I started to answer that via teams and I need to talk a little bit more with our, we call them our solutions advisors.","index":127,"end_time":441.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":433.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It depends a little bit on what the main goal is for that university.","index":128,"end_time":446.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":442.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And this is where it gets a little bit hairy.","index":129,"end_time":448.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So there''s a couple main drivers that we''ve noticed.","index":130,"end_time":451.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The three biggest being asset and maintenance management.","index":131,"end_time":456.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that is like facility facilities, teams, facilities managers, directors of facilities, those titles.","index":132,"end_time":463.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The second is space and optimizing space usage to really make the most out of the space that universities have, especially with, you know, declining enrollment and some of the hot issues that universities are facing right now, Decreased funding, all that sort of thing.","index":133,"end_time":481.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The third main driver being consolidation of various point systems.","index":134,"end_time":487.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So our solution does a lot of different.","index":135,"end_time":489.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Different things that sometimes universities will.","index":136,"end_time":493.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Before they switch to a system like ours that''s fully integrated and does a lot of different things, they''ll use point solutions for elements of what our software does.","index":137,"end_time":507.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And sometimes that creates a lot of IT complexity.","index":138,"end_time":510.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And IT teams will, I would say they are the ones who are most involved with this sort of key driver.","index":139,"end_time":519.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They want to consolidate solutions into one solution that will do everything.","index":140,"end_time":523.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that is the third main driver.","index":141,"end_time":526.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":142,"end_time":528.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because it''d be great to know whenever you sell specifically to universities, and I don''t know if you''ve talked about this with sales.","index":143,"end_time":537.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What''s the typical path?","index":144,"end_time":540.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So is it usually.","index":145,"end_time":541.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":540.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Does it ever.","index":146,"end_time":543.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Does like, does the trigger ever come from it?","index":147,"end_time":546.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So do you ever sell through it?","index":148,"end_time":549.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Like, is that a possibility?","index":149,"end_time":551.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Or do you usually go through the facility managers or someone else?","index":150,"end_time":557.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":551.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So what are some of the typical paths?","index":151,"end_time":559.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because I think.","index":152,"end_time":560.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":559.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I''ll have to get back to you on that.","index":153,"end_time":563.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t want to.","index":154,"end_time":565.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":564.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have a hunch of what it is, but I don''t want to tell you and be wrong.","index":155,"end_time":569.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I will get back to you.","index":156,"end_time":571.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.05,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I want to have a conversation with our sales team and just make sure that we are all aligned for the purpose of this campaign.","index":157,"end_time":578.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":158,"end_time":581.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because that''d be great to know.","index":159,"end_time":583.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":581.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And.","index":160,"end_time":583.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And the other thing, it''s, yeah.","index":161,"end_time":585.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Super important feedback that you sent us in that whenever, like, warm leads are being followed up with that that hasn''t led to success.","index":162,"end_time":597.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Can you talk a little bit about what the.","index":163,"end_time":599.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What warm leads mean?","index":164,"end_time":601.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, like, what were some of these instances you mention?","index":165,"end_time":604.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Paper?","index":166,"end_time":605.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So just because somebody downloaded a white paper, sales doesn''t even bother following up.","index":167,"end_time":610.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And.","index":168,"end_time":610.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, and I, I kind of understand why.","index":169,"end_time":612.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.73,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"They probably followed up a thousand times and ran on a whole 999 times out of that.","index":170,"end_time":618.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So it''s understandable.","index":171,"end_time":620.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But.","index":172,"end_time":620.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But then, like, what''s a warm lead that wouldn''t go down the funnel further?","index":173,"end_time":626.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":620.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, so what?","index":174,"end_time":626.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So when I say warm lead, I basically mean a lead that has maybe downloaded something, spent a little bit of time on our website, but they''re not ready necessarily to talk to sales, to book a demo, to take things to the next step.","index":175,"end_time":643.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They might be gathering information, but they''re not in a place where they''re ready to see more.","index":176,"end_time":650.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So, yeah, you''re absolutely right.","index":177,"end_time":653.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"When we pass those warm leads off to Sales.","index":178,"end_time":655.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If we''re like this person, through content syndication, they downloaded two white papers or they watched a webinar, sales is kind of like, okay, what''s that got to do with me?","index":179,"end_time":665.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"You know, when we, even when we do follow up on those leads, we don''t have a great response rate.","index":180,"end_time":673.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":665.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We might have a strong open rate, strong click rate.","index":181,"end_time":677.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They enter a nurture stream where they might continue to gather information.","index":182,"end_time":681.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":677.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But typically those leads, yeah, they take a little more nurturing.","index":183,"end_time":688.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think for the purpose of.","index":184,"end_time":689.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m glad you brought up the topic because that was going to be my next question.","index":185,"end_time":693.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, like, how does your nurturing work?","index":186,"end_time":696.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I don''t mean all the steps and all the materials that you send, but do you maybe not like off the top of your head, but somewhere in your systems, do you have numbers on, on how it works?","index":187,"end_time":707.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Like how efficient is, is your nurturing system?","index":188,"end_time":710.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because if it works well, the answer is easy.","index":189,"end_time":713.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, don''t get them on a call.","index":190,"end_time":715.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Put them in the nurturing sequence and then we''re good.","index":191,"end_time":718.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":715.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But I assume this isn''t the case.","index":192,"end_time":721.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.73,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But you might know that, yeah, we have data around within our various nurture streams, like the open rates, average open rates, average click rates, that sort of thing.","index":193,"end_time":733.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":722.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We don''t really have data around out of the deals that we close.","index":194,"end_time":739.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How many of those companies, universities, had personnel that was in our nurture stream?","index":195,"end_time":745.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We don''t do a good job of tracking that, so I can''t really speak to that specifically.","index":196,"end_time":753.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would theorize that we don''t do a great job of effectively pushing people down the stream.","index":197,"end_time":761.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think a lot of it boils down to just right timing with the company since it is a very expensive upfront purchase.","index":198,"end_time":770.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They have to be in the right place, have the right people aligned.","index":199,"end_time":773.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s not necessarily, you know, one person can decide that they want the system and pull the trigger.","index":200,"end_time":778.669,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So.","index":201,"end_time":779.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, makes sense.","index":202,"end_time":783.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":203,"end_time":783.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, that''s some good info.","index":204,"end_time":785.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because I was thinking if it''s just a matter of mining data, and I don''t know if we, I''m guessing we have the capacity to do this, but like, this might be pretty important and if you guys don''t have anybody who could do it, one of us might be able to jump into your systems and then retroactively look at what the main indicators are and the performance metrics for, for your nurturing.","index":205,"end_time":812.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because that might, that might give us, give us a lot of important information on, you know, it might point us in the right direction and, and what to do.","index":206,"end_time":822.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because, yeah, the Situation is definitely that whenever we get somebody in the door, they''re usually not ready to talk to sales.","index":207,"end_time":831.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I''m guessing that''s the situation like 95% of the time.","index":208,"end_time":835.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":832.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But that doesn''t mean that they won''t be in 30 to 60 days.","index":209,"end_time":838.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And the question is what we do in the meantime.","index":210,"end_time":841.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we probably.","index":211,"end_time":841.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And, and to prove that you and we are doing a good job, if we could prove that, okay, somebody came in the door and they don''t necessarily show up and as a deal, I don''t know this quarter, but if they show up as a deal the next, the following quarter and we''ve had so many touch points in the meantime, then then that can reassure everybody that, okay, like we''re doing our job and we just need to optimize the system.","index":212,"end_time":867.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And.","index":213,"end_time":869.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Maybe do more of what''s working.","index":214,"end_time":870.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.44,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But in order to do more of what''s working, we really have to figure out what is working because something probably is working.","index":215,"end_time":877.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"You just need to find it.","index":216,"end_time":879.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So I just wanted to throw that in there.","index":217,"end_time":881.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Just as you were speaking.","index":218,"end_time":883.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I was thinking, okay, like since you''re doing nurturing, like it''d be nice to know if it works or what part of it works.","index":219,"end_time":893.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Right.","index":220,"end_time":894.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So what data would you specifically look for?","index":221,"end_time":898.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Would you start with closed one deals and the contacts associated and reverse engineer from there?","index":222,"end_time":907.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":223,"end_time":908.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":907.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":224,"end_time":909.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":225,"end_time":910.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So it''s looking at the close one deals.","index":226,"end_time":914.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How many touch points do we have?","index":227,"end_time":916.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How many of those touch points come from our nurturing sequence?","index":228,"end_time":919.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we have lead source information for con, like the lead contact on each of the deals that have been closed 1.","index":229,"end_time":928.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can share data with you around, you know, with the breakdown of the lead source is there.","index":230,"end_time":935.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can tell you a lot of the time this isn''t very helpful, but sometimes it is events.","index":231,"end_time":941.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There''s a. Yeah, I can give you the top lead sources, but events is usually one.","index":232,"end_time":947.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Direct web visits is often in the top three or four.","index":233,"end_time":953.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.04,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So people who just come to our website, book a demo and then it just takes off from there.","index":234,"end_time":959.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":954.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They just were ready at that point.","index":235,"end_time":961.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I know that''s not exactly helpful for the purposes of the ABM campaign.","index":236,"end_time":966.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I mean it can be.","index":237,"end_time":969.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Especially if those people are asked on their demo call, where did you hear about us?","index":238,"end_time":975.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.93,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because that might be gold.","index":239,"end_time":977.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.09,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I''m assuming you''re recording those sales or those demos.","index":240,"end_time":982.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":977.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Recording the demos, Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":985.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t think our team does actually.","index":242,"end_time":988.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":985.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because I was wondering like if, if they ask where did you hear about us?","index":243,"end_time":993.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.7,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How would we get the information and if you did have recordings, we could, you know, put some AI on it and have it extract the information and.","index":244,"end_time":1003.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And that would give us a pretty good indication if it is asked.","index":245,"end_time":1007.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know if the demos are recorded and I don''t know, to be honest with you, if the sales team is asking how.","index":246,"end_time":1014.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":247,"end_time":1016.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How they found out about Plan on, that''s probably something that we could do better.","index":248,"end_time":1020.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1016.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I see lots of opportunities.","index":249,"end_time":1027.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":1028.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1027.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Digging a bit deeper into.","index":251,"end_time":1031,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Into stuff.","index":252,"end_time":1032.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":253,"end_time":1034.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":1036.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"For now, I''m, I''m good with questions, Taylor, so.","index":255,"end_time":1040.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":256,"end_time":1041.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But thanks long.","index":257,"end_time":1042,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"That, that was really good.","index":258,"end_time":1042.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, those were good questions and, and good to fill in the gaps there.","index":259,"end_time":1048.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I met with Bailey and Dan earlier this week and we kind of talked through some ideas initially that we had just based on the information that we had originally.","index":260,"end_time":1057.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But now that you''ve kind of given us some more input and context, we can walk through these a little bit more.","index":261,"end_time":1062.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know, Dan, you had this original idea of kind of like this sandbox test approach of like a smaller group.","index":262,"end_time":1069.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you want to explain that.","index":263,"end_time":1070.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A little bit more of what that would look like.","index":264,"end_time":1072.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":265,"end_time":1074.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So the idea here is that Taylor has been telling me that, you know, you''re a relatively big organization and making decisions isn''t lightning fast and you have to consult several people.","index":266,"end_time":1088.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And, you know, for one, the launch of the LinkedIn campaigns has been delayed because of that, whereas it would have come in super handy for our cold emails because, you know, we tend to synchronize the two.","index":267,"end_time":1103.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":268,"end_time":1103.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, like, that would have helped a lot.","index":269,"end_time":1106.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I''m not saying that it would have completely shifted the.","index":270,"end_time":1110.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"The results, but they''re supposed to be done together.","index":271,"end_time":1112.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So it''s totally normal for organizations your size to, you know, not make decisions fast enough.","index":272,"end_time":1120.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But what we''ve seen work is if whoever makes the calls is okay with setting up a quote, sandbox environment where we focus on a given number of accounts, like a specified.","index":273,"end_time":1135.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Like it could be a geographical segment or it could be named accounts, like 200 accounts, whatever, where they say, okay, you guys go ahead and experiment and, and you get to make all the calls, Lauren, and you don''t have to go back and ask.","index":274,"end_time":1154.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I think it''s Jay who is also involved in.","index":275,"end_time":1157.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"In these questions and where you just have to.","index":276,"end_time":1161.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1157.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"You just get to make the call.","index":277,"end_time":1162.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we can move three times as fast, and whatever we test and try will.","index":278,"end_time":1166.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Will get done a lot faster.","index":279,"end_time":1168.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And we could just move faster because it''s one thing to Bring you ideas and set up new experiments.","index":280,"end_time":1174.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But if it, it doesn''t go through very fast, then, then, then nobody''s going to be happy in the end.","index":281,"end_time":1180.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, so that''s one approach and we were wondering how, like how that sounds, is that too extreme?","index":282,"end_time":1187.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Do you, do you even agree?","index":283,"end_time":1188.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I mean, I love the idea and I definitely see the value in being able to test quite a bit, fail quite a bit, figure out what works so that we can extrapolate to a larger audience.","index":284,"end_time":1200.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can run this by my superiors.","index":285,"end_time":1204.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have a feeling they''re not going to go for it.","index":286,"end_time":1206.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1204.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, they, they''re a little bit tight with the reins to be honest.","index":287,"end_time":1212.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think they just want to be able to know what''s going on and have the opportunity to approve it before we move forward.","index":288,"end_time":1219.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1213.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I can check it''s worth, definitely worth asking at the very least.","index":289,"end_time":1224.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1226.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What do you think they will, what''s going to be their objection?","index":291,"end_time":1230.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Ah, just lack of trust.","index":292,"end_time":1235.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1232.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think they like to know, you know, what offers we''re putting out, what the, you know, making sure the branding is on brand for us.","index":293,"end_time":1244.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think they''re just going to know and have a sense of what we''re doing.","index":294,"end_time":1249.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1246.409,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, well if you want, if, if you decide to take this up with them, then I think we can give you a couple of slides or talking points and, and that might help you.","index":295,"end_time":1261.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, so the idea, yeah, if you could provide that, that would be great with.","index":296,"end_time":1267.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, just an estimation of what you see, the outcomes being what the goals are, especially what contacts, what accounts that we''ll be focusing on.","index":297,"end_time":1280.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"With this.","index":298,"end_time":1280.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would think that we wouldn''t necessarily identify like our top, top targets for this sandbox approach.","index":299,"end_time":1288.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I''ll let you tell me what you think would be best.","index":300,"end_time":1292.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":301,"end_time":1294.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":302,"end_time":1294.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I think we''ll, we''ll have a couple of bullet points and, and then, and then see where that takes us.","index":303,"end_time":1300.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":304,"end_time":1301.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1300.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":1303.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And the other idea, so we''ve got a couple of ideas and one of them, what you see on the screen is screen is intent based outreach, meaning what''s in the name?","index":306,"end_time":1316.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So looking at accounts and looking for intense signals and yes, downloading a white paper is in itself a signal.","index":307,"end_time":1328.319,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1316.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But if we''re able to consolidate more signals and go after the accounts who are exhibiting more than one of these intense signals, then we might have a way better hit rate because, because we''re, we''re taking into account a lot more signals.","index":308,"end_time":1347.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1328.319,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So, so, so that''s something that''s tended to work if like the mass outreach doesn''t work.","index":309,"end_time":1353.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"We can, we can narrow in on people, contacts, accounts who are showing proof that they are interested.","index":310,"end_time":1361.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"How will you get that data set from?","index":311,"end_time":1365.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I see from factors from the same email and LinkedIn.","index":312,"end_time":1369.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":313,"end_time":1372.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So running ads would be a super important source of signals because you know, we could run here too.","index":314,"end_time":1378.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1372.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1379.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1379,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"On the next slide.","index":316,"end_time":1380.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we have that in there too.","index":317,"end_time":1382.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1383.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So ads all over the place.","index":319,"end_time":1384.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1383.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":320,"end_time":1385.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":321,"end_time":1387.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1386.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":322,"end_time":1387.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1387.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So that is one thing.","index":323,"end_time":1389.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":324,"end_time":1393.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1393.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Should I go on to the next one, Taylor?","index":325,"end_time":1395.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1393.52,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that was the only other thing is just in addition was adding ads like that''d be another way.","index":326,"end_time":1399.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":327,"end_time":1401.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Now this idea comes from us not being like super confident about what offer would work and who our target Personas are and how they buy and you know, all the questions we talked about and there are more questions like that.","index":328,"end_time":1421.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So whenever we feel that we don''t have like a really good grip on we''re not inside the minds of our target customers enough, we want to go into discovery mode in a way that will both give us the information and set us up for sales conversations.","index":329,"end_time":1440.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So the best way to do that is to basically stage a research.","index":330,"end_time":1445.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And what this research is, is a topic that is super top of mind for our champions, for our target audience.","index":331,"end_time":1453.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And so what we could do is do, and I''m just, you know, saying the state of, I don''t know, facilities operations at American universities, 2026, for example, like we can title the research that and then we would say, okay, dear facility manager, we are running this research.","index":332,"end_time":1472.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"We are talking to experts who have at least 5 years experience in the field because we want to put together this very comprehensive study and it''s going to be great because no one''s done it before.","index":333,"end_time":1483.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1472.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And we want to pick the best minds.","index":334,"end_time":1485.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1483.7,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And if you''d like to get this for free, we would really appreciate your input.","index":335,"end_time":1491.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All we need is a 15 to 20 minute conversation from you, a couple of questions around the topics of xyz.","index":336,"end_time":1498.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1491.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And the important thing is that it''s an open ended conversation rather than a set survey.","index":337,"end_time":1505.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1499.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So it''s going to feel like an, a quick expert exchange of thoughts.","index":338,"end_time":1511.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But what we actually do is we get the type of information that helps us approach them better in the future.","index":339,"end_time":1520.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And.","index":340,"end_time":1522.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So put another way, we will actually prospect them.","index":341,"end_time":1527.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1524.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we ask about their challenges, how they deal with the challenges, when they want to buy a solution, how they do that, who they have to go to.","index":342,"end_time":1535.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1527.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we get super clear on their buying journey, their buying processes as well.","index":343,"end_time":1540.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And you know, we ask about, okay who else is involved?","index":344,"end_time":1543.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Why do projects typically trip up?","index":345,"end_time":1547.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1544.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Why.","index":346,"end_time":1548.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Why they get called off, canceled, These types of questions.","index":347,"end_time":1554.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And then one of the last questions that we like to ask is what''s.","index":348,"end_time":1560.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1554.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Like, what''s.","index":349,"end_time":1561.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1560.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What''s the number one item on your wish list right now when it comes to your category?","index":350,"end_time":1566.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1561.58,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So managing facilities or solving XYZ problem?","index":351,"end_time":1570.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1566.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Like, what''s your number one desire W that you would love to come true?","index":352,"end_time":1574.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And, and then often they give us some pretty good ideas which we can use to later follow up with them.","index":353,"end_time":1583.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1574.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So we can say in the thank you email, because after these conversations we''re like, thank you so much for your time and we''re going to be getting you the report once it''s done.","index":354,"end_time":1594.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1583.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Just one thing that you mentioned, you would love to see XYZ happen.","index":355,"end_time":1602.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And I took this idea, I kind of like that idea, and I took it back to the team and Jerry told me that, you know, he''s done that before or he solved that problem before or he solved something very similar in another with another client or a situation.","index":356,"end_time":1619.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And then if you want, I can put you in touch with Jerry, who''s probably a salesperson or solutions engineer or consultant or whomever, the appropriate person.","index":357,"end_time":1631.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1619.79,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And then most of the time they''ll be like, oh yeah, because, you know, they just admitted that it''s a big problem for them and they want that solved.","index":358,"end_time":1639.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Right.","index":359,"end_time":1640.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If they could talk to someone who solved that before.","index":360,"end_time":1643.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1640.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I''m gonna take that call.","index":361,"end_time":1647.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.25,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you.","index":362,"end_time":1649.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I like that idea a lot.","index":363,"end_time":1652.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1650.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would definitely want to take that back to Jay and make sure that his team has the capacity to have those kind of prospecting conversations with these, with these universities.","index":364,"end_time":1667.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1655.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I like the idea a lot.","index":365,"end_time":1669.749,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it even aligns with the messaging in the LinkedIn connection requests.","index":366,"end_time":1676.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, you know, we''re reaching out to thought leaders and, you know, facilities, teams across, you know, the U.S. no, I like that a lot.","index":367,"end_time":1687.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That would mean another asset created with you guys.","index":368,"end_time":1691.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1687.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":369,"end_time":1692.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Having to put together the report to distribute.","index":370,"end_time":1695.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1692.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1695.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1695.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So in the end, you know, we would put it up into a polish, pretty little report, 20 something pages, and then you could either gate it on your website or if that doesn''t work and you said it doesn''t work, you could use it as a sales asset and your salespeople could go like, okay, this is not on our website.","index":372,"end_time":1714.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1695.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"This is like a special report.","index":373,"end_time":1715.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, we sell these for fifteen hundred dollars, but I can give it to you.","index":374,"end_time":1720.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1716.22,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I think actually we did something.","index":375,"end_time":1724.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1723.1,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m trying to find it right now.","index":376,"end_time":1726.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1724.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Something somewhat similar survey among higher ed leaders in like 2018, I want to say and I think to this day in our nurture stream, it is still a very pop.","index":377,"end_time":1738.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1726.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Particular asset.","index":378,"end_time":1739,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1738.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Wow.","index":379,"end_time":1739.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"There you go.","index":380,"end_time":1740.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But I''ll have to find that and maybe can share that with you.","index":381,"end_time":1744.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1741.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":382,"end_time":1747.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1746.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":383,"end_time":1748.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1748.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Things that we get so much valuable information back, we would just have so much more confident in putting together the offers, the messaging and everything else.","index":384,"end_time":1761.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1749.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Right.","index":385,"end_time":1762.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1761.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1763.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.08,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you could share just this information on the screen, anything else related with me in writing just via team so that I can share that with Jay and with anyone else who might need to be involved to get them to buy into it, that would be great.","index":387,"end_time":1779.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Get their thoughts on if they, if they are into the idea too.","index":388,"end_time":1785.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ll, we''ll get that to you as well.","index":389,"end_time":1790.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1787.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Both the sandbox idea and this.","index":390,"end_time":1792.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":391,"end_time":1794,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1792.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1795.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":393,"end_time":1795.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can definitely sent you over like a list of everything we talked about too and yeah, provide you with a couple additional details on how that could work.","index":394,"end_time":1803.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1795.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, we want to make sure that we''re getting you the leads that you want but also you know, having a successful campaign in the time frame that we do have.","index":395,"end_time":1810.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So yes, love to get your team''s feedback on that.","index":396,"end_time":1814.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I like it.","index":397,"end_time":1817.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1815.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I like that idea.","index":398,"end_time":1818.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1817.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":399,"end_time":1820.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1819.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, those are just about a couple things we could come up with that would kind of be like new and like you said, we want to get that engagement back and like Dan said, it would be great information to have like for follow ups in the future too for your team to kind of understand the audience a little bit better because we seem to have like the list of the universities and the titles that we''re interested in.","index":400,"end_time":1837.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But actually hearing from them directly on these types of things I think would be beneficial to kind of help our efforts through so.","index":401,"end_time":1845.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":402,"end_time":1846.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1845.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And if for this, if we need to limit our number of universities we can target, I would like to focus on that.","index":403,"end_time":1856.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1846.92,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I said 395 R1 universities that we''ve determined are probably the best fit for plan on.","index":404,"end_time":1864.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1856.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So even if, if that''s all we can focus on, then that would still be really, really useful for us to have that information.","index":405,"end_time":1870.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1864.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":406,"end_time":1872.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1871.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1872.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Understandable for Dan, in the times you''ve done this before, is there a specific number you''d say we would do this like a survey outreach for?","index":408,"end_time":1879.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1872.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there like a sweet spot you''d say of like a target audience?","index":409,"end_time":1883.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1879.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is it?","index":410,"end_time":1884.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1884.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1884.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So if, if we can claim in this report that we''ve talked to 20 experts, then that carries significant weight.","index":412,"end_time":1894.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Even 15.","index":413,"end_time":1895.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"What is the minimum?","index":414,"end_time":1898.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1897.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Is 15 the minimum?","index":415,"end_time":1899.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1898.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, like below 15 you''re like, it''s subjective, you know, and depends on how you frame it.","index":416,"end_time":1912.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So if in that 15 you have like celebrity thought leaders and like super knowledgeable people who the market knows that they''re like, then getting even a couple of those and synthesizing their opinions and points of view, even that''s valuable.","index":417,"end_time":1930.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But if it''s absent that, I, I think if you said like 15, but it shouldn''t be too hard.","index":418,"end_time":1937.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1931.73,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"I mean, yeah, lists and, and we can even use the same list that we''ve been using so far.","index":419,"end_time":1944.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1937.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"It''s just another offer that we''re.","index":420,"end_time":1946.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1944.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"That we follow up with.","index":421,"end_time":1947.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1946.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":422,"end_time":1948.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1947.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, because they have been made aware of you now through the awareness campaign and they''ve got the materials, they know your name and things like that.","index":423,"end_time":1955.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1949.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we did follow up with the same audience, it could.","index":424,"end_time":1958.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we could make that number what it is just based on responses.","index":425,"end_time":1961.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1958.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we have 20.","index":426,"end_time":1962.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1961.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we have 30, you know, things like that.","index":427,"end_time":1964.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right, okay.","index":428,"end_time":1967.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":429,"end_time":1969.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But did you have any more questions around any of these ideas or anything in particular that you want us to provide for your team?","index":430,"end_time":1977.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1970.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you have to take a lot back to a few different people, so I want to make sure we answer all your questions.","index":431,"end_time":1982.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1977.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1983.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1982.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Trying to think of anything else around that last one that might come up.","index":433,"end_time":1988.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1984.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And if you do too, like have anything outstanding on teams, just shoot me a message.","index":434,"end_time":1994.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But.","index":435,"end_time":1994.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":436,"end_time":1995.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1995.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We have the time.","index":437,"end_time":1996.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sure.","index":438,"end_time":1997.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1996.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If there''s anything that you had a question around still.","index":439,"end_time":1999.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1997.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, I think, I think that''s clear.","index":440,"end_time":2003.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2001.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I really like that last idea.","index":441,"end_time":2005.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2003.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I want to take that back to Jay.","index":442,"end_time":2007.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2005.11,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And I will also take the.","index":443,"end_time":2010.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2008.27,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What was it, the sandbox idea back to our marketing leadership to see if they might buy into something like that.","index":444,"end_time":2018.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2013.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Especially if we tell them, you know, we''re only going to focus on X number of accounts that aren''t necessarily at the top of our target list.","index":445,"end_time":2026,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2018.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if the messaging isn''t spot on, in their opinion, it''s less of a.","index":446,"end_time":2031.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2026.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Of a miss.","index":447,"end_time":2032.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2031.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":448,"end_time":2032.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2032.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":449,"end_time":2033.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2032.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"We''re not risking.","index":450,"end_time":2034.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2033.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":451,"end_time":2035.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2035.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That much.","index":452,"end_time":2036.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2036.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Right.","index":453,"end_time":2037.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2037.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if you could share that with me, I will get some feedback on those and let you know what I hear.","index":454,"end_time":2042.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2038.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I did want to let you know the contract extension, it''s still in review.","index":455,"end_time":2047.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2044.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m following up with legal on that, but I think with the holidays, it just got.","index":456,"end_time":2051.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2047.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m pushed to the bottom of the pile.","index":457,"end_time":2054.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2052.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But yeah, no, I appreciate, I appreciate your time and all the ideas that you guys have put in.","index":458,"end_time":2061.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2055.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"One thing I would like to ask.","index":459,"end_time":2063.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2061.69,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Once we do have a clear plan of how we want to move forward for the next four months, it''s been requested from my boss to have a written plan of what we''re planning to do for the next four months.","index":460,"end_time":2075.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2063.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What we hope our outcomes are, the goals aligned with each activity.","index":461,"end_time":2080.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2075.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Um, I think she would like to see something kind of written and set in stone of what we''re doing, so.","index":462,"end_time":2086.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2080.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":463,"end_time":2087.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2086.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Once we decide what we want to do as far as which approach we want to take for this new campaign, we can write it all out and kind of like do the month.","index":464,"end_time":2095.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2087.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The month to month look.","index":465,"end_time":2096.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2095.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can send that over to you to share with her.","index":466,"end_time":2098.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2096.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":467,"end_time":2099.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2098.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":468,"end_time":2101.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2100.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":469,"end_time":2102.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2102.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, happy to share some ideas with you and kind of get things rolling, and we''ll work on that.","index":470,"end_time":2107.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2103.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''ll get that document over to you today so that you can share that with your leadership.","index":471,"end_time":2111.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2107.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":472,"end_time":2112.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2111.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you very much.","index":473,"end_time":2113.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2112.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":474,"end_time":2114.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2113.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":475,"end_time":2115.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2114.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope you have a good rest of your day.","index":476,"end_time":2116.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2115.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You too.","index":477,"end_time":2117.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2116.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It was good to meet you.","index":478,"end_time":2119.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2117.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Bye, Lauren.","index":479,"end_time":2119.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2119.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Good to meet you, too.","index":480,"end_time":2120.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2119.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"}],"dateString":"2026-01-08T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com,dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE83814EHHRY5JCHPW4N7H9T","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.93,"bullets":["Shifted ABM focus from awareness to lead generation; revamp spreadsheet with seven categories completed.","Aligned on need to tailor messaging by titles and lead qualification to drive sales-ready prospects.","Explored sourcing buyer journey data to improve visibility into nurturing sequence effectiveness.","Proposed sandbox testing for agile experimentation; Lauren to seek leadership buy-in with limited risk.","Pitched research-driven outreach strategy to identify pain points and uncover sales engagement triggers."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I really like that last idea. I want to take that back to Jay.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"},{"quote":"We could even use the same list that we''ve been using so far.","speaker":"Dan Rényi"},{"quote":"Want to make sure we''re getting you the leads that you want.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["abm","lead gen","messaging","data","buying journey"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T23:21:40Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Shift from Awareness to Lead Generation**\n\nThe campaign focus will move from broad brand awareness to targeted lead generation, aiming for quality leads that sales can engage effectively (02:22).\n\n- **Completed awareness campaign used three senders with three domains**, enabling delivery despite initial pauses, which helped secure new contacts and distribute materials broadly.\n    - The team segmented contacts into **seven new categories** to better tailor lead generation messaging.\n    - Taylor emphasized the need to shift away from awareness messaging to a **faster, more focused lead generation approach** due to a tight timeline ending in **April**.\n    - Lauren agreed this shift should concentrate on a **smaller, more qualified lead pool** that sales can actively pursue.\n    - This pivot aligns with the marketing roadmap and leverages insights from prior outreach to optimize impact.\n\n- **Taylor and Dan reviewed Lauren’s proposed messaging sequence and found it too similar to previous brand awareness efforts** (04:28).\n    - They recommended adopting new messaging focused on **lead qualification and conversion speed** rather than broad awareness.\n    - Lauren confirmed the prior messaging lacked sufficient title-specific tailoring but agreed to pivot toward outcome-driven messaging to meet lead generation goals.\n\n## **Lead Qualification, Buyer Insights, and Revenue Context**\n\nUnderstanding lead quality, buyer roles, and contract values is critical for campaign targeting and sales alignment (05:09).\n\n- **Lauren clarified the average contract value for university clients is in the six-figure range**, with recurring revenue also likely in that range, varying by deployment model (on-premise vs. cloud) (06:13).\n    - This underscores the **high-value nature of each contract**, necessitating precise targeting and longer sales cycles.\n\n- **Dan probed the buying group composition for universities, revealing three main drivers for purchase decisions** (07:12).\n    - Facilities managers and directors lead on asset and maintenance management.\n    - Space optimization is critical due to enrollment declines and funding cuts.\n    - IT teams focus on consolidating disparate point solutions into integrated systems.\n    - Lauren will confirm typical buying paths with sales to refine campaign targeting.\n\n- **Warm leads often come from content engagement but rarely convert immediately** as they require extended nurturing (10:28).\n    - Lauren indicated warm leads usually gather information but are not ready for demos or sales conversations.\n    - The sales team sees low response rates from these leads despite strong open and click rates.\n    - Dan suggested mining nurture stream data to identify which touchpoints contribute to eventual closed deals, enabling optimization of nurturing efforts.\n    - Lauren can share lead source breakdowns showing events and direct web visits among top sources, but lacks detailed tracking of nurture effectiveness tied to closed deals.\n\n## **Campaign Process Improvements: Sandbox Testing and Intent-Based Outreach**\n\nIntroducing a sandbox test environment and intent-based outreach will accelerate learning and improve targeting precision (17:53).\n\n- **Dan proposed a sandbox testing approach focusing on a limited set of accounts (e.g., 200) where the team can rapidly test and adjust campaigns without lengthy approvals** (17:53).\n    - This approach could triple decision speed and reduce delays seen in prior LinkedIn campaign launches.\n    - Lauren likes the idea but anticipates leadership concerns over trust and brand control.\n    - She will seek leadership buy-in and requested supporting slides with expected outcomes and scope for approval.\n    - Dan committed to delivering these materials to aid internal advocacy.\n\n- **Intent-based outreach will target accounts showing multiple high-intent signals across channels like email and LinkedIn ads to improve hit rates** (21:43).\n    - This method narrows outreach to engaged prospects, contrasting with broad mass campaigns.\n    - Running ads alongside cold emails is planned to generate these signals.\n    - Taylor confirmed intent data and ad integration are included in upcoming campaign plans.\n\n## **Strategic Discovery Research to Inform Messaging and Sales**\n\nA research-driven outreach will gather insights from target prospects, improving messaging and enabling tailored sales conversations (23:21).\n\n- **Dan suggested conducting an expert research study titled something like “State of Facilities Operations at American Universities 2026”**, engaging facility managers in qualitative interviews to gather buying journey insights and pain points (23:21).\n    - The study would involve **15 to 20 expert interviews** to establish credibility and provide valuable content.\n    - Follow-up emails would reference individual pain points raised, creating warm sales leads.\n    - Lauren strongly supported the idea, noting alignment with LinkedIn connection messaging and the potential need for a new report asset.\n    - Dan described the final deliverable as a polished 20+ page report, usable as a gated asset or exclusive sales collateral.\n\n- **Lauren recalled a similar 2018 survey of higher ed leaders remaining a popular nurture asset**, indicating the power of this approach.\n    - She will locate and share that asset as a reference.\n    - Lauren will assess her team’s capacity to conduct the prospecting conversations required.\n    - Dan and Taylor will provide written summaries of this and sandbox ideas for sharing with leadership.\n\n## **Next Steps, Contract Status, and Documentation**\n\nClear planning documents and contract updates will support campaign execution and leadership alignment (34:46).\n\n- **Lauren requested a written four-month plan detailing activities, goals, and expected outcomes to present to leadership** (34:46).\n    - Taylor agreed to deliver a month-by-month plan once the campaign approach is finalized.\n    - The plan will incorporate feedback and provide clarity on resource allocation and timelines.\n\n- **Lauren noted the contract extension is still under legal review, delayed by holidays** (33:57).\n    - She will continue following up to expedite completion.\n\n- **Taylor and Dan committed to sharing all discussed ideas, including the sandbox and research proposals, in writing to facilitate internal discussions** (29:21).\n    - This documentation aims to secure leadership buy-in for new agile approaches and research-driven campaigns.\n    - Lauren will gather feedback and relay it back to the team.\n\n- **Lauren emphasized targeting the 395 R1 universities identified as best fits for Planon** (30:45).\n    - Even limited targeting within this group would provide valuable insights and lead generation opportunities.\n    - Dan confirmed the list can be leveraged for both sandbox testing and research outreach.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","Lead Generation","Nurturing","Sandbox Testing","Intent-based Outreach","Discovery Research"],"overview":"- **Campaign Shift:** Move from brand awareness to targeted lead generation, focusing on quality leads for sales engagement.  \n- **Lead Categorization:** Contacts are now segmented into seven categories to tailor messaging for lead generation effectively.  \n- **Contract Value Insight:** Average contract value for university clients is six-figure, emphasizing need for precise targeting and longer sales cycles.  \n- **Sandbox Testing Proposal:** Test approach with 200 accounts to improve campaign adjustments and decision speed without lengthy approvals.  \n- **Research Study Initiative:** Conduct interviews with facilities managers to gain insights and prepare a report on buying journeys in universities.  \n- **Planning Documentation:** Request for a four-month plan detailing activities and goals to align with leadership for campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nConfirm with sales team the typical buying group composition and decision-making process for university clients to ensure alignment on campaign targeting (09:40)\nVerify with sales whether demos are recorded and if sales team captures lead source info during demos; evaluate opportunities for improvement (17:00)\nPresent the sandbox testing approach and discovery research study concepts to internal marketing leadership and Jay’s team to gauge interest and capacity; provide feedback to Taylor and Dan (20:50)\nFollow up with legal on contract extension status and update marketing partners accordingly (33:50)\nShare prior survey asset from 2018 related to higher education leaders with Taylor and Dan for potential reuse or inspiration (28:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nPrepare and deliver slides and written talking points detailing sandbox approach, benefits, goals, and target accounts to Lauren to assist in internal pitching (21:30)\nDraft a comprehensive, month-by-month 4-month campaign plan detailing activities, goals, outcomes aligned with leadership expectations; send to Lauren for leadership review (34:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"09e9eadc-0ab1-45cd-9324-a323441a1828","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
