    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.82,"bullets":["Dan flagged hundreds of legacy ABM emails; Baylee confirmed outdated automation and disabled it.","Taylor and Baylee agreed to update website copy and image assets after Dan''s input.","Dan requested updated poster file; Taylor will ensure only current version is active.","Carousel ad numbers flagged as outdated; Taylor will replace with updated data from Dan.","Website delivery now blocked solely by three images Dan committed to source shortly."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''m getting a couple hundred of these emails a day.","speaker":"Dan Nelsen"},{"quote":"I’ve turned it off so you shouldn''t get any emails moving forward.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","content","automation","campaign"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T23:24:19Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Automation and Notification Cleanup**\n\nThe team identified and prioritized fixing the excessive email notifications caused by outdated automation in HubSpot.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen reported receiving over 100 erroneous ABM campaign emails daily** due to old automation still running despite no recent campaign launches (01:31).  \n    - Baylee Gunnell confirmed this is likely residual automation from about two years ago and committed to investigate immediately after the call.  \n    - The automation was originally set to notify K. Ross, who has now been removed from the HubSpot account to stop further notifications.  \n    - Baylee disabled the problematic automation before the meeting ended, ensuring Dan should no longer receive these emails.  \n    - This cleanup will restore Dan’s ability to turn mail notifications back on, improving his workflow and reducing distractions.\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum and Baylee will monitor any further faulty notifications** and requested Dan forward any future erroneous emails for quick resolution (18:54).  \n    - This proactive approach aims to maintain clean, relevant communication streams linked to active campaigns.  \n    - Resolving these notification issues supports better engagement tracking and follow-up by the marketing team.  \n\n## **Website Content and Visual Updates**\n\nThe website update process is progressing with key copy and visual assets being finalized and integrated.\n\n- **Dan provided updated copy for the services product tab, covering five sections, delivered earlier that day for immediate integration** (05:13).  \n    - Taylor confirmed headings are ready and the team will add the new copy into Bug Herd for review.  \n    - Dan requested generally stock photos to fill out the page visually, which will be sourced accordingly.  \n    - Once the service validation copy is fully integrated, Dan’s team will conduct a final review to catch any last edits or issues (15:29).\n\n- **The poster artwork required formatting and content tweaks focusing on the features column and text alignment** (07:04).  \n    - Dan identified inconsistencies in justification across feature items and requested uniform formatting for a polished appearance (08:33).  \n    - The team agreed to provide both a high-resolution and a compressed low-resolution version of the updated poster for versatile use (08:54).  \n    - These updates will align marketing collateral with the latest branding and product messaging.\n\n- **Outstanding image assets remain for three website sections: wet vs. dry discharge, thermic vs. stick agitators, and building integrated vs. standalone digesters** (10:46).  \n    - Dan will supply photos clarifying inside agitator differences and visual examples of discharge types to enhance user understanding (11:31).  \n    - For building integration visuals, Dan explained the concept of digesters sunk into floors moving waste from hot to cold zones within facilities, and promised to provide related images (13:42).  \n    - These images are the last blocking items before the website updates can be fully implemented (20:03).\n\n## **Marketing Collateral Consistency and Data Accuracy**\n\nA focus on ensuring all marketing materials use consistent, up-to-date data to maintain credibility and clarity.\n\n- **Dan flagged outdated cost figures on carousel ads and requested updated numbers be checked and applied across all marketing assets** (16:48).  \n    - Taylor committed to verifying the source of existing numbers on the website and replacing them with Dan’s more current, defensible data sets (17:44).  \n    - This effort aims to prevent discrepancies that confuse potential customers or weaken the company’s value proposition.  \n    - Dan plans to review remaining ads in the carousel and send further comments as needed to maintain accuracy (18:19).\n\n- **Taylor confirmed ongoing coordination to ensure that all web and ad content reflects the latest validated data and messaging** (19:33).  \n    - This alignment will help unify the company’s public-facing materials and reduce risks of outdated or conflicting information.\n\n## **Process and Communication Improvements**\n\nThe discussion revealed areas for improving internal workflows and communication clarity.\n\n- **Dan emphasized the importance of centralized, updated collateral to avoid multiple versions causing confusion or misplacement** (20:22).  \n    - Taylor agreed to audit and update all relevant links and files to ensure only the newest poster and website content are accessible.  \n    - This reduces the risk of team members or Dan himself accidentally using outdated materials in presentations or client outreach.\n\n- **The team reinforced clear ownership and timely follow-up on deliverables, with Taylor leading updates in Bug Herd and Dan providing final media assets soon** (20:50).  \n    - This structured approach supports efficient iteration and quality control before public release.  \n    - Baylee and Taylor’s close collaboration on technical cleanup and content updates demonstrates improved coordination across marketing and operations teams.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Automation","Website Updates","Poster Design","ABM Campaign","Carousel Ads","Image Assets"],"overview":"- **Email Notification Cleanup:** Excessive erroneous emails were fixed; problematic automation disabled to improve Dan''s workflow.  \n- **Website Content Updates:** Updated copy for services section integrated; stock photos to be sourced to enhance visual appeal.  \n- **Poster Artwork Adjustments:** Inconsistencies resolved; both high and low-resolution versions to be provided for marketing use.  \n- **Image Assets Remaining:** Final images needed for key website sections before updates can be fully implemented.  \n- **Marketing Data Accuracy:** Outdated cost figures will be updated to maintain credibility and consistency across all marketing materials.  \n- **Internal Workflow Improvements:** Centralized collateral and clear ownership established to reduce confusion and enhance communication efficiency.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nForward representative emails of the erroneous HubSpot notifications to Baylee and Taylor for troubleshooting (01:30)\nProvide photos illustrating the internal difference between thermic and stick agitators for website image inclusion (12:00)\nLocate and send images showing “wet versus dry discharge” and “building integrated versus standalone” system layouts, including through-floor digesters (13:30)\nHave team conduct a final review of the new service/product tab copy once it is incorporated into Bug Herd and notify marketing of any further comments (15:40)\nSend updated treatment cost figures and confirm data sources in the carousel ads and website for consistency (16:45)\nContinue reviewing remaining carousel ads and provide additional feedback in due course (18:20)\nEnsure there is a single, updated version of the SVG poster shared among all teams (20:30)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nReview and clarify source of treatment cost numbers on carousel ads and website, then update materials with Dan’s provided figures (17:00)\nImplement requested copy changes and formatting fixes on the poster, producing both high-res and compressed versions for Dan’s use (08:55)\nCoordinate integration of new service/product tab copy in Bug Herd and notify Dan when ready for team review (15:25)\nWork on requested updates and ensure image placements as soon as Dan supplies photos (10:30)\nCommunicate with Dan to confirm resolution of HubSpot automation and stop of excessive email notifications (19:00)\nSend Dan updated pages via Bug Herd as they are completed (19:40)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nInvestigate and disable old HubSpot automation triggering excessive ABM campaign emails; remove K. Ross user from HubSpot to prevent future alerts (02:00)\nNotify Dan when automation is successfully turned off to stop unwanted emails (19:00)\nAssist Taylor with coordination and follow-up for website and HubSpot notification issues (00:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"c115cece-aa4e-43c4-add7-1da366ad6321","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
