g schedule"],"overview":"- **SEO Traffic Trends:** December saw mixed SEO results; engagement up, but direct traffic dipped slightly during holidays.  \n- **Notable Traffic Increase:** New Christmas merchandise page had an **84,000% traffic increase**, with solid gains on many blog pages.  \n- **Year-Over-Year Growth:** 2025 showed broad growth in most areas except homepage; new blog attracted high traffic with no prior data.  \n- **Podcast Staffing Changes:** Intern Nikki will manage podcast tasks, reducing Nigel''s involvement as they adjust meeting frequency to biweekly.  \n- **Communication Improvements:** Nikki will tag alongside Nigel on relevant communications, ensuring smooth transitions during staffing changes.  \n- **Strategic Resource Allocation:** Leadership focuses on delegating tasks to maintain growth, while monitoring SEO health amid operational adjustments.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nAdjust meeting calendar invitations to biweekly occurrence on the first and third weeks of the month (07:36)\nContinue tagging Nikki and Nigel on Slack when sending over career board related communications (08:25)\nMonitor and await podcast updates for new episode publishing decisions (08:59)\n\n**Nigel Sapp**\nSend over the recorded podcast episode with Alan from Slack to the team for production (05:55)\nBegin onboarding intern Nikki to handle podcast publishing, editing, and related New North tasks, and keep Taylor informed (06:18)\nTransition meeting participation and communications to include Nikki, especially for content and career board matters (08:13)\nUpdate on podcast backlog episode review progress and potential publishing schedule (08:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"64428987-4ee2-4ccc-8b5b-e3285ed4531a","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
