  'Meeting Notes: Taylor Doerbaum and Nigel Sapp',
  '## **SEO Performance and Traffic Trends**

The December SEO report showed mixed results influenced by the holiday season, with notable gains in engagement despite overall traffic dips (02:24).

- **Time on page increased significantly in December**, signaling stronger user engagement despite typical holiday slowdowns.
    - Direct traffic dipped slightly compared to November’s high, reflecting expected seasonal behavior.
    - Page traffic on main landing pages decreased, but many blog pages saw solid increases.
    - The new Christmas merchandise page recorded an extraordinary **84,000% traffic increase**, likely due to it being new and highly relevant.
- **Year-over-year comparison for 2025 versus 2024 revealed broad growth across most pages**, except a minor drop on the homepage.
    - Top-performing pages saw significant gains, supporting a positive trend in organic reach.
    - A new blog launched in 2025 attracted high traffic, but lacked prior-year data for comparison.
- **SEO score improved by one point from the previous month**, with ongoing developer recommendations provided to maintain optimization.
    - Taylor emphasized continuing to monitor and apply these developer recommendations for steady SEO health.

## **Podcast Production and Publishing Strategy**

Podcast efforts are undergoing a staffing shift and a temporary slowdown in new content, with plans to delegate tasks and adjust meeting cadence (05:34).

- **Nigel introduced an intern, Nikki, who will manage podcast publishing and coordination**, reducing Nigel’s direct involvement.
    - Nigel plans to have Nikki handle backlog episode reviews and new publishing tasks starting mid-January.
    - Podcast output in Q1 2025 may be limited as Nigel focuses on other priorities and Nikki ramps up.
- **Meeting frequency will shift from weekly to biweekly, focusing on the first and third weeks of each month**, aligning with SEO reporting and workload.
    - Taylor will update calendar invites accordingly and include Nikki in communications.
- **Publishing of backlog podcast episodes is paused temporarily until Nikki completes listening and editing**, with updates forthcoming.
    - This approach aims to ensure quality control as the intern acclimates and takes ownership.
    - Nigel expressed appreciation for the added support, highlighting operational bandwidth constraints.

## **Communication and Workflow Adjustments**

The team is streamlining communication and task ownership to improve efficiency amid shifting responsibilities (07:47).

- **Taylor will tag Nikki alongside Nigel on Slack messages related to the careers board and podcast updates**, ensuring smooth handoff.
    - Nigel confirmed Nikki is already actively handling assigned tasks and will continue to do so.
- **Nigel will attend an offsite next week, so Nikki will represent him in meetings starting the week after**, maintaining continuity.
- **This structured delegation reflects a broader effort to balance workload while sustaining content delivery and SEO monitoring.**

## **Strategic Outlook and Resource Allocation**

Leadership is prioritizing resource shifts and process adjustments to maintain growth momentum with limited capacity (06:01).

- **Nigel’s decision to onboard an intern reflects a strategic choice to delegate operational tasks**, allowing him to focus on higher-level priorities.
    - This aligns with plans to slow new podcast production temporarily without sacrificing quality.
- **The SEO and content teams remain aligned on maintaining steady progress through ongoing monitoring and incremental improvements**, as evidenced by the modest SEO score increase.
- **Biweekly check-ins and clearer task ownership aim to improve coordination and responsiveness during this transition period.**',
  '2026-01-09 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Adjust meeting calendar invitations to biweekly occurrence on the first and third weeks of the month (07:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue tagging Nikki and Nigel on Slack when sending over career board related communications (08:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and await podcast updates for new episode publishing decisions (08:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Send over the recorded podcast episode with Alan from Slack to the team for production (05:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Begin onboarding intern Nikki to handle podcast publishing, editing, and related New North tasks, and keep Taylor informed (06:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Transition meeting participation and communications to include Nikki, especially for content and career board matters (08:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Update on podcast backlog episode review progress and potential publishing schedule (08:50)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
