    '{"id":"01KE7X3Y9JSTTANJ1MYX45SPQ3","title":"Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)","summary":{"notes":"## **Booth Design and Event Marketing Materials**\n\nThe team decided to prioritize clearer messaging on the booth backdrop to better capture attendees’ attention and communicate the core service quickly.\n\n- **Josh Bartel suggested** emphasizing the tagline “**Inventory Optimization as a Service**” prominently across the top of the booth banner, moving the logo and “Kill stockouts, limited excess” text lower on the design to avoid important text being blocked by booth furniture or attendees (03:22)\n    - This change addresses concerns that the current font size and placement make key messages hard to read from a distance.\n    - The design team will create **four new variations** to test this arrangement and ensure visibility with a finalized print-ready file.\n    - Michael Jones agreed with prioritizing tagline visibility and proposed placing the logo in the lower left for branding balance.\n    - The clearer headline aims to increase booth engagement by immediately communicating the value proposition to passersby, improving lead generation efficiency.\n\n- For brochures and handouts, the team agreed to combine **physical flyers with QR codes** linking to an event-specific landing page (11:04)\n    - Michael Jones proposed replacing the full brochure with a stand holding a flyer featuring a QR code, reducing print costs and improving flexibility.\n    - Taylor Doerbaum emphasized that the QR code link will point to a **dedicated assessment page** with a unique URL to track event-specific conversions.\n    - They will keep some physical copies available based on attendee preference, enabling testing of what drives higher engagement.\n    - This hybrid approach balances accessibility and tracking precision while allowing fast updates without reprinting.\n\n## **Survey and Content Strategy**\n\nThe recent email survey sent to **2,400 contacts** yielded **61 page views and 15 submissions**, informing upcoming content and marketing activity (16:17)\n\n- Michael Jones and Josh Bartel reviewed the responses and produced four LinkedIn posts plus newsletter content based on the survey insights (16:40)\n    - They plan a one-page summary of survey results with highlighted conclusions to replace detailed multi-box formats for clearer communication.\n    - New LinkedIn posts will follow the existing cadence of **two posts per week** on main and personal accounts, and dates will be adjusted as new content arrives.\n    - Michael highlighted the need to deliver on promised survey results promptly to maintain credibility and engagement.\n    - Taylor suggested supplementing survey content with a **year-in-review and 2026 outlook** post as a content bridge for January and February.\n\n- To boost engagement and thought leadership, Taylor proposed creating **LinkedIn carousel posts** summarizing key themes from 2025 and forecasts for 2026 (20:00)\n    - These image-based posts will provide visually compelling, easy-to-digest content for organic reach.\n    - Michael requested examples to guide content creation, which Taylor will share via Google Drive.\n    - This approach supports multi-format content reuse across channels, increasing audience touchpoints and reinforcing brand authority.\n\n## **LinkedIn Profile Optimization and Thought Leadership**\n\nAttention to personal LinkedIn profiles was identified as a critical but underutilized asset for customer engagement and brand positioning.\n\n- Michael Jones noted that potential and existing clients frequently view individual LinkedIn pages, making profile quality as important as the company website (24:19)\n    - He suggested reviewing and improving the LinkedIn pages of key team members—himself, Josh Bartel, and Drew—to maximize impact.\n    - Taylor agreed and described a process used for other clients where CEOs provide monthly industry insights that are crafted into thought leadership posts.\n    - This strategy creates a clear distinction between company updates and personal expert commentary, enhancing credibility and customer trust.\n    - The team plans to include LinkedIn profile optimization and personal branding in the brainstorming session scheduled for the end of the month (26:03).\n\n## **Survey Tool and Email Deliverability Improvements**\n\nThe team plans to switch survey distribution fully to SurveyMonkey next week and improve email deliverability by updating outreach domains.\n\n- Taylor confirmed the SurveyMonkey form is ready for launch next Tuesday, incorporating a corrected question and consolidating all survey activity on one platform (22:04)\n    - This switch streamlines data collection and survey management.\n    - Due to poor deliverability from **Mailforge-purchased domains** over the past year, new email domains are being acquired through **Smart Lead** for better inbox placement (22:59)\n    - These fresh domains are currently warming up and will be integrated into SurveyMonkey campaigns next month.\n    - Michael observed HubSpot warnings about domain issues, confirming the urgency of this change.\n    - Improved deliverability is expected to increase open rates and survey participation, enhancing marketing ROI.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) List Management**\n\nMichael Jones has added new companies to the ABM list and seeks clarification on updating procedures to improve list management efficiency.\n\n- He referenced multiple spreadsheets (“Hydrogen companies list updated,” “remove list”) and asked which to use for adding new companies (28:30)\n    - Taylor proposed consolidating the lists into a single spreadsheet with multiple tabs to reduce confusion and streamline updates.\n    - Michael agreed to send the current files offline for review and consolidation.\n    - Better list management will improve ABM targeting accuracy and reduce administrative overhead for the marketing team.","outline":null,"keywords":["Assessment page","Booth design","QR code marketing","Survey results","LinkedIn content strategy","ABM list"],"overview":"- **Booth Design Update:** Tagline “Inventory Optimization as a Service” will be emphasized for better engagement and visibility at events.  \n- **Hybrid Brochure Strategy:** Use physical flyers with QR codes linking to assessments, reducing print costs while improving tracking.  \n- **Survey Insights Review:** 2,400 contacts surveyed; generated 61 views, 15 submissions; 4 LinkedIn posts and newsletter content created.  \n- **Engagement Boost Proposal:** Create LinkedIn carousel posts summarizing 2025 themes and 2026 forecasts for enhanced audience reach.  \n- **LinkedIn Profile Importance:** Optimize personal LinkedIn pages for team members to improve engagement with potential clients and brand perception.  \n- **Survey Tool Transition:** Switching to SurveyMonkey next week for better data collection; new email domains acquired for improved deliverability.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nRequest new booth design variations emphasizing ''Inventory Optimization as a Service'' in top third and logo placement below (09:50)\nDesign QR code flyer for event stands alongside physical brochures (14:23)\nCreate duplicate landing page URL for event-specific tracking linked to QR code (15:46)\nProvide examples of LinkedIn carousel posts and organize a Google Drive folder with content samples (21:40)\nAdd LinkedIn personal branding review to brainstorm meeting agenda for Jan 28 (26:03)\nPrepare materials for the brainstorm session and request any additional agenda items (27:38)\nReview ABM company lists and work with Michael to consolidate into one sheet with tabs (29:26)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nProvide feedback on new LinkedIn posts drafts from survey content (16:46)\nConsider content and timing strategy for LinkedIn and website year-end recap and 2026 outlook posts (19:46)\nSend updated ABM company lists to Taylor for consolidation (28:50)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nFinalize content drafts for survey-related LinkedIn posts and newsletter for review and approval (16:46)\n"},"duration":29.950000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Michael Jones"},{"id":2,"name":"Josh Bartel"}],"sentences":[{"text":"That nice hat.","index":0,"end_time":2.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just wanted to go ahead and show I got the merch.","index":1,"end_time":5.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you very much.","index":2,"end_time":6.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I gotta take this off now.","index":3,"end_time":10.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":4,"end_time":12.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But it''s very, very warm.","index":5,"end_time":13.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":6,"end_time":14.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m so glad you like it.","index":7,"end_time":15.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a cool hat.","index":8,"end_time":18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''m like, oh, very nice.","index":9,"end_time":19.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, very nice.","index":10,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":11,"end_time":22.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you very much.","index":12,"end_time":22.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":13,"end_time":23.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I got mine as well at my.","index":14,"end_time":24.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"My daughter has been wearing it around.","index":15,"end_time":27.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":24.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"She made a good point.","index":16,"end_time":28.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":27.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"She''s like, it was really nice then to send you this hat, wasn''t it?","index":17,"end_time":31.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I was like, yeah, it''s pretty cool.","index":18,"end_time":33.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":32.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And she''s like, but wait a minute now.","index":19,"end_time":35.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":33.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If I wear it around, people might see it, and they might decide to call these people and use their.","index":20,"end_time":40.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Use their service.","index":21,"end_time":41.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":40.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I was like, yeah, that''s the idea.","index":22,"end_time":42.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s why people push their printer stuff on merch.","index":23,"end_time":44.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":42.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And she''s like, that''s really smart.","index":24,"end_time":46.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":44.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You should keep.","index":25,"end_time":46.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Keep working with them.","index":26,"end_time":48.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":47.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"They''re good at marketing.","index":27,"end_time":49.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I love that.","index":28,"end_time":50.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She was like, just understanding the idea of, like, you know, swag for the first time.","index":29,"end_time":55.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s so funny.","index":30,"end_time":57.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I love that.","index":31,"end_time":57.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":32,"end_time":59.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, happy New Year to you both.","index":33,"end_time":61.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you both have a good Christmas and New Year''s?","index":34,"end_time":64.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes and yes.","index":35,"end_time":65.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And yourself.","index":36,"end_time":66.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Good.","index":37,"end_time":67.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It was all right.","index":38,"end_time":68.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We all got sick here, so it wasn''t as planned.","index":39,"end_time":71.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":72.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":72.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You guys get the flu or just.","index":42,"end_time":74.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I.","index":43,"end_time":75.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It could have been.","index":44,"end_time":76.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We have no idea.","index":45,"end_time":77.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was, like, sore throat, like, fever, like, terrible body aches, but it didn''t feel like anything.","index":46,"end_time":84.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I usually get strep throat, like, every year.","index":47,"end_time":86.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like that''s always what I get.","index":48,"end_time":87.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it wasn''t that.","index":49,"end_time":88.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":87.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It wasn''t Covid.","index":50,"end_time":89.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It.","index":51,"end_time":89.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was like this weird thing I guess everyone''s saying is going around.","index":52,"end_time":92.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we all just got it one after another.","index":53,"end_time":95.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":96.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":95.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We have one person on our team who got it, and then our friends while we were traveling.","index":55,"end_time":99.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We were with some friends, and they all had the flu the week before they traveled with us.","index":56,"end_time":102.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, it very well could have been that.","index":57,"end_time":104.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":102.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Honestly, I don''t know.","index":58,"end_time":105.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s.","index":59,"end_time":105.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":105.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I feel like I''m still recovering.","index":60,"end_time":106.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s been brutal.","index":61,"end_time":107.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So not fun.","index":62,"end_time":109.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like always during the holidays, it tends to amp up, but it''s okay.","index":63,"end_time":114.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We were all together anyway.","index":64,"end_time":115.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We were all together sick, so.","index":65,"end_time":117.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, at least you got to find.","index":66,"end_time":122.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Guys.","index":67,"end_time":123.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Hear you''re recovering, though.","index":68,"end_time":124.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":123.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":69,"end_time":125.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":70,"end_time":125.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Little by little.","index":71,"end_time":126.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cool.","index":72,"end_time":128.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yes.","index":73,"end_time":129.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me jump in here to our deck, have a.","index":74,"end_time":132.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A few things for you guys today.","index":75,"end_time":134.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just wanted to start off with a couple of project updates we''ve been working on.","index":76,"end_time":137.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just want to let you know that we did launch that assessment page that we had approved before break.","index":77,"end_time":141.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was already launched before then, but I just wanted to confirm with you now, we did that the last week before the holiday, so that is up and running now.","index":78,"end_time":150.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So hopefully we see some.","index":79,"end_time":152.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Some good.","index":80,"end_time":153.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, some new good things coming from that in the new year as people start amping up for the new.","index":81,"end_time":159.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":153.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The new work months and year.","index":82,"end_time":161.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so then, yeah, we''ll just keep an eye on that.","index":83,"end_time":164.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But just want to let you know that''s live.","index":84,"end_time":166.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the booth design options, I know we met Michael beforehand.","index":85,"end_time":171.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Josh, I don''t know if you had a chance to look at these yet.","index":86,"end_time":173.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":171.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure that design four, Michael, you said was your favorite.","index":87,"end_time":178.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":174.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that would be this one here.","index":88,"end_time":180.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And the idea behind it, I don''t know if you already told you, is just because you guys normally have a table right here.","index":89,"end_time":185.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We wanted to make sure that none of the text on the booth design was blocked.","index":90,"end_time":189.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way people could see it, even if someone''s standing in front of it.","index":91,"end_time":191.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if this is the one you guys agree on, we can go ahead and get this all print ready and send you the final cuts, everything.","index":92,"end_time":198.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if that''s good to go.","index":93,"end_time":199.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, we.","index":94,"end_time":202.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Look, we''ve had lots of feedback.","index":95,"end_time":204.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, Josh, three or four make a decision.","index":96,"end_time":209.409,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m.","index":97,"end_time":210.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":210.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m fine with number.","index":98,"end_time":211.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Number.","index":99,"end_time":212.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"One.","index":100,"end_time":220.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"One thing that''s, you know, I think in.","index":101,"end_time":223.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"In some prior versions, and I don''t know what our current one looks like, we had kind of our tagline like kill stockouts, limited excess or the equivalent was maybe a bit more prominent and high up.","index":102,"end_time":234.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like Michael, for just the reason you''re talking about, you have to get really.","index":103,"end_time":237.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":234.779,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You''re gonna have to get really close to the booth, possibly to see that text at the bottom, because there''s going to be booths next to ours and people standing around and all kinds of reasons why it''s kind of could be blocked chairs, tables set up.","index":104,"end_time":253.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I''m wondering, like, we.","index":105,"end_time":256.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We do have.","index":106,"end_time":259.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":258.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Sorry, go ahead.","index":107,"end_time":261.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I was just checking the other ones to make sure that I think they were all in the corner.","index":108,"end_time":263.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just want to double check.","index":109,"end_time":264.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''m okay with.","index":110,"end_time":266.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m okay with keeping that language down there.","index":111,"end_time":269.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But I''m wondering, like, someone who looks at our booth, they''re going to look at the top third, like above the top fold.","index":112,"end_time":275.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right.","index":113,"end_time":275.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I mean, it''s kind of like a website too.","index":114,"end_time":277.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Even if they just walk up to it and they have a totally unobstructed view.","index":115,"end_time":280.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It feels like something in the first third should grab them.","index":116,"end_time":283.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":280.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I think the way to.","index":117,"end_time":287.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"When I say grab them, I mean, like, I''m wondering, should we communicate what we do in some way higher up?","index":118,"end_time":293.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So, like, for example, I know I''d mess up having these things side by side.","index":119,"end_time":297.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But, like, we have some white space under less risk.","index":120,"end_time":300.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Should we shift the less Rick section down?","index":121,"end_time":302.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Or maybe at the.","index":122,"end_time":303.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Underneath, it put like a kind of a call out or a quoted text or something that''s like, should we.","index":123,"end_time":309.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Should we.","index":124,"end_time":309.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I mean, we have enough room.","index":125,"end_time":311.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Should we put it at the top somewhere so you could, you know, justify the logo and tagline left and then have some kind of a quote or large text that sort of.","index":126,"end_time":322.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"In that dark bold text announces what we do?","index":127,"end_time":325.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m.","index":128,"end_time":325.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m obviously spitballing here, but I''m just like, when I look at the top third of this, I don''t know that I''m going to be able to notice and read inventory optimization as a service, because it''s just small, small font.","index":129,"end_time":335.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s the headline?","index":130,"end_time":337.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s.","index":131,"end_time":337.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s the one thing I want you to read?","index":132,"end_time":339.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":337.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And right now, I think the things that jump out to me are less risk and more reward, which is obviously really nonspecific.","index":133,"end_time":345.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right.","index":134,"end_time":346.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What do you guys think about that?","index":135,"end_time":347.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m just pulling up our designer''s notes because I.","index":136,"end_time":351.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We did talk to him about, like, the whole idea behind it ahead of time.","index":137,"end_time":355.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m just looking at his thing here specifically.","index":138,"end_time":359.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But one of the pictures we got was this.","index":139,"end_time":361.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So which was the reason we wanted to move.","index":140,"end_time":364.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you said, there''s a space beneath it, but that was more so just factoring in this kind of covering that.","index":141,"end_time":372.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s why there''s a.","index":142,"end_time":373.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That space below.","index":143,"end_time":375.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So there wouldn''t be too much extra room without blocking it, I guess, on the left side if we added something else in that way.","index":144,"end_time":383.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, but if you look at the new design, the whole bottom third is like, the space is still above the bottom third.","index":145,"end_time":390.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right.","index":146,"end_time":390.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if you look at also just the size of the print, like, go back to the actual image.","index":147,"end_time":394.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I don''t know.","index":148,"end_time":395.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I don''t know how much of this wraps around, but I''m just like.","index":149,"end_time":397.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Visually, the.","index":150,"end_time":398.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"The word hydrian is.","index":151,"end_time":400.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":398.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It looks like it might be a third.","index":152,"end_time":404.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s probably more like a quarter of the width, but I''m wondering.","index":153,"end_time":408.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It looks like.","index":154,"end_time":409.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It looks like the print is bigger on that one.","index":155,"end_time":412.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s right.","index":156,"end_time":413.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But then the one Thing I noticed too is fewer stockouts, less inventory is extremely prominent.","index":157,"end_time":418.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s one of the first things you read on the current booth.","index":158,"end_time":421.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":423.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If that specific tagline is the thing that you want to be seen first, then we can just move it around and he can create a couple different variations like he did with this one.","index":160,"end_time":435.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"He created the same variation in different formatting.","index":161,"end_time":437.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we could just say we want this to be more prominent and he can create a couple different ways.","index":162,"end_time":442.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the top sizing, I think when it is like the print ready actual asset file that will like, this will be more prominent.","index":163,"end_time":449.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The top, the actual logo.","index":164,"end_time":451.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But this is just kind of how it''ll sit, like the design and picture.","index":165,"end_time":454.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''re right.","index":166,"end_time":455.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This would be in the corner.","index":167,"end_time":456.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you want this to be more prominent, we can move.","index":168,"end_time":459.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Move it up and just see how he think it would look with like a design mind, how it would look best to fit in.","index":169,"end_time":466.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":459.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the other things, is there something that you would say is the least what you''re worried about people seeing immediately?","index":170,"end_time":474.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It sounds like obviously your logo would be first, then this would be something you want to be prominent.","index":171,"end_time":479.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":474.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Out of these two things, is there one that you would prefer is more visible than the other?","index":172,"end_time":484.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like more prominently put certain like way.","index":173,"end_time":488.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s a.","index":174,"end_time":488.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I know like common sense says you should have your logo first, but I don''t know actually how important that is.","index":175,"end_time":495.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, so you could stick that whole logo block down under the less risk part.","index":176,"end_time":500.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then you''d have a whole.","index":177,"end_time":502.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":501.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You could fit a.","index":178,"end_time":503.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You know, that whole entire top of the banner then is free for a headline, whether it''s kill stock.","index":179,"end_time":509.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s limited excess.","index":180,"end_time":510.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":509.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Or you could have a second sort of thing.","index":181,"end_time":512.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like.","index":182,"end_time":512.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You could.","index":183,"end_time":518.989,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.509,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You could pull inventory optimization as a service out of the logo and put it as your banner.","index":184,"end_time":525.309,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.989,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m just trying to think like, how does someone across the room see that we do something?","index":185,"end_time":529.709,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.949,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like if they''re thinking about inventory, how does our sign from across the room immediately catch their eye and make them walk over.","index":186,"end_time":536.109,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":529.709,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":541.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Give it a go.","index":188,"end_time":544.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, I think, yeah.","index":189,"end_time":546.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If we have sort of fill stock outs excess left and right, maybe put the logo in the top left hydrant below it somewhere.","index":190,"end_time":556.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Mm.","index":191,"end_time":557.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.399,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we just pull this back up.","index":192,"end_time":562.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would move.","index":193,"end_time":563.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re saying, Josh, potentially put the hydra in down here.","index":194,"end_time":566.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Move your tagline up to the front.","index":195,"end_time":568.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would you maybe want it like not on top of each other.","index":196,"end_time":571.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then it would be side to side.","index":197,"end_time":572.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like Killstock.","index":198,"end_time":573.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Helps eliminate access into sentence form.","index":199,"end_time":576.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":577.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I was actually thinking of putting the logo and maybe this would look goofy, but I was thinking use that white, the blue space under less risk that you have.","index":201,"end_time":584.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, that''s kind of.","index":202,"end_time":585.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Well, you still have lots of padding.","index":203,"end_time":587.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If you move the logo and everything down there.","index":204,"end_time":589.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":590.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":206,"end_time":590.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then you just use like.","index":207,"end_time":591.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like we said that whole.","index":208,"end_time":592.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That whole top banners for the tagline.","index":209,"end_time":596.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":592.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Maybe maybe this would, like, if that.","index":210,"end_time":599.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, imagine if it just across the entire top of the booth, it said inventory optimization as a service and as big a letters as you can fit.","index":211,"end_time":605.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay.","index":212,"end_time":606.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, inventory optimization as a service is kind of an interesting and unique and very accurate description of what we do.","index":213,"end_time":613.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":607,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right.","index":214,"end_time":614.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then, you know, maybe you keep kill stock Excellent excess down.","index":215,"end_time":618.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Down low.","index":216,"end_time":619.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Because I think that''s.","index":217,"end_time":621.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s good space to use.","index":218,"end_time":622.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s just not going to be what people see first.","index":219,"end_time":624.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right.","index":220,"end_time":625.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just bring the attention then to the tagline and then have the logo down here.","index":221,"end_time":629.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":222,"end_time":630.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can move that as far as the actual, like, logo piece.","index":223,"end_time":634.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would you be okay with that staying up to the left of this line?","index":224,"end_time":638.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just because we already have that piece here, it might be, like a good way to just brand your tagline, even though that''s what we''re seeing first.","index":225,"end_time":644.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I. I''m good with that.","index":226,"end_time":646.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Doesn''t take up a ton of space.","index":227,"end_time":647.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":228,"end_time":650.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I will send that back to our design team and just see that they''ll probably make, like, another four variations, so we can mess around with that and see what you like best and we''ll go from there.","index":229,"end_time":659.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":230,"end_time":663.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":231,"end_time":667.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So then for the brochure, I know we had talked a little bit about this to Michael at one of the previous times.","index":232,"end_time":672.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the design, we''re working on this right now, kind of redoing that as well.","index":233,"end_time":676.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We had talked about doing a QR code, kind of just adding it somewhere.","index":234,"end_time":681.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that way instead of having it on the backdrop where it could break or anything like that, it''s something we could print out and change with no issue.","index":235,"end_time":688.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there a particular page that you had in mind that you''re like.","index":236,"end_time":691.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we had to bring somebody to a page from a brochure handout, it would be this.","index":237,"end_time":694.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":691.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if so, we can.","index":238,"end_time":696.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.429,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Also.","index":239,"end_time":696.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Bailey had mentioned previously she had created a duplicate of a page with a different URL so we could track conversions specifically for your events.","index":240,"end_time":706.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we could do something like that.","index":241,"end_time":708.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If it''s like, whether it''s the assessment page like this or it''s this one''s the outdated version, but an Assessment page like this or the Contact Us page.","index":242,"end_time":718.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And you want to make it unique to, like, an event setting.","index":243,"end_time":720.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can, like, create a separate landing page that that QR code links to so we can track conversions specific to that.","index":244,"end_time":726.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That makes a lot of sense, I think.","index":245,"end_time":728.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":729.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"One of the things I was thinking about is do we want to do away with the brochure itself?","index":247,"end_time":734.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Do we just want to get rid of the brochure as a hard copy and then create, like a stand where the QR code is?","index":248,"end_time":742.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I want to know something just wise.","index":249,"end_time":744.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":745.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the QR code will take them to the brochure itself.","index":251,"end_time":748.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":252,"end_time":749.799,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just get rid of the paper and just have, like, maybe we could design like some kind of flyer that you put on a stand with the QR code that kind of explains what it is.","index":253,"end_time":757.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.799,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":757.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know because I have no idea how this works, but people do turn up, they pick up the brochure, it goes in.","index":255,"end_time":765.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":757.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":256,"end_time":767.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t know how people think about things nowadays.","index":257,"end_time":770.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Whether or not having it to their phone is sufficient.","index":258,"end_time":774.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Do they then lose it?","index":259,"end_time":775.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Do they not know it?","index":260,"end_time":776.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They had a hard copy.","index":261,"end_time":778.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Would that be better?","index":262,"end_time":778.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m looking for advice, really.","index":263,"end_time":780.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think it depends on the person, because I think my mom always says she always prefers paper over everything.","index":264,"end_time":787.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":781.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She''s very much like that mindset.","index":265,"end_time":789.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":787.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I like both, honestly.","index":266,"end_time":791.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":789.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But a way to think about it if we''re trying to avoid having to have the printouts is if somebody stops at your booth and they scan the QR code and then they take a look at it and they, like, close the Safari app and they keep walking, it''s still going to remain in that tab.","index":267,"end_time":803.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s not like it''s easily lost it, that it''ll still be open in that tab unless they choose to close it.","index":268,"end_time":808.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":803.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whereas if you have a paper copy and they lose it, then they didn''t scan it right away.","index":269,"end_time":812.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it could.","index":270,"end_time":813.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You could honestly do both, where you have the option for someone to just scan a QR code, which then pops up the brochure and then you can have like a version of it on the table ready to go and kind of.","index":271,"end_time":824.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would potentially be safer.","index":272,"end_time":826.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think, you know, you''ve got both things.","index":273,"end_time":828.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think also to your point, that gives us more wiggle room with regard to what we can actually show on the scan code.","index":274,"end_time":834.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":275,"end_time":834.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then you can always change out that QR code easily if you wanted to change it or make any adjustments.","index":276,"end_time":839.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you Go to, like, events, and then you can give us, you know, real time feedback.","index":277,"end_time":843.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like more people actually grab paper than they did scan it and then.","index":278,"end_time":846.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":279,"end_time":846.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"To have the option of both would be good.","index":280,"end_time":848.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that way we can kind of test it, see which people like, and then that way you''re not missing out either way.","index":281,"end_time":854.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Josh, you.","index":282,"end_time":855.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You good with that?","index":283,"end_time":855.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":284,"end_time":856.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll do a code, have a hard copy.","index":285,"end_time":860.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":286,"end_time":861.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Good.","index":287,"end_time":862.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thanks for that.","index":288,"end_time":862.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll design.","index":289,"end_time":864.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll design a, like a stand option and then the.","index":290,"end_time":867.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":864.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But anyway, about, like the QR code page, Is there something specific, like a page that you would say?","index":291,"end_time":871.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is where we want it to go.","index":292,"end_time":873.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":871.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would it be the free assessment page?","index":293,"end_time":875.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would it be the contact us page?","index":294,"end_time":876.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, gosh, I don''t know.","index":295,"end_time":879.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, the thing is, again, we''re sort of struggling with which one actually would get the most traction.","index":296,"end_time":884.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Would it be the assessment?","index":297,"end_time":885.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Ideally we would like.","index":298,"end_time":887.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because if we''re talking to them, the first thing we would do is try to promote the assessment anyway.","index":299,"end_time":892.939,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And we would want to encourage them to do the assessment.","index":300,"end_time":895.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.939,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":301,"end_time":896.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I think that would make sense that we would, you know, probably send.","index":302,"end_time":899.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I agree.","index":303,"end_time":900.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, I was going to say, whatever you''re talking to them about at an event, if you''re saying, like, oh, we have this assessment, then it''s right there, go ahead and skim this and it''ll pop up something like that.","index":304,"end_time":909.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if that''s what you''re already talking to them about, that might be a good option.","index":305,"end_time":912.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we can just take the new version we just made live and create like a separate landing page, like we said, so we can track conversion on there.","index":306,"end_time":919.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":307,"end_time":920.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, so great.","index":308,"end_time":922.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So let''s just be real clear.","index":309,"end_time":923.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":922.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll have.","index":310,"end_time":924.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":923.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have a brochure, but we''ll.","index":311,"end_time":926.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"The scan itself would take them to the website and it would take them to.","index":312,"end_time":929.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":926.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, and we can create like a little small flyer you could put in a.","index":313,"end_time":935.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On a stand that just says scan here for that too.","index":314,"end_time":937.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll do both.","index":315,"end_time":938.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great, that''s perfect.","index":316,"end_time":939.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And would it just take them to the live site?","index":317,"end_time":942.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It would just be a link to the live website.","index":318,"end_time":944.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Wouldn''t just be a standalone page.","index":319,"end_time":946.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":944.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"No, it''ll be a link to the free assessment page, but we can just make a duplicate and change the URL.","index":320,"end_time":952.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that way when you go to events, we''ll see these people actually scanned it at the event and not just direct traffic or organic traffic.","index":321,"end_time":958.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way we can differentiate the two.","index":322,"end_time":960.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it''ll still be the Same assessment page.","index":323,"end_time":962.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":960.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I just don''t want them to go to a landing page.","index":324,"end_time":964.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That.","index":325,"end_time":964.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":964.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":326,"end_time":965.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":964.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It wouldn''t go anywhere because I want them to then go there and then they go around the whole thing and see.","index":327,"end_time":969.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I got what you''re saying.","index":328,"end_time":970.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":329,"end_time":970.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll make sure that it''s like the actual page.","index":330,"end_time":972.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":970.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if they want to go to contact us or blogs, they can continue to go from there.","index":331,"end_time":976.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":332,"end_time":977.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":333,"end_time":978.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":334,"end_time":979.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just shifting gears now to the survey now that we''ve run the last one for the past couple months.","index":335,"end_time":985.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":980.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That one was turned off in Limlist.","index":336,"end_time":987.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now we can shift eventually to the survey monkey one next week.","index":337,"end_time":989.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But 2,400 emails were sent out there and then we had 61 page views and 15 submissions.","index":338,"end_time":996.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":990.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you''ve looked through those responses yet.","index":339,"end_time":999.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve done all of that.","index":340,"end_time":1002.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''ve looked through the responses and we''ve actually produced some content for it from it as well.","index":341,"end_time":1006.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Oh, awesome.","index":342,"end_time":1007.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":343,"end_time":1008.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":344,"end_time":1009.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you want to share that with me now or like specifics or do you want to go through SurveyMonkey next?","index":345,"end_time":1014.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1009.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll go through SurveyMonkey, but just very quickly, I won''t show you anything.","index":346,"end_time":1017.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So Josh has got couple more drafts.","index":347,"end_time":1019.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I''ve got four posts for LinkedIn.","index":348,"end_time":1021.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":349,"end_time":1022.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And the content for the newsletter.","index":350,"end_time":1025.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we will go with what we discussed, which is we''ll do a one page.","index":351,"end_time":1030.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Like instead of the individual boxes, we''ll have a page for the survey results and then we''ll still have in green what we think and, you know, we''ll pick a new story and do it.","index":352,"end_time":1041.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So Josh has just got the drafts on that once.","index":353,"end_time":1044.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Once he''s approved or given the feedback on those, we will get those to you as soon as we possibly can, but.","index":354,"end_time":1052.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Awesome, that sounds great.","index":355,"end_time":1053.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said, I want Josh to finalize so that we can get it done.","index":356,"end_time":1059.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then so now just quickly on LinkedIn, I''m giving four posts.","index":357,"end_time":1065.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I can''t remember if you guys are still sort of keen, like one or two a week, isn''t it?","index":358,"end_time":1072.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, well, we have all across all four of the accounts.","index":359,"end_time":1076.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re doing the Tuesday, Thursday still cadence on the main page and then same with all of your personal pages.","index":360,"end_time":1083.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we''re reusing the content, but I can move those around now if you have new content for us to promote and just shift the date.","index":361,"end_time":1090.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":362,"end_time":1091.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m just trying to think of how much we, you know, if we want to sort of do once a week, twice A week.","index":363,"end_time":1095.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1091.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It does obviously impact the, you know, the content because we still, we, we have this, you know, we have the, the, the sort of first part, phase one content, the survey.","index":364,"end_time":1107.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I don''t have anything else after that.","index":365,"end_time":1110.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I''m trying to, I''m trying to sort of grasp at straws.","index":366,"end_time":1113.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was thinking about this at the end of December, what to write and I drafted out those things and I don''t know.","index":367,"end_time":1120.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Well, I know we had talked about this too.","index":368,"end_time":1123.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll just skip over here.","index":369,"end_time":1124.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You and I had talked a little bit about potentially doing like a year recap and like a look ahead to 2026 if we needed break in between where you wanted to prepare something and have more time for the February issue.","index":370,"end_time":1136.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1124.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, oops, I went ahead and just created this outline.","index":371,"end_time":1140.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1137.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If it''s like you''re still interested in where I just kind of put out something, this is a bit long.","index":372,"end_time":1145.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1140.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll have to make it.","index":373,"end_time":1146.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But just kind of show like as we look back in the year.","index":374,"end_time":1150.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let''s take a moment, go back.","index":375,"end_time":1151.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then you and I had talked about maybe doing like a hydran, like your take on things.","index":376,"end_time":1155.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just highlighted here where you could talk about supply chain themes that you''ve seen in 2025, what your takeaway is as a company.","index":377,"end_time":1164.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1155.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then maybe if you had any stuff with your specific clients that you wanted to share that happened last year.","index":378,"end_time":1170.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then also like company highlights, I know we talked about potentially doing.","index":379,"end_time":1173.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then lastly it would just kind of wrap up and talk about what we''re looking ahead for in 2026.","index":380,"end_time":1179.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I know it was an idea that we had of potentially doing for January if we needed more time breakup.","index":381,"end_time":1184.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if that''s still something you want.","index":382,"end_time":1186.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To do, I think we''re pretty close on the survey.","index":383,"end_time":1189.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1186.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think we have to do this.","index":384,"end_time":1191.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I do like this because it does give me some thoughts for content for LinkedIn.","index":385,"end_time":1199.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":386,"end_time":1201.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can do that.","index":387,"end_time":1202.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1201.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Go ahead and maybe use some of this material.","index":388,"end_time":1204.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We have to think about this and actually go ahead and maybe create something for the website because the library has got two new reports from December, but it hasn''t got anything else in January.","index":389,"end_time":1215.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That might not be a bad idea actually, Taylor, just to maybe think about creating something for the website and then spin off content for LinkedIn and then whatever else feeds into.","index":390,"end_time":1230.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because we''ve been promising the survey information for some time.","index":391,"end_time":1233.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we have to deliver on that because we did it last time we said results from the survey are coming soon.","index":392,"end_time":1239.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve got to fulfill that.","index":393,"end_time":1241.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But you''re absolutely right.","index":394,"end_time":1242.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We.","index":395,"end_time":1242.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We did say if we didn''t have anything, we needed something else.","index":396,"end_time":1245.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But like you said, we could, we could move it into other forms of content.","index":397,"end_time":1248.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1245.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And something I just did with one of my other clients actually is I created like a carousel that we were able to use on LinkedIn just organically.","index":398,"end_time":1256.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1248.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you just create like carousel images.","index":399,"end_time":1258.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1256.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we could basically do the same thing here where if you did like a year in review, our design can team can just create like four different image slides and then we just upload it into Publer and it becomes like a carousel image where people can just scroll through and see like the updates and we can put it into like bullet form on the images where we kind of highlight these things as well.","index":400,"end_time":1278.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It could be like even a series of like, you know, what we saw in 2025, what we''re looking for in 2026.","index":401,"end_time":1283.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But that''s just like another creative way to do it where you could add some design elements just to the organic.","index":402,"end_time":1288.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Doesn''t have to be anything huge either.","index":403,"end_time":1290.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1288.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s something that we could put together just as like an organic style post.","index":404,"end_time":1294.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, we could definitely utilize that and just kind of make it more compelling.","index":405,"end_time":1298.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1294.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"People like imagery, so.","index":406,"end_time":1299.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1298.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":407,"end_time":1300.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"If you''ve got examples you''re allowed to share, that would be nice to see.","index":408,"end_time":1303.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1304.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hopefully can inspire us and definitely share this with us as well, because then that gives me more to think about when it.","index":410,"end_time":1311.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"When it comes to, you know, what else we should be putting out there.","index":411,"end_time":1314.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.94,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1315.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will pull together a folder in Google Drive and I''ll send it over to you with a couple of the other things I''ve done for my clients.","index":413,"end_time":1320.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Lovely.","index":414,"end_time":1321.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":415,"end_time":1322.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1321.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":416,"end_time":1323.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay, so let me go back here then.","index":417,"end_time":1326.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So for SurveyMonkey, we have the form ready to go.","index":418,"end_time":1330.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1328.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I went ahead and updated the question four that you had talked about.","index":419,"end_time":1333.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1330.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The one in HubSpot we actually won''t utilize this time around because we''ll keep everything in SurveyMonkey.","index":420,"end_time":1337.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I did change it in SurveyMonkey because it was the same typo error.","index":421,"end_time":1342.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that has been changed now for the launch.","index":422,"end_time":1346.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I figured next Tuesday morning would be a good day to launch it so we can get that prepped to go.","index":423,"end_time":1351.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1346.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Something I did want to note is a couple of our internal team members, we''ve been noticing that a couple of the domains that were purchased through mailforge have not had the best deliverability over the past, like, year.","index":424,"end_time":1363.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1352.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ve all noticed that.","index":425,"end_time":1363.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we''ve talked about that through lemlist and stuff.","index":426,"end_time":1366.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re in the process right now of acquiring some new domains for your team that are just going to be through smart lead and that way they''ll be fresh.","index":427,"end_time":1375.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They''re warming up too, so that way we can utilize those.","index":428,"end_time":1378.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1379.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1379.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Have better deliverability.","index":430,"end_time":1380.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did see in.","index":431,"end_time":1382.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"In.","index":432,"end_time":1382.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In HubSpot actually there were a couple of warnings about some domains.","index":433,"end_time":1388.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1382.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I.","index":434,"end_time":1389.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, it''s something that we''ve noticed across the team and I think there was like a article on it too that our owner had sent us.","index":435,"end_time":1396.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, for some reason the mailforge had like gone down or something and the domain deliverability just kind of plummeted.","index":436,"end_time":1403.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So now everybody''s shifting gears and so we wanted to stay ahead of that.","index":437,"end_time":1406.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And for the SurveyMonkey one, we''ll keep the current one that we have as planned.","index":438,"end_time":1411.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We ran a couple of tests and everything.","index":439,"end_time":1413.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1411.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So once the other ones are warmed up though, for the following month we''ll insert those into SurveyMonkey and switch them out.","index":440,"end_time":1419.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1413.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we should be good to go as normal for the.","index":441,"end_time":1422.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For the launch that we have prepared for Tuesday.","index":442,"end_time":1424.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":443,"end_time":1425.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1424.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So yeah, so everything will be in one place, which is great.","index":444,"end_time":1429.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we talked about the survey.","index":445,"end_time":1433.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1432.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll look for that then.","index":446,"end_time":1434.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1433.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the newsletter and then the content that we were talking about, just wanted to go through the organic stats.","index":447,"end_time":1441.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1434.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This was just from the past year that we had here.","index":448,"end_time":1444.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1441.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The followers connections have the increase, which is really great.","index":449,"end_time":1448.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1444.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And reach and engagements continue to stay up.","index":450,"end_time":1450.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1448.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":451,"end_time":1452.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.679,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then with the new content too, we''ll continue to see these increase because now we have that consistency back that we''re reusing.","index":452,"end_time":1458.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So one of the things I was thinking about as well, talking about sort of connections and things like that.","index":453,"end_time":1465.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was reading Bailey''s post about branding, personal branding.","index":454,"end_time":1469.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1465.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It did make me think, do you think we need to look at our.","index":455,"end_time":1477.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because I''m thinking it''s mine probably Drew.","index":456,"end_time":1481.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1477.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Definitely Josh our LinkedIn pages because if.","index":457,"end_time":1486.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1481.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I know this for a fact, because I don''t, even though I don''t have the premium of LinkedIn in, I''d see all the people who actually go and see me and I do see our potential customers, existing customers go on to onto my LinkedIn page and I''m sure they do.","index":458,"end_time":1501.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":459,"end_time":1501.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They definitely do it for job.","index":460,"end_time":1503.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I do wonder if it''s something we might want to think about.","index":461,"end_time":1507.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1504.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I do wonder if it''s probably as important as how well the website actually is displayed is how well our LinkedIn pages are displayed.","index":462,"end_time":1516.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1507.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I do.","index":463,"end_time":1517.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1516.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You''re saying like you''re individual posts being.","index":464,"end_time":1519.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Our own, our own individual LinkedIn pages.","index":465,"end_time":1523.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I do wonder if that''s something we might want to build into the program when we can.","index":466,"end_time":1528.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, maybe having a review of our, I think just the three of us, I don''t, I don''t know.","index":467,"end_time":1536.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know if the other people''s actually track who looks at their LinkedIn page.","index":468,"end_time":1541.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1536.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But just for the sake of argument, Josh is front and center.","index":469,"end_time":1545.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So his priority, mine could be as well particularly because obviously the interaction I have with the prospects and things like that.","index":470,"end_time":1554.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So just something to make a note of, if you wouldn''t mind.","index":471,"end_time":1557.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1554.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we should maybe sort of when we got some time to pencil some, some points into that.","index":472,"end_time":1563.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely add that to our brainstorm that''s coming up at the end of the month.","index":473,"end_time":1567.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can add that in as a point to note.","index":474,"end_time":1570.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1568.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But one of my other clients that I have, he''s the founder and CEO, like this situation too.","index":475,"end_time":1575.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so for the main page, like their company page, we do the same similar like kind of reuse their blog posts that they''ve had any news and things like that.","index":476,"end_time":1583.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But then for his particular content I just send him like a Google sheet each month and I ask him to like just write down some things that are happening across his industry and then give me like some things to work with.","index":477,"end_time":1593.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then from there I just create posts that are more thought leadership centric that come from him as the CEO, as the founder to kind of talk about their specific, you know, brand but also like the industry specific items that we talk about, like whether it''s tariffs here and things like that.","index":478,"end_time":1610.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because that way it differentiates like you''re saying the content from like main page.","index":479,"end_time":1613.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You know, this is the latest blog we post and kind of separates Josh and you as like thought leaders.","index":480,"end_time":1618.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You actually know what you''re talking about.","index":481,"end_time":1619.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re seeing what''s going on in the industry.","index":482,"end_time":1621.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1619.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it can be done for sure where we, we differentiate the two while still like working content in um.","index":483,"end_time":1628.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1622.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said, I do that for my other clients.","index":484,"end_time":1630.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1628.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it''s definitely something that I think would be beneficial.","index":485,"end_time":1632.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1630.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you''re saying just to create that separation.","index":486,"end_time":1635.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1632.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, and I think as well it just sort of helps with.","index":487,"end_time":1637.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Helps, you''re quite right.","index":488,"end_time":1639.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is that thought leadership things?","index":489,"end_time":1640.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So what is the website?","index":490,"end_time":1641.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1640.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Why should I be working with these people''s front of mind?","index":491,"end_time":1645.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1641.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because I see him all the time.","index":492,"end_time":1646.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1645.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''m lovely saying I want to see what his pages looks like, but that seems, and I totally agree with what Bailey was saying, because I know a lot of people do that.","index":493,"end_time":1656.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"They do look at the individual.","index":494,"end_time":1657.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":495,"end_time":1658.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":496,"end_time":1658.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1658.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You want to position.","index":497,"end_time":1659.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1658.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Position as the thought leader where.","index":498,"end_time":1662.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Where possible, obviously, because that''s the whole point.","index":499,"end_time":1666.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1662.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":500,"end_time":1667.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that just brings me to the brainstorm.","index":501,"end_time":1669.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Anyway, so I had a couple of notes on here, just talking about a couple things I know you and I had mentioned.","index":502,"end_time":1673.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I can add that as a point to.","index":503,"end_time":1676.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1673.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To our deck.","index":504,"end_time":1677,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That will start for talking about the specific expert content.","index":505,"end_time":1680.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, and then we can just touch base on any of the other topics.","index":506,"end_time":1684.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if there was anything specific that you guys wanted to see in that meeting, we''ll have a whole hour to.","index":507,"end_time":1688.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To go through some stuff.","index":508,"end_time":1690,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If there''s anything additional that comes through, let us know and we''ll come prepared with that.","index":509,"end_time":1694.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1690.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, but yeah, looking forward to it.","index":510,"end_time":1696.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1694.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it''ll be a good time to brainstorm.","index":511,"end_time":1698.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We will definitely.","index":512,"end_time":1699.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1698.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We got some time to.","index":513,"end_time":1700.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"To think through that before the 28th, and we''ll make sure we give you as much feedback as we possibly can.","index":514,"end_time":1706.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1701.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":515,"end_time":1708.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":516,"end_time":1709.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, I know we got.","index":517,"end_time":1711.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ve run out of time very, very quickly.","index":518,"end_time":1713.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''ve added some more names to the abm, the new ABM list.","index":519,"end_time":1717.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, remind me.","index":520,"end_time":1719.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1717.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"There''s two worksheets.","index":521,"end_time":1721.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"The one I think is the second worksheet.","index":522,"end_time":1723.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is that the one where I should be adding new stuff to?","index":523,"end_time":1726.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So you''re talking about the companies list one.","index":524,"end_time":1728.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1726.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Specifically one, yeah.","index":525,"end_time":1730.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, gosh, probably.","index":526,"end_time":1731.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I bet you I''ve closed it now.","index":527,"end_time":1732.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1731.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s the abm.","index":528,"end_time":1734.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I bet you''ve closed it.","index":529,"end_time":1738.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1736.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sorry, I apologize.","index":530,"end_time":1739.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I''ll find it and send it to you.","index":531,"end_time":1740.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, just if you want to send that one over to me, I''ll confirm on my end because I know we did have like a running EBM one, and then we have the new companies list one.","index":532,"end_time":1748.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1742.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''ve got it here.","index":533,"end_time":1752.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":534,"end_time":1752.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Hydrogen companies list updated.","index":535,"end_time":1754.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I''ve got the remove list, and I''ve got the Hydrian companies list updated.","index":536,"end_time":1760.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1755,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I''m assuming it''s the removed list is where I''d be adding new ones to.","index":537,"end_time":1765.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1761.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Am I getting that right?","index":538,"end_time":1766.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think so.","index":539,"end_time":1767.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1766.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if you could just send me the three links, I''m thinking let''s make this easier on everybody and let''s see if we can consolidate a couple of them and just make it a one sheet.","index":540,"end_time":1775.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1767.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now that we have the company''s list, we can at least make it separate tabs in the same sheet.","index":541,"end_time":1779.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way we don''t have to have three different links.","index":542,"end_time":1781.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll take this offline, and I would go ahead and send that to you with support.","index":543,"end_time":1786.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1781.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":544,"end_time":1787.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1786.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you both.","index":545,"end_time":1788.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1787.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope you have a good rest of your day.","index":546,"end_time":1789.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You as well.","index":547,"end_time":1790.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1789.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Take care.","index":548,"end_time":1790.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1790.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You too.","index":549,"end_time":1791.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1790.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"}],"dateString":"2026-01-07T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1","participants":["josh@hydrian.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,michael.jones@hydrian.com,taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","josh@hydrian.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","michael.jones@hydrian.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE7X3Y9JSTTANJ1MYX45SPQ3","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Launched the approved assessment page prior to holiday; now live and tracking early engagement results.","Agreed on booth design revisions; tagline and logo placement to improve visibility and clarity.","Confirmed QR code strategy to reduce print collateral; dual-format brochure approach will enable testing.","Aligned on redirecting QR scans to a duplicate assessment page to track event-driven conversions.","Planned LinkedIn and newsletter content based on prior survey insights and planned recap messaging."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Just want to let you know that we did launch that assessment page that we had approved before break.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"We''ll do a code, have a hard copy.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"Inventory optimization as a service is kind of an interesting and unique and very accurate description of what we do.","speaker":"Josh Bartel"}],"topics":["launch","content","design","events","tracking"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Booth Design and Event Marketing Materials**\n\nThe team decided to prioritize clearer messaging on the booth backdrop to better capture attendees’ attention and communicate the core service quickly.\n\n- **Josh Bartel suggested** emphasizing the tagline “**Inventory Optimization as a Service**” prominently across the top of the booth banner, moving the logo and “Kill stockouts, limited excess” text lower on the design to avoid important text being blocked by booth furniture or attendees (03:22)\n    - This change addresses concerns that the current font size and placement make key messages hard to read from a distance.\n    - The design team will create **four new variations** to test this arrangement and ensure visibility with a finalized print-ready file.\n    - Michael Jones agreed with prioritizing tagline visibility and proposed placing the logo in the lower left for branding balance.\n    - The clearer headline aims to increase booth engagement by immediately communicating the value proposition to passersby, improving lead generation efficiency.\n\n- For brochures and handouts, the team agreed to combine **physical flyers with QR codes** linking to an event-specific landing page (11:04)\n    - Michael Jones proposed replacing the full brochure with a stand holding a flyer featuring a QR code, reducing print costs and improving flexibility.\n    - Taylor Doerbaum emphasized that the QR code link will point to a **dedicated assessment page** with a unique URL to track event-specific conversions.\n    - They will keep some physical copies available based on attendee preference, enabling testing of what drives higher engagement.\n    - This hybrid approach balances accessibility and tracking precision while allowing fast updates without reprinting.\n\n## **Survey and Content Strategy**\n\nThe recent email survey sent to **2,400 contacts** yielded **61 page views and 15 submissions**, informing upcoming content and marketing activity (16:17)\n\n- Michael Jones and Josh Bartel reviewed the responses and produced four LinkedIn posts plus newsletter content based on the survey insights (16:40)\n    - They plan a one-page summary of survey results with highlighted conclusions to replace detailed multi-box formats for clearer communication.\n    - New LinkedIn posts will follow the existing cadence of **two posts per week** on main and personal accounts, and dates will be adjusted as new content arrives.\n    - Michael highlighted the need to deliver on promised survey results promptly to maintain credibility and engagement.\n    - Taylor suggested supplementing survey content with a **year-in-review and 2026 outlook** post as a content bridge for January and February.\n\n- To boost engagement and thought leadership, Taylor proposed creating **LinkedIn carousel posts** summarizing key themes from 2025 and forecasts for 2026 (20:00)\n    - These image-based posts will provide visually compelling, easy-to-digest content for organic reach.\n    - Michael requested examples to guide content creation, which Taylor will share via Google Drive.\n    - This approach supports multi-format content reuse across channels, increasing audience touchpoints and reinforcing brand authority.\n\n## **LinkedIn Profile Optimization and Thought Leadership**\n\nAttention to personal LinkedIn profiles was identified as a critical but underutilized asset for customer engagement and brand positioning.\n\n- Michael Jones noted that potential and existing clients frequently view individual LinkedIn pages, making profile quality as important as the company website (24:19)\n    - He suggested reviewing and improving the LinkedIn pages of key team members—himself, Josh Bartel, and Drew—to maximize impact.\n    - Taylor agreed and described a process used for other clients where CEOs provide monthly industry insights that are crafted into thought leadership posts.\n    - This strategy creates a clear distinction between company updates and personal expert commentary, enhancing credibility and customer trust.\n    - The team plans to include LinkedIn profile optimization and personal branding in the brainstorming session scheduled for the end of the month (26:03).\n\n## **Survey Tool and Email Deliverability Improvements**\n\nThe team plans to switch survey distribution fully to SurveyMonkey next week and improve email deliverability by updating outreach domains.\n\n- Taylor confirmed the SurveyMonkey form is ready for launch next Tuesday, incorporating a corrected question and consolidating all survey activity on one platform (22:04)\n    - This switch streamlines data collection and survey management.\n    - Due to poor deliverability from **Mailforge-purchased domains** over the past year, new email domains are being acquired through **Smart Lead** for better inbox placement (22:59)\n    - These fresh domains are currently warming up and will be integrated into SurveyMonkey campaigns next month.\n    - Michael observed HubSpot warnings about domain issues, confirming the urgency of this change.\n    - Improved deliverability is expected to increase open rates and survey participation, enhancing marketing ROI.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) List Management**\n\nMichael Jones has added new companies to the ABM list and seeks clarification on updating procedures to improve list management efficiency.\n\n- He referenced multiple spreadsheets (“Hydrogen companies list updated,” “remove list”) and asked which to use for adding new companies (28:30)\n    - Taylor proposed consolidating the lists into a single spreadsheet with multiple tabs to reduce confusion and streamline updates.\n    - Michael agreed to send the current files offline for review and consolidation.\n    - Better list management will improve ABM targeting accuracy and reduce administrative overhead for the marketing team.","outline":null,"keywords":["Assessment page","Booth design","QR code marketing","Survey results","LinkedIn content strategy","ABM list"],"overview":"- **Booth Design Update:** Tagline “Inventory Optimization as a Service” will be emphasized for better engagement and visibility at events.  \n- **Hybrid Brochure Strategy:** Use physical flyers with QR codes linking to assessments, reducing print costs while improving tracking.  \n- **Survey Insights Review:** 2,400 contacts surveyed; generated 61 views, 15 submissions; 4 LinkedIn posts and newsletter content created.  \n- **Engagement Boost Proposal:** Create LinkedIn carousel posts summarizing 2025 themes and 2026 forecasts for enhanced audience reach.  \n- **LinkedIn Profile Importance:** Optimize personal LinkedIn pages for team members to improve engagement with potential clients and brand perception.  \n- **Survey Tool Transition:** Switching to SurveyMonkey next week for better data collection; new email domains acquired for improved deliverability.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nRequest new booth design variations emphasizing ''Inventory Optimization as a Service'' in top third and logo placement below (09:50)\nDesign QR code flyer for event stands alongside physical brochures (14:23)\nCreate duplicate landing page URL for event-specific tracking linked to QR code (15:46)\nProvide examples of LinkedIn carousel posts and organize a Google Drive folder with content samples (21:40)\nAdd LinkedIn personal branding review to brainstorm meeting agenda for Jan 28 (26:03)\nPrepare materials for the brainstorm session and request any additional agenda items (27:38)\nReview ABM company lists and work with Michael to consolidate into one sheet with tabs (29:26)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nProvide feedback on new LinkedIn posts drafts from survey content (16:46)\nConsider content and timing strategy for LinkedIn and website year-end recap and 2026 outlook posts (19:46)\nSend updated ABM company lists to Taylor for consolidation (28:50)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nFinalize content drafts for survey-related LinkedIn posts and newsletter for review and approval (16:46)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"f82c51d2-5f5b-489f-b9ff-787d2eb47806","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
