    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1',
    '{"id":"01KE098Y6D2JYDDHX5QJS08Z06","title":"AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Budget Adjustment and Financial Planning**\n\nThe team recognized a **negative budget deficit for Q1**, prompting a plan to rebalance funds from later quarters to cover immediate needs (03:03).\n\n- **Brent Willans** highlighted the deficit, emphasizing the importance of paying the team fairly and proposing to shift budget from **Q2, Q3, and Q4** back into **February and March** to cover current shortfalls.\n- This adjustment accounts for increased workload, including **contact mapping** and **ABM testing**, which exceeded initial Q1 estimates.\n- The plan anticipates moving to a **maintenance mode by Q3**, allowing a potential dip in spending before ramping up again in Q4 for the next fiscal cycle.\n- Brent requested feedback by Monday on how much budget to reallocate, with the goal of smoothing payments while maintaining project momentum.\n\n## **Lead Scoring and Sales Process Enhancement**\n\nImproving lead qualification with a custom scoring model is a key priority to increase sales effectiveness and nurture prospects over time (05:40).\n\n- Brent shared a detailed spreadsheet incorporating **HubSpot''s implicit and explicit scoring data**, aiming to develop an advanced system beyond HubSpot’s native limits.\n- Colin Costigan stressed that **lifecycle stages should not move backwards**, requiring manual checks for deals that fall through to maintain score accuracy.\n- The team plans to automate lists for **inactive leads** and develop outreach strategies to re-engage them, improving sales pipeline quality.\n- Brent emphasized strengthening the MQL process by providing BDRs with actionable intelligence on leads’ interests and next steps, moving beyond simple lead assignment to ongoing nurturing.\n\n## **Data Integration and Reporting Clarifications**\n\nClarifying data definitions and system filters is essential to ensure accurate reporting and seamless integration with Salesforce (01:45).\n\n- Colin explained the effort to map Salesforce fields to the data box filters, revealing inconsistencies like missing segmentation for **\"classic\" products** and unclear categories such as **\"utilities\"**.\n- Brent clarified that major product categories include **Whims, Aquarius, and Rio**, with many legacy products sunsetted, requiring cleanup for accurate reporting.\n- The team agreed to share and upload the **classic product list** to align data fields before pushing updates into Salesforce.\n- Colin confirmed workflows are set so that **contacts tagged as marketers in demand** are categorized as subscribers to avoid inflating MQL counts during form testing.\n\n## **Form Development and Lead Capture Priorities**\n\nBuilding and prioritizing custom forms is critical to capturing quality leads, with one form representing up to **10–20% of daily lead volume** (11:00).\n\n- Brent identified the **Hawk lead input form** as the top priority due to its significant lead contribution, with Colin agreeing to prioritize its completion.\n- Guille Santana reported technical issues caused by a HubSpot billing problem blocking form access, which Brent is actively resolving.\n- The team plans to consolidate form ownership and clarify distinctions between similar forms, with Brent coordinating with James (webmaster) and Blake (BDR lead) for final decisions.\n- Brent confirmed that some forms were run as isolated campaigns embedded via Marketo and WordPress, and will gather necessary source files and code from James to streamline redevelopment.\n\n## **Client Satisfaction and Partnership Support**\n\nStrong client feedback and a flexible staffing model underpin the team’s commitment to reliable delivery and growth support (16:38).\n\n- Brent shared positive references from **Vivian**, rating the team **10 out of 10** and offering to provide testimonials.\n- Colin emphasized the availability of extra staffing through an **accordion business model**, ensuring no bandwidth issues even during busy periods.\n- The team is prepared to step in as an integration partner for other companies if needed, reinforcing their role as a trusted resource.\n- Brent reiterated transparency and open communication as core values facilitating smooth collaboration and client confidence.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Data Box","Deficit Billing","HubSpot Scoring","Salesforce Filters","ROI Calculator","Hot Lead Input Form"],"overview":"- **Budget Reallocation:** Addressed Q1 budget deficit; plan to shift funds from Q2, Q3, Q4 to February and March.  \n- **Lead Scoring System:** Developing custom lead scoring model to enhance sales effectiveness; automation for inactive leads planned.  \n- **Data Integration Needs:** Focus on aligning Salesforce filters and mapping to ensure accurate reporting and avoid MQL inflation.  \n- **Form Prioritization:** Hawk lead input form prioritized to capture significant lead volume; addressing technical issues preventing access.  \n- **Client Satisfaction Metrics:** Positive client feedback; staffing model ensures support during busy periods, reinforcing trusted resource role.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nReview scoring model with team and send detailed spreadsheet to Colin and Guille for feedback by next week (05:34)\nProvide comprehensive classic product list for Salesforce filtering alignment (09:58)\nCoordinate with James to retrieve existing ROI calculator build code and share with Colin for redevelopment (10:59)\nClear HubSpot billing issues affecting form visibility and notify Guille once resolved (12:54)\nConfirm with James and Blake which “hot lead input” form version will be standardized and communicate decision to Guille (15:05)\nFollow-up with James regarding form hosting, campaign integration, and documentation (13:00)\nProvide updates or changes regarding deficit billing budget adjustments after internal discussion and communicate next steps to Colin by Monday (17:44)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and share filtered Salesforce report draft incorporating Barb’s segmentation feedback and product list for review by Barb and Kyle (08:38)\nBuild workflows to separate test form contacts to subscriber status to maintain clean MQL data (10:14)\nBegin redevelopment of ROI calculator once code received from James (11:01)\nDiscuss with Barb feasibility and impacts of moving budget forward and adjusting billing cycles for Q1 and Q2 (03:09)\nFollow up with Barb Monday to finalize scoring model details and budget plan adjustments (17:44)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nDocument list of all custom forms and coordinate with Barb and James to clarify form versions and usage, especially for hot lead input forms (11:11)\nClarify with Barb the main form used out of versions with different question sets and ensure proper integration once billing issues resolve (14:06)\n"},"duration":18,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Then, yeah.","index":0,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And do you mind doing the screen share?","index":1,"end_time":4.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just because I''m only on my laptop.","index":2,"end_time":6.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kind of limited.","index":3,"end_time":7.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, no worries.","index":4,"end_time":9.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m sure she''ll be here in a minute.","index":5,"end_time":13.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":15.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There she is.","index":7,"end_time":34.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":8,"end_time":42.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Barb.","index":9,"end_time":43.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Barb.","index":10,"end_time":44.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hi.","index":11,"end_time":45.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":12,"end_time":46.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":13,"end_time":47.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a bit of a different background.","index":14,"end_time":49.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re at our leadership annual planning meeting, so I''m.","index":15,"end_time":53.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":49.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just popped out of the conference room.","index":16,"end_time":55.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks for doing that.","index":17,"end_time":56.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":18,"end_time":56.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":19,"end_time":57.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll get you back in there.","index":20,"end_time":60.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Wouldn''t miss this for the world.","index":21,"end_time":61.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you kidding me?","index":22,"end_time":62.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, geez.","index":23,"end_time":63.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Aim higher, Colin.","index":24,"end_time":65.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Come on, that''s a low bar.","index":25,"end_time":68.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Talk me is the best part of my week.","index":26,"end_time":71.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":27,"end_time":75.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":76.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you want to pull up the agenda?","index":29,"end_time":78.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":30,"end_time":79.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":31,"end_time":84.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Barb, we also got your email last night for everything we wanted to cover, so.","index":32,"end_time":89.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I want to make sure that we get through all of that.","index":33,"end_time":91.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, if you can just go to the next slide, we''ll go ahead and get started.","index":34,"end_time":94.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the data box you just wanted us to put in, basically like what the filters and metrics are representing, I guess a little description.","index":35,"end_time":104.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we don''t even have to talk about it right now.","index":36,"end_time":107.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s, you know, I''m still reviewing it, but I just, I brought it up and I''m like, what does community mean?","index":37,"end_time":112.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just didn''t know.","index":38,"end_time":113.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, the rest of it''s pretty self explanatory, but Gaye or Colin, if you could just give me some definitions on.","index":39,"end_time":119.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"On page seven specifically, that''d be great.","index":40,"end_time":122.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":41,"end_time":123.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":122.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was me trying to match what Kyle had shared as like that table.","index":42,"end_time":129.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Break it down.","index":43,"end_time":130.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":129.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":131.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":132.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s what I was going for there.","index":46,"end_time":133.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":132.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that makes more sense to me.","index":47,"end_time":136.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":48,"end_time":137.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":137.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":49,"end_time":138.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that was kind of a placeholder of like, you know, let''s have you guys review this, see if this is what you meant or what Kyle was looking for.","index":50,"end_time":145.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me pull that up real quick.","index":51,"end_time":148.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t showed him yet.","index":52,"end_time":151.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think that''s next week.","index":53,"end_time":153.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, it looks amazing.","index":54,"end_time":154.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":55,"end_time":155.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":56,"end_time":156.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re pretty jazzed about it.","index":57,"end_time":158.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Vivian is like overjoyed.","index":58,"end_time":160.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":59,"end_time":160.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":162.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":162.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this was just utilizing like the salesforce fields, so that kind of goes even into the question that we had around the filters for extracting the list.","index":62,"end_time":170.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can, we can get anything in data box from Salesforce.","index":63,"end_time":175.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":170.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, if he wants a different metric, we could make that switch, no problem.","index":64,"end_time":179.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":180.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":66,"end_time":181.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then we do have the discussion around the deficit billing.","index":67,"end_time":185.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to hop into that now or do you want to get through the rest of the agenda and then come back?","index":68,"end_time":188.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can probably do that one pretty quick.","index":69,"end_time":191.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So just, I think you know me by now.","index":70,"end_time":194.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m pretty transparent.","index":71,"end_time":195.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So you know, we''re in a negative deficit and we don''t, we don''t like that over here.","index":72,"end_time":200.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, people should get paid.","index":73,"end_time":202.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, so what I want to do, just think about this.","index":74,"end_time":206.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Maybe for today and Monday we can figure out what to do for when I sent it over to you again.","index":75,"end_time":212.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Guillerm.","index":76,"end_time":213.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Pretty open about this stuff.","index":77,"end_time":214.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean we''re not saving lives here.","index":78,"end_time":216.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we had a certain amount of money for January, February, March.","index":79,"end_time":219.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s no longer true for January, but it is true from February onwards.","index":80,"end_time":225.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And what that means is I have a certain amount of money.","index":81,"end_time":228.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I know we haven''t talked about Q2, 3 and 4, but I have budget that has been passed for you guys.","index":82,"end_time":235.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so when I talked to Vivian, I showed her the negative and she''s like, okay, we don''t, we don''t.","index":83,"end_time":240.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That is not cool.","index":84,"end_time":241.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":85,"end_time":242.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And maybe we want a front end load given what we need to do with all this, like the contact mapping, etc.","index":86,"end_time":248.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like it.","index":87,"end_time":249.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s a lot and I, I think it''s more than what we had budgeted for, for Q1.","index":88,"end_time":254.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so.","index":89,"end_time":255.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, and obviously, I mean, because we.","index":90,"end_time":258.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Went down and I didn''t want to hold anything up.","index":91,"end_time":259.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, working with us, we like to get ahead of the game.","index":92,"end_time":261.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":262.839,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.519,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we also want to pay you.","index":94,"end_time":264.119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.839,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So think about what we need to do and what we would need to do to level that up.","index":95,"end_time":270.599,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.279,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And what I can do is we have a contract already for Q1.","index":96,"end_time":275.119,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.759,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can take from Q2, 3 and 4 and kind of move it backwards starting in February and then we''ll talk about Q2.","index":97,"end_time":282.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.119,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we thought at least for the first half of the year, I think Q1 especially.","index":98,"end_time":287.479,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.079,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But then Q2 with all the ABM testing and stuff, I mean, again, we haven''t talked about it yet, but maybe we dip down a little bit in Q3 but.","index":99,"end_time":295.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":287.559,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because we''ll be rolling by then, hopefully.","index":100,"end_time":298.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, I know we will be, but.","index":101,"end_time":300.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Think about definitely rolling.","index":102,"end_time":301.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll be in like maintenance mode at that point.","index":103,"end_time":303.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I thought.","index":104,"end_time":304.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I just said look.","index":105,"end_time":305.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then Q4 will want to ramp back up for the next year.","index":106,"end_time":308.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":305.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":107,"end_time":309.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And see what else we could have bought companies by then.","index":108,"end_time":313.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Who the heck knows?","index":109,"end_time":314.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, maybe think about it for today and let me know what you think and you can give me A quick call on Monday or text or whatever.","index":110,"end_time":321.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":314.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, just see what it take to level it up.","index":111,"end_time":324.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bump up Q2 or Q1, February and March, and then I''ll.","index":112,"end_time":330.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, and then I''ll pull it from Q3 and 4.","index":113,"end_time":334.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":114,"end_time":335.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":334.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":115,"end_time":336.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there any specific initiatives you had in mind besides what''s already been shared?","index":116,"end_time":339.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just the scoring.","index":117,"end_time":341.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I think that I haven''t shared it yet, but.","index":118,"end_time":344.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I''ve got all the HubSpot scoring implicit and explicit.","index":119,"end_time":348.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I think that for me, because we never did that at Avanti or rico, we just didn''t do it right.","index":120,"end_time":353.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I don''t know, life cycle stage, we did.","index":121,"end_time":357.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":354.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I don''t know what that''s going to take.","index":122,"end_time":358.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I, you know, I''ve got a full spreadsheet that we want to do a whole bunch of stuff, but I need to send it to you guys first after I talk to the team today, and then a reality check from you guys to say, okay, that looks great, however, but I think you need that first to understand what we''re going to.","index":123,"end_time":380.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"How much more we''re going to need.","index":124,"end_time":381.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":380.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think.","index":125,"end_time":381.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that would be great.","index":126,"end_time":383.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we typically.","index":127,"end_time":385.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So HubSpot has a native scoring mechanism.","index":128,"end_time":387.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We tend to build just a custom one because there are some limits to the native one.","index":129,"end_time":392.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just build it however we need.","index":130,"end_time":395.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one thing that I always want to be cognizant of is Lifecycle stage doesn''t move backwards.","index":131,"end_time":400.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So someone levels up.","index":132,"end_time":402.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we need to have like a.","index":133,"end_time":403.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s probably going to be a manual check in, like if the opportunity fell through or something.","index":134,"end_time":408.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":135,"end_time":409.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I will talk to them about that today because some of this, you know, again, I, I did try and look at some models in HubSpot and for instance, you know, inactivity minus 10.","index":136,"end_time":421,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":409.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, if they''re already at this stage, they don''t go backwards.","index":137,"end_time":424.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":138,"end_time":425.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But do we show that in Salesforce that look, they''ve been inactive for six months, you know, so they went what.","index":139,"end_time":432.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We could do there.","index":140,"end_time":432.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we could even automatically apply them to a list based on those parameters.","index":141,"end_time":437.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, like, maybe we have some sort of outreach effort to those that are, like, have gone a little cold.","index":142,"end_time":441.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":143,"end_time":443.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I love the way you think.","index":144,"end_time":444.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that''s, you know, talking to the BDR team.","index":145,"end_time":446.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We want, like, right now they kind of sit there with a catcher''s mitt.","index":146,"end_time":450.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gwen.","index":147,"end_time":450.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":148,"end_time":451.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know.","index":149,"end_time":451.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":150,"end_time":452.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s qualified.","index":151,"end_time":453.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, you know, what we''re trying to do is strengthen the mql, not Just say, here''s your mql.","index":152,"end_time":459.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Give them a call.","index":153,"end_time":460.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If they don''t call you back, then it''s lost.","index":154,"end_time":462.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Here''s the mql.","index":155,"end_time":463.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s what they''re interested in.","index":156,"end_time":464.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s how to contact them.","index":157,"end_time":465.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s what your next step is.","index":158,"end_time":466.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":159,"end_time":467.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But then we want to continue to nurture them.","index":160,"end_time":469.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":161,"end_time":469.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And add points to it and.","index":162,"end_time":471.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Or add on to their score over their lifecycle.","index":163,"end_time":475.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And anyway, you know the drill.","index":164,"end_time":476.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I think I need to talk to them first, send it over to you, give it a good think next week and then just say, look, in order to get this done, conceivably we''re going to need to pull X from the back half of the year and put it into Q1 and 2 and I''m happy to work with you then.","index":165,"end_time":493.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":166,"end_time":494.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s perfect.","index":167,"end_time":494.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":168,"end_time":496.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely do that.","index":169,"end_time":497.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":170,"end_time":498.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":497.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right then.","index":171,"end_time":498.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guia.","index":172,"end_time":499.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we''re good to move to the next slide then.","index":173,"end_time":500.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For sure.","index":174,"end_time":501.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Barb, I''d send an email about this.","index":175,"end_time":504.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that you''ve been swamped.","index":176,"end_time":505.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the filters that you had shared, I was trying to find the exact matches in Salesforce and they weren''t lining up directly.","index":177,"end_time":514.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like you had like.","index":178,"end_time":517.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, yeah.","index":179,"end_time":518.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":180,"end_time":518.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Y.","index":181,"end_time":519.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So like Rio wasn''t broken out as whims.","index":182,"end_time":521.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rio.","index":183,"end_time":522.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was just Rio.","index":184,"end_time":523.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to check on things like that.","index":185,"end_time":524.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then there was like.","index":186,"end_time":525.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I didn''t know what the utilities was referring to.","index":187,"end_time":528.079,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I couldn''t find anything for that.","index":188,"end_time":529.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.079,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, utilities is the segment.","index":189,"end_time":534.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":531.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we have storm water, wastewater, drinking.","index":190,"end_time":537.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Water, the pre existing segments that are in the contact.","index":191,"end_time":540.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, all right, cool.","index":192,"end_time":542.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like building a report and trying to find all these filters.","index":193,"end_time":544.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that makes a lot more sense.","index":194,"end_time":546.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sure.","index":195,"end_time":547.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And just get as close as you can.","index":196,"end_time":549.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like it should be wims Rio.","index":197,"end_time":550.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But eh, we''re a little loose around here with our branding.","index":198,"end_time":552.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Apparently that''s not even an option in the dropdown.","index":199,"end_time":555.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, there''s the brand.","index":200,"end_time":558.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can say like the brand is wims, but then there''s the inferred product interest and the direct product interest are also two different fields.","index":201,"end_time":565.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":566.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":203,"end_time":567.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So basically the categories are whims, Aquarius, and if we start with those we''re fine.","index":204,"end_time":572.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, but.","index":205,"end_time":574.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":206,"end_time":574.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you know we have a huge product list and most of those are sunset.","index":207,"end_time":578.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":208,"end_time":579.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we want to look at classic, but I don''t even know that they''re in there.","index":209,"end_time":582.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I have the list.","index":210,"end_time":584.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t remember classic being in there.","index":211,"end_time":585.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I''ll do is.","index":212,"end_time":587.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so I''ll build the.","index":213,"end_time":589.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll build what I can out of all of this and then send it over to you and maybe check with Kyle and just make sure that all the filters and everything we''re grabbing are correct.","index":214,"end_time":598.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":215,"end_time":599.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I do have the classic list, so I can upload that or I can send it to you guys to make sure it matches.","index":216,"end_time":604.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I have.","index":217,"end_time":605.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, if you could send it to us, that''d be great.","index":218,"end_time":607.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we just have.","index":219,"end_time":608.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we do the push into the system, everything is using the same data, custom fields, everything like that.","index":220,"end_time":613.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":221,"end_time":614.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":222,"end_time":615.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":614.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":223,"end_time":618.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, the next slide.","index":224,"end_time":619.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we have all these workflows set up, so contact owners and everything.","index":225,"end_time":626.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also added any contacts with marketers in demand would just be set as a subscriber.","index":226,"end_time":631.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when we test any forms, we don''t get put to MQL or anything.","index":227,"end_time":635.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":228,"end_time":636.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Forgot about you guys.","index":229,"end_time":637.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":636.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Cool.","index":230,"end_time":641.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''re all good there.","index":231,"end_time":642.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":232,"end_time":642.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":642.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":233,"end_time":645.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the ROI calculator, kind of similar.","index":234,"end_time":648.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think, I imagine this is going to go a lot faster than the RICO calculator.","index":235,"end_time":651.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I just wanted to ask if there was any like existing code that you would be able to provide and that we could just rebuild.","index":236,"end_time":658.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll get it from James.","index":237,"end_time":661.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":659.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That would be fantastic.","index":238,"end_time":662.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we can just get that put together.","index":239,"end_time":664.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, he built them, so I''ll get those for sure.","index":240,"end_time":668.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":241,"end_time":668.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then what was the other thing that we needed here?","index":242,"end_time":671.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so quick question.","index":243,"end_time":674.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":671.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Just um, Barb, do you have like a list of all the forms that were like custom built, like the health assessment, the ROI calculators and stuff like that or.","index":244,"end_time":686.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":674.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s just the 3da.","index":245,"end_time":689.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s the, the horrible hawk one.","index":246,"end_time":691.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hawk op one that I think is the major custom one.","index":247,"end_time":695.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then the ROI and the health assessment.","index":248,"end_time":697.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Now the health assessment, there''s two.","index":249,"end_time":699.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"One for Aquarius, one for Winds.","index":250,"end_time":701.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I guess there''s four.","index":251,"end_time":703.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":701.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, I can, I can get.","index":252,"end_time":706.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll talk to James soon.","index":253,"end_time":708.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The priority outside of building the database that the top priority is that HAWK one apparently.","index":254,"end_time":717.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":708.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I, yeah, I didn''t know this but they, they account for, depending on the day, 10 to 20% of our leads.","index":255,"end_time":724.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''m like, oh, that''s important.","index":256,"end_time":725.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So Vivian did mention that.","index":257,"end_time":727.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":728.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":728.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, did she?","index":260,"end_time":729.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":261,"end_time":729.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So she, when I talked to her yesterday, she''s, she''s pretty chill.","index":262,"end_time":732.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But she said I just, she goes, I''m so tired of hearing about that form.","index":263,"end_time":736.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Can we ask Colin to prioritize it.","index":264,"end_time":738.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":265,"end_time":738.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":266,"end_time":739.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the hot lead input form.","index":267,"end_time":742.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.97,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That one.","index":268,"end_time":743.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.77,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":269,"end_time":744.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":270,"end_time":744.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That one I already built, but I cannot show it to you because HubSpot is like with the billing problem.","index":271,"end_time":750.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":744.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So all forms isn''t.","index":272,"end_time":752.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.77,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I know I can''t do anything and I''m like, I have proof of payment weeks ago, but I like, I have to.","index":273,"end_time":760.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m going to spend most of my day trying to clear that up.","index":274,"end_time":763.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":275,"end_time":763.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Sorry that when I saw it, I''m.","index":276,"end_time":765.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, no, that''s not your fault.","index":277,"end_time":767.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just HubSpot being HubSpot.","index":278,"end_time":769.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately, we''re dead.","index":279,"end_time":771.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Beats.","index":280,"end_time":771.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, we''re not.","index":281,"end_time":772.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll.","index":282,"end_time":774.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I''ll get that cleared up.","index":283,"end_time":775.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Gay.","index":284,"end_time":775.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''ll send you a note right away.","index":285,"end_time":777.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":778.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And another question.","index":287,"end_time":779.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So all of these forms, like the ROI calculators, the health assessment, I couldn''t find them on your website.","index":288,"end_time":787.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.19,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I found them on, on WordPress.","index":289,"end_time":790.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.23,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Right, but you don''t have them.","index":290,"end_time":791.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Those were like isolated campaigns right there.","index":291,"end_time":795.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.96,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":292,"end_time":798.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It was my.","index":293,"end_time":800.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and so, you know, I, I''m not going to have all of the answers on those.","index":294,"end_time":805.599,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I came in to the company when they, they had launched it like the week before, and it was a mashup of Graziti, who was our Marketo folks, and James, who was our webmaster.","index":295,"end_time":818.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":805.599,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we ran the campaigns out of Marketo and then I asked James to embed it onto the website.","index":296,"end_time":824.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so I have no clue who has what, but I''ll ask James.","index":297,"end_time":830.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He will know and get you what you need.","index":298,"end_time":833.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And if he has more questions, I''ll just copy you and then just, you know, the way that James works, great guy.","index":299,"end_time":839.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He always copies Vivian because he is a contractor.","index":300,"end_time":842.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":301,"end_time":842.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''Re transparent about everything anyway.","index":302,"end_time":845.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":303,"end_time":846.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, he''s very transparent.","index":304,"end_time":848.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So yeah, for sure.","index":305,"end_time":849.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll, I''ll.","index":306,"end_time":850.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll work it out.","index":307,"end_time":851.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":308,"end_time":852.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":852.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":309,"end_time":853.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And just one more question about form Spar.","index":310,"end_time":856.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.81,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I guess I''ll.","index":311,"end_time":857.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":856.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I have to share my whole screen for this.","index":312,"end_time":860.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":857.69,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"One second because I, I finished building the.","index":313,"end_time":868.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"This one, the hacklit input form, but then I was building this one OTT lead input form and I know it''s the same one.","index":314,"end_time":880.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":869.86,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s the both is 2731.","index":315,"end_time":883.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Ah, got it, got it.","index":316,"end_time":886.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":885.3,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Because I noticed like this part of the form is different.","index":317,"end_time":889.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Like problems customer is experiencing is different on the other one.","index":318,"end_time":894.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":889.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I wanted to ask you, like.","index":319,"end_time":896.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":894.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Or which one do we use as like the main one?","index":320,"end_time":902.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.59,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Imagine that''ll probably be a question for James.","index":321,"end_time":905.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is.","index":322,"end_time":906.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s A question for James and also for Blake.","index":323,"end_time":908.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":324,"end_time":909.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So he''s our BDR to say how is this different?","index":325,"end_time":911.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''ll ask him today and get back to you.","index":326,"end_time":913.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.149,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t want to assume anything, but for me it was always weird that it was the same form, which is why I messed it up so badly in Marketo because I overrode the four form, thinking it was just hot.","index":327,"end_time":925.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I can''t get it back until Adobe calls me and it''s been weeks.","index":328,"end_time":931.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":329,"end_time":932.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Fascinating support system there.","index":330,"end_time":935.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s insane.","index":331,"end_time":938.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s Marketo, which just sucks anyways.","index":332,"end_time":941.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does, yeah.","index":333,"end_time":942.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll get you that answer as well.","index":334,"end_time":944.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":335,"end_time":945.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think the last one was just data box, which I think we already went through.","index":336,"end_time":950.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":337,"end_time":950.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''re all good then.","index":338,"end_time":952.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we covered everything in your email, right?","index":339,"end_time":955.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":340,"end_time":957.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thanks so much and thanks for everything.","index":341,"end_time":959,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":957.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re like incredibly impressed.","index":342,"end_time":962.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":959,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I. I think I mentioned this before, but, you know, it took two and a half months to get to a testing cutover stage and we knew we weren''t going to.","index":343,"end_time":971.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":962.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We were going to go to a phase 2.","index":344,"end_time":972.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The other opcos cbird is in month number 11 and I cannot fathom.","index":345,"end_time":981.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And they had an integration partner.","index":346,"end_time":983.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Don''t know who it is.","index":347,"end_time":984.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But then the other one who''s.","index":348,"end_time":987.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She''s so great.","index":349,"end_time":987.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She''s really on the struggle bus here.","index":350,"end_time":990.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, she''s.","index":351,"end_time":991.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":990.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I think she''s about six months in, no integration partner.","index":352,"end_time":994.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And she''s just dealing with, you know.","index":353,"end_time":998.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''Re available to help out anywhere.","index":354,"end_time":999.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know Vivian was talking to Hawk as well.","index":355,"end_time":1003.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has there been any updates there?","index":356,"end_time":1005,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I haven''t seen any updates.","index":357,"end_time":1007.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Probably not in the first half of January.","index":358,"end_time":1009.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think everybody''s digging out the holidays, but I''ll let you know.","index":359,"end_time":1013.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But she did send a very.","index":360,"end_time":1014.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She said you guys were 10 out of 10 and to call her for a reference and.","index":361,"end_time":1017.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, and then Dory as well.","index":362,"end_time":1019.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I.","index":363,"end_time":1020.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The other company, I said, look, like if you have a part, like if you need a partner, we have one.","index":364,"end_time":1025.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Please, please.","index":365,"end_time":1027.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The only thing Vivian asked Colin and I said it was no problem on your behalf was bandwidth.","index":366,"end_time":1032.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I said, well, that''s the beauty of, you know, Tristan''s business model is that it''s an accordion.","index":367,"end_time":1039.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":368,"end_time":1039.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.16,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I said they''ve never not had bandwidth.","index":369,"end_time":1043.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1044.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I mean, if we even hit a point where we needed to get extra staff, we would just do that anyway.","index":371,"end_time":1048.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":372,"end_time":1049.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I said, she goes, okay.","index":373,"end_time":1050.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just, if I''m giving out, handing out references I want to make sure that.","index":374,"end_time":1053.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we would handle it.","index":375,"end_time":1055.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1053.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem.","index":376,"end_time":1055.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I said.","index":377,"end_time":1056.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I said it''s never been an issue, and it won''t be, so.","index":378,"end_time":1059.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep.","index":379,"end_time":1059.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":380,"end_time":1059.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":381,"end_time":1060.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":382,"end_time":1060.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you so much, Barb.","index":383,"end_time":1062.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":384,"end_time":1062.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":385,"end_time":1063.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Talk to you soon.","index":386,"end_time":1064.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1063.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, yeah, and then I''ll reach out to you on Monday.","index":387,"end_time":1067.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":388,"end_time":1068.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":389,"end_time":1069.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1069.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Have a think about it when I send you the scoring, and we''ll.","index":391,"end_time":1071.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll go from there.","index":392,"end_time":1072.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":393,"end_time":1073.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":394,"end_time":1073.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you.","index":395,"end_time":1073.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take care, guys.","index":396,"end_time":1074.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Bye.","index":397,"end_time":1074.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"}],"dateString":"2026-01-09T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE098Y6D2JYDDHX5QJS08Z06","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Resolved data box filters and clarified segment definitions; Colin to finalize report structure.","Barb proposed reallocating Q2–Q4 budget to cover Q1 deficit and sustain contact mapping progress.","Colin confirmed HubSpot scoring will be custom and adaptable to lifecycle stage rules.","Barb emphasized prioritizing HAWK form fix, which drives up to 20% of leads.","ROI calculators and custom forms reviewed; Barb to coordinate asset delivery via James."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We''re like incredibly impressed.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"Maybe think about it for today and let me know what you think.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"We’re available to help out anywhere.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["budget","delivery","scoring","data","forms"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T18:29:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Budget Adjustment and Financial Planning**\n\nThe team recognized a **negative budget deficit for Q1**, prompting a plan to rebalance funds from later quarters to cover immediate needs (03:03).\n\n- **Brent Willans** highlighted the deficit, emphasizing the importance of paying the team fairly and proposing to shift budget from **Q2, Q3, and Q4** back into **February and March** to cover current shortfalls.\n- This adjustment accounts for increased workload, including **contact mapping** and **ABM testing**, which exceeded initial Q1 estimates.\n- The plan anticipates moving to a **maintenance mode by Q3**, allowing a potential dip in spending before ramping up again in Q4 for the next fiscal cycle.\n- Brent requested feedback by Monday on how much budget to reallocate, with the goal of smoothing payments while maintaining project momentum.\n\n## **Lead Scoring and Sales Process Enhancement**\n\nImproving lead qualification with a custom scoring model is a key priority to increase sales effectiveness and nurture prospects over time (05:40).\n\n- Brent shared a detailed spreadsheet incorporating **HubSpot''s implicit and explicit scoring data**, aiming to develop an advanced system beyond HubSpot’s native limits.\n- Colin Costigan stressed that **lifecycle stages should not move backwards**, requiring manual checks for deals that fall through to maintain score accuracy.\n- The team plans to automate lists for **inactive leads** and develop outreach strategies to re-engage them, improving sales pipeline quality.\n- Brent emphasized strengthening the MQL process by providing BDRs with actionable intelligence on leads’ interests and next steps, moving beyond simple lead assignment to ongoing nurturing.\n\n## **Data Integration and Reporting Clarifications**\n\nClarifying data definitions and system filters is essential to ensure accurate reporting and seamless integration with Salesforce (01:45).\n\n- Colin explained the effort to map Salesforce fields to the data box filters, revealing inconsistencies like missing segmentation for **\"classic\" products** and unclear categories such as **\"utilities\"**.\n- Brent clarified that major product categories include **Whims, Aquarius, and Rio**, with many legacy products sunsetted, requiring cleanup for accurate reporting.\n- The team agreed to share and upload the **classic product list** to align data fields before pushing updates into Salesforce.\n- Colin confirmed workflows are set so that **contacts tagged as marketers in demand** are categorized as subscribers to avoid inflating MQL counts during form testing.\n\n## **Form Development and Lead Capture Priorities**\n\nBuilding and prioritizing custom forms is critical to capturing quality leads, with one form representing up to **10–20% of daily lead volume** (11:00).\n\n- Brent identified the **Hawk lead input form** as the top priority due to its significant lead contribution, with Colin agreeing to prioritize its completion.\n- Guille Santana reported technical issues caused by a HubSpot billing problem blocking form access, which Brent is actively resolving.\n- The team plans to consolidate form ownership and clarify distinctions between similar forms, with Brent coordinating with James (webmaster) and Blake (BDR lead) for final decisions.\n- Brent confirmed that some forms were run as isolated campaigns embedded via Marketo and WordPress, and will gather necessary source files and code from James to streamline redevelopment.\n\n## **Client Satisfaction and Partnership Support**\n\nStrong client feedback and a flexible staffing model underpin the team’s commitment to reliable delivery and growth support (16:38).\n\n- Brent shared positive references from **Vivian**, rating the team **10 out of 10** and offering to provide testimonials.\n- Colin emphasized the availability of extra staffing through an **accordion business model**, ensuring no bandwidth issues even during busy periods.\n- The team is prepared to step in as an integration partner for other companies if needed, reinforcing their role as a trusted resource.\n- Brent reiterated transparency and open communication as core values facilitating smooth collaboration and client confidence.\n\n","outline":null,"keywords":["Data Box","Deficit Billing","HubSpot Scoring","Salesforce Filters","ROI Calculator","Hot Lead Input Form"],"overview":"- **Budget Reallocation:** Addressed Q1 budget deficit; plan to shift funds from Q2, Q3, Q4 to February and March.  \n- **Lead Scoring System:** Developing custom lead scoring model to enhance sales effectiveness; automation for inactive leads planned.  \n- **Data Integration Needs:** Focus on aligning Salesforce filters and mapping to ensure accurate reporting and avoid MQL inflation.  \n- **Form Prioritization:** Hawk lead input form prioritized to capture significant lead volume; addressing technical issues preventing access.  \n- **Client Satisfaction Metrics:** Positive client feedback; staffing model ensures support during busy periods, reinforcing trusted resource role.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nReview scoring model with team and send detailed spreadsheet to Colin and Guille for feedback by next week (05:34)\nProvide comprehensive classic product list for Salesforce filtering alignment (09:58)\nCoordinate with James to retrieve existing ROI calculator build code and share with Colin for redevelopment (10:59)\nClear HubSpot billing issues affecting form visibility and notify Guille once resolved (12:54)\nConfirm with James and Blake which “hot lead input” form version will be standardized and communicate decision to Guille (15:05)\nFollow-up with James regarding form hosting, campaign integration, and documentation (13:00)\nProvide updates or changes regarding deficit billing budget adjustments after internal discussion and communicate next steps to Colin by Monday (17:44)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nPrepare and share filtered Salesforce report draft incorporating Barb’s segmentation feedback and product list for review by Barb and Kyle (08:38)\nBuild workflows to separate test form contacts to subscriber status to maintain clean MQL data (10:14)\nBegin redevelopment of ROI calculator once code received from James (11:01)\nDiscuss with Barb feasibility and impacts of moving budget forward and adjusting billing cycles for Q1 and Q2 (03:09)\nFollow up with Barb Monday to finalize scoring model details and budget plan adjustments (17:44)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nDocument list of all custom forms and coordinate with Barb and James to clarify form versions and usage, especially for hot lead input forms (11:11)\nClarify with Barb the main form used out of versions with different question sets and ensure proper integration once billing issues resolve (14:06)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a364ada9-31f6-4753-a41a-81e88aec8c05","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
