    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28","Oid":"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07"}',
    '{"id":"01KE4R0W2XS0KC9G3W0ZNMME01","title":"iCorps + New North Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Management**\n\nMarketing efforts delivered strong engagement last month and set a focused agenda for January.\n\n- **81 marketing points were delivered in December**, including monthly management, the AI scorecard page, and launching the new ABM campaign (05:49)  \n    - January plans include **59 points focused on campaign monitoring and optimizations** to improve results  \n    - The ABM highly engaged lead list grew to **245 leads**, with new entries from LinkedIn paid ads and nurture campaigns  \n    - **Kristen followed up on a lead requesting a free IT checkup meeting on January 15**, suggesting a second outreach to increase conversion chances  \n    - The first LinkedIn submission for the AI readiness quiz was received; follow-up will include sending quiz results and offering a consultation  \n    - A positive LinkedIn organic outreach response came from an attorney interested in the AI tool comparison sheet, providing a work email for follow-up  \n    - December produced **47 MQLs with 6 converting to SQLs, yielding a 13% MQL-to-SQL conversion rate**  \n- **SEO progress includes approval and imminent publishing of three key pages**, thanks to Samuel Bagnall’s coordination with Jeff (09:28)  \n    - Additional pages pending include a blog post delayed for **approximately two months**, an AI-focused page on Microsoft Copilot, and two glossary definition pages  \n    - Samuel will verify the blog post status and confirm publishing to close pending items  \n    - Nathalie will consolidate and send campaign leads and notes to Ruby for Kristen’s follow-up  \n\n## **Website Content and Navigation Improvements**\n\nThe team identified gaps in website navigation and content integration for AI offerings that affect user experience and lead capture.\n\n- The **AI readiness assessment landing page is not easily accessible** from the main site, limiting visitor discovery and engagement (12:00)  \n    - Ruby noted that the “Development and AI” page lacks clear CTAs or links to the readiness assessment, causing confusion for visitors seeking AI services  \n    - Nathalie proposed adding a clickable block on the assessments page and inserting an explanatory text module with a CTA on the development page to guide users to the assessment  \n    - Ruby emphasized the need to unify AI content and assets on the website, ensuring easy access to related blogs, PDFs, and landing pages to support paid marketing efforts  \n    - Nathalie will compile an inventory of all campaign assets and map them for better internal understanding and site integration  \n- The **Copilot readiness page remains unpublished due to pending approval**, blocking full content rollout (14:48)  \n    - Ruby will revisit her edits to tighten the AI content flow and improve linkage between the Copilot page and other AI assets  \n    - The team agreed to prioritize finalizing and publishing all AI-related pages to align with marketing campaigns and enhance site usability  \n\n## **Executive Reporting and Dashboard Development**\n\nLeadership seeks streamlined, clear reporting formats to better track marketing progress, requiring tailored dashboards for different executives.\n\n- Ruby reported that **senior leaders Mike, Jeff, and CFO Chris Cook want more direct insight into marketing activities**, including the option to join meetings periodically for process transparency (19:40)  \n    - They seek an easy-to-understand, at-a-glance reporting format summarizing key metrics such as leads, campaign progress, and keyword performance  \n    - Ruby highlighted that current dashboards, like Pulse, are too detailed and not executive-friendly, especially for Chris Cook who prefers minimalistic bullet summaries  \n    - Nathalie recommended scheduling a session with leadership to identify their exact key metrics needs and build a **real-time executive dashboard tailored for quick insights** (24:20)  \n- Colin Costigan agreed to build **two dashboards: one detailed for Jeff covering keyword tracking, tools (Ahrefs, Semrush), and overall marketing health, and a simpler one for Chris focused on cost metrics, ROI, MQL-to-SQL conversion, and site metrics** (26:55)  \n    - The plan includes integrating keyword tools into Data Box to present AI citation and ranking data clearly  \n    - This approach aims to satisfy varying leadership expectations while improving transparency and decision-making support  \n\n## **Process Coordination and Follow-up Actions**\n\nClear communication and task ownership were established to maintain momentum on key deliverables.\n\n- Nathalie will resend the delayed blog post to Samuel for final confirmation and track publishing status (10:15)  \n- Ruby will coordinate follow-ups with Kristen on high-priority leads, including the IT checkup request and AI readiness quiz submissions (06:00)  \n- Nathalie and Ruby will work together to update website navigation and content blocks related to AI readiness and Copilot materials (12:59)  \n- Colin and Ruby will lead dashboard design and metric selection sessions with leadership to finalize executive reporting formats (27:00)  \n- The team agreed to invite Mike and Jeff to join meetings biweekly, allowing them to observe marketing discussions and better understand decision criteria (20:40)  \n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**\n\nThe meeting reinforced the importance of aligning digital assets and reporting with broader business goals in AI and marketing.\n\n- The decision to publish AI-related content, including readiness assessments and Copilot pages, supports positioning the company as a leader in AI services (09:29)  \n- Enhancing the website’s navigation and content integration reflects a strategy to **convert paid campaign interest into measurable leads by improving user experience** (13:00)  \n- Leadership’s desire for tailored dashboards underscores the need to balance detailed marketing data with concise executive summaries to drive informed decisions and resource allocation (24:10)  \n- The use of industry-standard tools like Ahrefs and Semrush for keyword and SEO tracking signals a commitment to competitive monitoring and continuous improvement (27:30)  \n- Ruby’s insight about leadership’s limited familiarity with paid marketing history shapes the approach to education and reporting, ensuring clarity on campaign impacts and ROI (25:00)","outline":null,"keywords":["AI readiness assessment","account-based marketing (ABM)","lead nurturing","SEO content","executive dashboards","marketing metrics"],"overview":"- **Marketing Engagement:** December saw **81 points delivered**, with plans for **59 points** focused on campaign optimizations in January.  \n- **Lead Growth:** ABM campaign generated **245 leads**, with new entries from LinkedIn ads and nurture campaigns.  \n- **SEO Updates:** Three key pages approved for publishing; additional content pending to enhance visibility and user access.  \n- **Website Navigation Issues:** AI readiness assessment page is hard to find; improvements to content flow and CTAs are needed.  \n- **Executive Dashboard Needs:** Leadership requires clear, concise reporting; tailored dashboards to be developed for different executives.  \n- **Strategic Alignment:** Publishing AI content positions the company as an AI leader; focus on user experience to convert interest into leads.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend Samuel the blog post and relevant pending content to confirm publication status (10:19)\nCompile and send Ruby the two specific leads and notes for follow-up with Kristen (11:01)\nAdd clickable blocks and text modules on the website’s Development and AI page to promote AI readiness assessment and related assets (13:09)\nCreate a list and mapping of all AI campaign assets and landing pages to ensure proper website integration and navigation (18:14)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nReach out again to the nurture campaign lead who requested the free IT checkup meeting for follow-up (06:11)\nCoordinate with Kristen to follow up with the AI quiz lead and send quiz results in PDF format (06:58)\nReview and provide feedback on website AI content and navigation; revisit prior edits and ensure Copilot page approvals progress (12:59)\nFacilitate invitation for clients Mike and Jeff to join bi-weekly meetings for enhanced visibility (20:50)\nWork with Nathalie and Colin on designing executive dashboards tailored for client leadership needs (24:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nLead the development of two distinct marketing dashboards – one comprehensive (for Jeff) and one simplified (for CFO Chris Cook) – incorporating key metrics such as cost per lead and MQL to SQL conversion (24:50)\nIntegrate keyword tracking tools like Ahrefs and Semrush into new dashboards for executive monitoring (27:20)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nConfirm blog post publication status with Nathalie and continue monitoring content approvals (10:33)\nSupport dashboard requirements by clarifying content publishing progress and SEO strategy as necessary (09:34)\n"},"duration":28.260000228881836,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"id":2,"name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":8.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.76,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":11.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.56,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Sorry everybody.","index":2,"end_time":13.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.12,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How''s everyone doing?","index":3,"end_time":14.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.48,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":15.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How is.","index":5,"end_time":16.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How was your holiday season?","index":6,"end_time":18.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It was good.","index":7,"end_time":20.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.24,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It was really busy.","index":8,"end_time":22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.92,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It was good.","index":9,"end_time":23.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How about yours?","index":10,"end_time":24.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I know you were off, right?","index":11,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.04,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, I was.","index":12,"end_time":26.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":26.09,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It was also busy.","index":13,"end_time":28.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, it wasn''t much of a break.","index":14,"end_time":30.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I had family here, so it''s always busy to host people and try to entertain them.","index":15,"end_time":37.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But it was a good break.","index":16,"end_time":38.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.21,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":17,"end_time":39.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.97,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Colin, I haven''t seen you in a while.","index":18,"end_time":41.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.77,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hope you''re doing well.","index":19,"end_time":41.929,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":41.13,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":42.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":42.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good to see you, Sam.","index":21,"end_time":43.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":42.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":45.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.97,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Sorry I missed your email when you were trying to send me a thing.","index":23,"end_time":48.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.33,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I. I was on vacation, so I was like, no worries.","index":24,"end_time":51.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.93,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"You shouldn''t be checking your email on vacation anyway.","index":25,"end_time":53.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":51.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, because I can''t with.","index":26,"end_time":56.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.85,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I corps when you.","index":27,"end_time":57.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.93,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I was in Mexico, so when you leave you can''t open your email.","index":28,"end_time":60.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.61,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"So I saw it.","index":29,"end_time":61.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.49,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I couldn''t respond though.","index":30,"end_time":62.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.33,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, I missed it.","index":31,"end_time":63.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.61,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But it''s all right.","index":32,"end_time":64.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.49,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Thank you for thinking of me.","index":33,"end_time":65.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.13,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":34,"end_time":66.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":65.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, did your family go back home?","index":35,"end_time":91.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.06,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, my mom has left.","index":36,"end_time":94.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.699,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"My older sister''s still here.","index":37,"end_time":96.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She''s got one more week of vacation.","index":38,"end_time":99.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96.86,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":100.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Were they working while they were there?","index":40,"end_time":102.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.02,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Were they just purely on like vacation?","index":41,"end_time":104.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.38,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Purely on vacation.","index":42,"end_time":106.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they both work in like education so they get like full winter breaks and summer breaks off.","index":43,"end_time":113.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":106.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":44,"end_time":114.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.03,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":115.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"My mom had like three weeks.","index":46,"end_time":118.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":116.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"My sister has like almost a month.","index":47,"end_time":120.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":118.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, Nice paid too.","index":48,"end_time":123.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know, can''t be bad.","index":49,"end_time":126.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124.83,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":127.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Also I was wondering if they were like working remote or something like that.","index":51,"end_time":131.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.31,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That could be kind of hard.","index":52,"end_time":132.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.99,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"But they could just fully like enjoy their.","index":53,"end_time":134.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.87,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Their trip.","index":54,"end_time":135.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.17,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":55,"end_time":136.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.65,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":137.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":137.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.25,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Hey guys.","index":58,"end_time":159.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":59,"end_time":160.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.97,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Hey.","index":60,"end_time":161.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":161.47,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Hey, Ruby.","index":61,"end_time":162.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How''s everybody doing?","index":62,"end_time":165.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good.","index":63,"end_time":167.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''m doing good.","index":64,"end_time":169.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.91,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How are you guys?","index":65,"end_time":170.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good.","index":66,"end_time":171.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.47,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Oh, hey, Colin.","index":67,"end_time":172.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Good to see you.","index":68,"end_time":173.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.63,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, you too.","index":69,"end_time":174.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How was your holiday season, Ruby?","index":70,"end_time":179.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know if relaxing is the word, but it was good.","index":71,"end_time":187.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It was good.","index":72,"end_time":188.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Nice time.","index":73,"end_time":189.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Everything that needed to happen happened and everybody had fun.","index":74,"end_time":193.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I''ll call it.","index":75,"end_time":194.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s a win.","index":76,"end_time":195.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"There you go.","index":77,"end_time":196.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":195.76,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Good.","index":78,"end_time":197.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Are your kids back in school now?","index":79,"end_time":200.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They were for a minute and now it''s a snow day, so for an ice day I should say.","index":80,"end_time":209.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But it is actually now snowing like big massive flakes.","index":81,"end_time":212.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So how about you guys?","index":82,"end_time":218.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Come on.","index":83,"end_time":219.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You got kiddos, right?","index":84,"end_time":220.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.29,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Are they school?","index":85,"end_time":220.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.29,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I do, I do.","index":86,"end_time":221.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a daughter.","index":87,"end_time":222.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":221.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She will be.","index":88,"end_time":223.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":222.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She turns one this month.","index":89,"end_time":225.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":223.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":90,"end_time":226.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":227.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":226.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So no smoothies from her every day.","index":92,"end_time":230.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.33,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":93,"end_time":231.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":232.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":231.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Me and my wife were joking about that last night.","index":95,"end_time":233.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, to be Marley.","index":96,"end_time":235.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":233.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s her name.","index":97,"end_time":236.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":235.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Living rent free and no schedule for the day.","index":98,"end_time":240.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":237.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds pretty nice.","index":99,"end_time":241.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.29,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":100,"end_time":242.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Oh, I like that name.","index":101,"end_time":243.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Marley.","index":102,"end_time":243.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s cute.","index":103,"end_time":244.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":104,"end_time":245.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.36,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":105,"end_time":246.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"How about you, Natalie?","index":106,"end_time":248.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.76,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How was your holiday and all that?","index":107,"end_time":253.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.72,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It was good.","index":108,"end_time":254.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I was just telling Sam my family came to visit, so that was fun.","index":109,"end_time":259.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I had to find a lot of things to entertain them in the city while it''s cold at the same time, which was challenging, but it was, it was good to see them.","index":110,"end_time":268.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":268.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Good.","index":112,"end_time":269.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, so let''s take a quick look at your points.","index":113,"end_time":278.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So just looking back on last month, we had 81 points delivered.","index":114,"end_time":283.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we had all of your monthly management tasks as well as the AI scorecard page, as well as setting up and launching the new ABM campaign.","index":115,"end_time":293.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.61,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then in January, we have 59 points working this month, all of the management tasks.","index":116,"end_time":300.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So really just monitoring the campaigns that we have running this month, seeing what optimizations we need to do.","index":117,"end_time":306.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":118,"end_time":311.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.83,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at abm.","index":119,"end_time":313.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So for the highly engaged lead list, just an update from our last meeting.","index":120,"end_time":318.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ve increased the number of leads to 245 in that list.","index":121,"end_time":323.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I did take a look at some of the ones that were coming from the LinkedIn paid ads.","index":122,"end_time":330.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So a lot of them are coming from the construction IT budget guide.","index":123,"end_time":334.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we did get a couple come in.","index":124,"end_time":337.669,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.75,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This was the one that came in from the nurture campaign that we have running.","index":125,"end_time":344.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.23,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the one that Kristen already followed up with on the 15th, but it might be worth following up with them again because this is the one that asked for the free IT checkup meeting.","index":126,"end_time":359.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So actually requesting like getting on a meeting and having that more consultation versus downloading the PDF.","index":127,"end_time":368.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":360.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this might be one that''s worth reaching out to one more time.","index":128,"end_time":371.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, good call.","index":129,"end_time":372.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll ping her, ping her on this one.","index":130,"end_time":376.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":372.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":131,"end_time":379.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":376.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we also had the first submission for the AI readiness quiz from LinkedIn.","index":132,"end_time":385.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this person filled out the multiple choice questions that we have on the LinkedIn form.","index":133,"end_time":394.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So they gave us this information.","index":134,"end_time":396.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"These are basically the same questions that are on the AI readiness quiz landing page and at the end they receive their readiness assessment.","index":135,"end_time":406.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So Kristin could follow up with this one one more time as well and send over their results pretty much.","index":136,"end_time":413.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then see if they''d like to meet to see how I could help get that set up.","index":137,"end_time":418.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, now for this one for results.","index":138,"end_time":421.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Remind me again, is this like, this is a thing that we need to like put together like a design for and like pop the stuff in?","index":139,"end_time":432.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":140,"end_time":434.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we could create it into a PDF.","index":141,"end_time":437.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":142,"end_time":438.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I just couldn''t remember if we had.","index":143,"end_time":440.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":439.17,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If we had like a, a template for it or if, or if we could take like, how does it show up on the.","index":144,"end_time":447.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Maybe we could just take like how it looks on the website.","index":145,"end_time":449.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was thinking.","index":146,"end_time":452.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, we just have that boiler take boilerplate text that''s on the website.","index":147,"end_time":457.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Once they finish the quiz, it gives them their result immediately.","index":148,"end_time":460.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But for LinkedIn, when they submit that multiple choice form, it just says, thank you.","index":149,"end_time":465.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll follow up shortly with your results to email them with that same text essentially thing.","index":150,"end_time":472.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, All right, cool.","index":151,"end_time":479.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.54,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Work on that.","index":152,"end_time":482.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":481.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":153,"end_time":485.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":484.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":154,"end_time":488.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then for the LinkedIn organic outreach, I think I sent a note about this yesterday.","index":155,"end_time":495.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We did get one positive response from an attorney to Kristin''s LinkedIn and she.","index":156,"end_time":501.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"She''s interested in the AI tool comparison sheet and provided her work email to send that over.","index":157,"end_time":507.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":158,"end_time":512.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sorry, which one was that?","index":159,"end_time":516.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":513.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":160,"end_time":516.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"For LinkedIn organic messages on Kristin''s account.","index":161,"end_time":524.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":526.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So she did get a response on LinkedIn.","index":163,"end_time":530.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":531.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Okay.","index":165,"end_time":532.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.79,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":532.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.23,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And this is the contact''s name.","index":167,"end_time":533.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":168,"end_time":536.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then just looking back on our results for December.","index":169,"end_time":545.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we had 47 MQLs come in and six of those turned to SQLs.","index":170,"end_time":552.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we had almost 13% MQL to SQL conversion rate.","index":171,"end_time":556.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then looking at SEO.","index":172,"end_time":564.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So thank you, Sam, for getting these, these three pages approved.","index":173,"end_time":568.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I saw that email from Jeff.","index":174,"end_time":569.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So our team is going to get all three of these published today.","index":175,"end_time":573.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":176,"end_time":575.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.48,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":177,"end_time":576.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":575.52,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":178,"end_time":577.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then other ones that we''re just waiting on are this blog post, this new blog post, and then these other pages as well.","index":179,"end_time":587.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This one is the, the AI page we started off with initially where we were just talking about Microsoft Copilot.","index":180,"end_time":596.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We decided we''re not using that one for abm, but we still wanted to publish it just so that we''re making sure that we''re covering this keyword.","index":181,"end_time":604.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.19,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then we also have these two glossary definition pages.","index":182,"end_time":607.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the blog post.","index":183,"end_time":611.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.07,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"When was that finished?","index":184,"end_time":613.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Is that.","index":185,"end_time":613.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.42,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"How long has that been waiting for?","index":186,"end_time":615.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.18,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I guess, sort of my question.","index":187,"end_time":617.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.74,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I''m not sure, but I can, I can resend it to you after this meeting.","index":188,"end_time":623.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":189,"end_time":625.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":624.5,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I said no, it''s been like months.","index":190,"end_time":626.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.14,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Or is it just because I''m.","index":191,"end_time":628.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.58,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Was it like last month?","index":192,"end_time":630.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.54,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":193,"end_time":631.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.06,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"I mean, you can just send it and I''ll.","index":194,"end_time":633.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.58,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s been a couple of months.","index":195,"end_time":635.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":196,"end_time":636.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.02,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text