k like, a quarter, a business quarter to get that done.","index":307,"end_time":1147.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And his final thoughts were, these are fine.","index":308,"end_time":1151.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, he said these are fined.","index":309,"end_time":1154.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.23,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":310,"end_time":1162.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.15,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Well, that all sounds good to me.","index":311,"end_time":1164.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1162.71,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then, let''s see.","index":312,"end_time":1167.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1164.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I do have some, like, stuff I wanted to bring back to you guys that I got from.","index":313,"end_time":1171.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1167.19,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"From Mike and from Jeff and meeting with them, like, you know, over the last couple of weeks, they''re kind of wanting, like, a.","index":314,"end_time":1184.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.27,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"They want to, like, hop in on these meetings with us every once in a while, which I think would be great, just so that they can get an eye in more on what our weekly process is like, because they have a lot of questions about, you know, how we''re doing on stuff or, like, how we''re looking at the progress and, you know, what the what.","index":315,"end_time":1205.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.66,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How do we make decisions based on what the data is telling us?","index":316,"end_time":1209.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.88,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And when I explain to them that we meet like this and that you guys.","index":317,"end_time":1213.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.6,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We look at the data and we.","index":318,"end_time":1215.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1214.04,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You guys talk about ideas and then we talk like, that doesn''t really totally land for them.","index":319,"end_time":1220.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":320,"end_time":1221.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.64,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Where I''m like, yeah, like, we talk about it.","index":321,"end_time":1223.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.559,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We have all these meetings, and I save all the decks, and, like, we''ve got it all.","index":322,"end_time":1226.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1223.08,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But I think for them, they''re wanting, like, I don''t know.","index":323,"end_time":1233.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1226.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think one is they just want to be able to hop in on these meetings.","index":324,"end_time":1237.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.29,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I''d say, like, I think we said that I would invite.","index":325,"end_time":1241.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1237.65,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I could Invite them like every two weeks or something, bi weekly or so.","index":326,"end_time":1251.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.77,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":327,"end_time":1252.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.85,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then if they want to hop on, they can.","index":328,"end_time":1254.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"If they don''t, that''s fine.","index":329,"end_time":1256.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1254.69,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So they can kind of see our process a little more, because I. I think that would help.","index":330,"end_time":1262.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1258.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then beyond that, they are looking for more of, like, a easy, quick check in, of being able to, at a glance, see where things are at in terms of, like, reporting or progress or what''s working, what''s not working.","index":331,"end_time":1283.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1262.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I know we have.","index":332,"end_time":1286.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1285.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I explained to them we have Pulse and that, you know, we.","index":333,"end_time":1290.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1286.68,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We have these meetings.","index":334,"end_time":1291.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We''re constantly looking at progress.","index":335,"end_time":1293,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"You guys are constantly looking at it.","index":336,"end_time":1294.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1293,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"We are, but I don''t think it''s really in a format that, like, is executive enough for them to.","index":337,"end_time":1303.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1294.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s not really accessible for them, I think for me to just say, like, oh, here''s the link to Pulse, or if I were to even send them, like, Screenshots from Pulse or something like that, like on a Cadence or.","index":338,"end_time":1318.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1303.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Or something.","index":339,"end_time":1319.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.52,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But so I just kind of wanted to bring that to you guys and see what your ideas are or if you''ve ever had any other clients have similar issues like this where, you know, executive leadership is looking for a little bit more of an eye into stuff and a quick little, you know, know, at a glance thing, like, what that would look like.","index":340,"end_time":1339.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then that''s like, they also want, like, you know, the list of keywords that we did and like, how we.","index":341,"end_time":1352.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.89,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"How we know what keywords are working and what ones aren''t and how the ranking works.","index":342,"end_time":1357.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And like, that.","index":343,"end_time":1358.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1357.57,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''s a lot on, like, what Jeff was asking about is like the.","index":344,"end_time":1361.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.37,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And some of that obviously is more like the nitty gritty.","index":345,"end_time":1364.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, he wants to see it.","index":346,"end_time":1365.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.01,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"But when me telling him, like, yes, we monitor keywords.","index":347,"end_time":1372.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.73,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yes, we have a keyword sheet.","index":348,"end_time":1373.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1372.06,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yes, like, all these things are happening.","index":349,"end_time":1375.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.78,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, it''s not.","index":350,"end_time":1377.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.18,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I don''t know how to make it more concrete for him.","index":351,"end_time":1383.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.42,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then on the super simple side, but the most important side is our cfo Chris Cook, wanting, like, super bare bones, just like bullets, basically.","index":352,"end_time":1403.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like, he doesn''t like a lot of.","index":353,"end_time":1405.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1403.43,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He doesn''t like slides.","index":354,"end_time":1406.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1405.59,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He doesn''t like a lot of words.","index":355,"end_time":1408.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.75,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He doesn''t like a lot of.","index":356,"end_time":1409.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like a lot.","index":357,"end_time":1410.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.03,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"He likes a very, very little bit.","index":358,"end_time":1412.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.99,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That tells him a lot.","index":359,"end_time":1413.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.51,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So I got what I''d like your help with is figuring out what I could provide to him that shows the key pieces.","index":360,"end_time":1426.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.35,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And for him, it''s.","index":361,"end_time":1427.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1426.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I think for all of them, if we just identify like the priority and we do this in this call.","index":362,"end_time":1439.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Right.","index":363,"end_time":1439.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.24,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s like, okay, how many leads, how many things moved, like, what happened?","index":364,"end_time":1443.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1439.44,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And so I think the answer is probably in a lot of these.","index":365,"end_time":1449.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.96,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s.","index":366,"end_time":1450.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It''s somewhere in the format of how this deck, how these meetings go.","index":367,"end_time":1454.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1450.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"It''s just figuring out how to package that in a way that''s accessible for leadership.","index":368,"end_time":1459.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.47,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":369,"end_time":1461.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think because even the reporting dashboard that we have for you, it''s got like six or seven slides with like so much information.","index":370,"end_time":1470.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1461.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think that also probably overwhelming.","index":371,"end_time":1473.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So maybe what we could do is schedule a time to sit down with them and understand what are the key metrics that they want to look at, like, at a glance.","index":372,"end_time":1480.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1473.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So like, what they think about how well marketing is doing, what are the key metrics they want to see.","index":373,"end_time":1486.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1482.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And we can build all of that into just one executive dashboard for them that updates in real time that they can look at.","index":374,"end_time":1492.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, that could be good.","index":375,"end_time":1496.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.07,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"My guess is it''s leads, How the ads are doing, how the emails are doing, and overall, like site health and keyword ranking stuff.","index":376,"end_time":1519.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.38,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And I think it''s also going to be important for them to understand that there''s.","index":377,"end_time":1525.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.86,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Because historically, up until recently or I guess the past couple of years, we never did paid.","index":378,"end_time":1533.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So for them, they''re.","index":379,"end_time":1535.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.56,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"The history of what they''re used to seeing and understanding from marketing is all like organic.","index":380,"end_time":1544.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.2,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"So that usually is like, okay, Google, Google search console.","index":381,"end_time":1553.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1548.84,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like I would usually give them like our impressions and clicks for the month or you know, just the Google Analytics.","index":382,"end_time":1561.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1553.16,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Google Analytics, like web traffic report or how many clicks, how many this, how many that.","index":383,"end_time":1567.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1562.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And again, that''s organic, but it does give you the granular level of like how we''re doing in paid.","index":384,"end_time":1572.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1568.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"And then we also did, I know, touch on recently wanting to build.","index":385,"end_time":1579.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1575,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Like.","index":386,"end_time":1583.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1583.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The AI and like ChatGPT or Copilot or any of these other LLMs and like how we''re performing when it comes to AI search.","index":387,"end_time":1593.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1583.28,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I think that''s something that they want to make sure we keep looking at too.","index":388,"end_time":1598.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1594.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":389,"end_time":1599.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1598.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we''ll do, Ruby, is we''ll put together two dashboards because it sounds like for Jeff, we have a lot of information that we want to be able to show in a dashboard.","index":390,"end_time":1609.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1599.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then maybe it''s a little bit different for Cook.","index":391,"end_time":1610.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1609.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine it''s going to be a lot more around like cost metrics, like cost per lead return on investment site metrics, MQL to SQL metrics.","index":392,"end_time":1618.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1610.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll build some preliminary metrics into a dashboard and then show up to that call and say, like, you know, here''s what we put together.","index":393,"end_time":1625.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1619.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can build anything you need.","index":394,"end_time":1626.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1625.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anything different that you need from this?","index":395,"end_time":1629.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1626.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can even have, like, a resources list, so they can easily go there and say, like, boom, here''s like, our keyword list.","index":396,"end_time":1634.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then if we integrate directly with AHREFS into Data Box, then we can show those AI citations and things like that.","index":397,"end_time":1640.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1635.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":398,"end_time":1641.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1640.67,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":399,"end_time":1642.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1641.55,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"That''d be great, because I know Jeff is super interested in, like, what tools we''re using for keywords, so AHREFS is the thing, and.","index":400,"end_time":1651.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.83,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we use Ahrefs and Semrush.","index":401,"end_time":1655.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1652.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds like a great plan.","index":402,"end_time":1658.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1657.31,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":403,"end_time":1660.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1659.36,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":404,"end_time":1661.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1660.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, Sam, I saw you like my message, but, Natalie, that blog was posted, so we''re all good.","index":405,"end_time":1666.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1661.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":406,"end_time":1666.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1666.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1667.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.8,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"Sorry for not letting you know.","index":408,"end_time":1669.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.24,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"},{"text":"No worries.","index":409,"end_time":1670.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":410,"end_time":1673.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1673.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":411,"end_time":1675.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.92,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Sounds like we got some good takeaways and some good action items, and we''ll get going on them.","index":412,"end_time":1681.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":413,"end_time":1682.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.32,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"All right, Happy New Year.","index":414,"end_time":1684.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.12,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":415,"end_time":1685.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.8,"speaker_name":"Ruby Pontbriand"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":416,"end_time":1686.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1685.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to see you guys again.","index":417,"end_time":1687.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1686.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":418,"end_time":1687.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.45,"speaker_name":"Samuel Bagnall"}],"dateString":"2026-01-07T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"rpontbriand@icorps.com","meeting_link":"https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_NWVjNDBkODktN2I3OS00ZWQ0LTgzMDEtMWNkNDk5OGVlYjQ2@thread.v2/0?context={\"Tid\":\"0188564a-93de-489c-bf54-1927d4a9ed28\",\"Oid\":\"bdae9fd3-d481-4c5e-aeea-7272e37b7d07\"}","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,rpontbriand@icorps.com,sbagnall@icorps.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","sbagnall@icorps.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE4R0W2XS0KC9G3W0ZNMME01","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Delivered 81 points in December including AI scorecard page and ABM campaign launch.","Generated 47 MQLs in December with a 13% MQL to SQL conversion rate.","Agreed to follow up on high-intent leads from nurture and LinkedIn campaigns.","Team will map AI campaign assets and improve website visibility for new landing pages.","Leadership dashboard planned to improve visibility into lead performance and keyword strategy."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We had 81 points delivered...as well as setting up and launching the new ABM campaign.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"We had 47 MQLs come in and six of those turned to SQLs.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"We’ll build some preliminary metrics into a dashboard and then show up to that call...","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["delivery","lead-gen","reporting","visibility","website","exec"],"model":"gpt-4-vision-2024-06","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Management**\n\nMarketing efforts delivered strong engagement last month and set a focused agenda for January.\n\n- **81 marketing points were delivered in December**, including monthly management, the AI scorecard page, and launching the new ABM campaign (05:49)  \n    - January plans include **59 points focused on campaign monitoring and optimizations** to improve results  \n    - The ABM highly engaged lead list grew to **245 leads**, with new entries from LinkedIn paid ads and nurture campaigns  \n    - **Kristen followed up on a lead requesting a free IT checkup meeting on January 15**, suggesting a second outreach to increase conversion chances  \n    - The first LinkedIn submission for the AI readiness quiz was received; follow-up will include sending quiz results and offering a consultation  \n    - A positive LinkedIn organic outreach response came from an attorney interested in the AI tool comparison sheet, providing a work email for follow-up  \n    - December produced **47 MQLs with 6 converting to SQLs, yielding a 13% MQL-to-SQL conversion rate**  \n- **SEO progress includes approval and imminent publishing of three key pages**, thanks to Samuel Bagnall’s coordination with Jeff (09:28)  \n    - Additional pages pending include a blog post delayed for **approximately two months**, an AI-focused page on Microsoft Copilot, and two glossary definition pages  \n    - Samuel will verify the blog post status and confirm publishing to close pending items  \n    - Nathalie will consolidate and send campaign leads and notes to Ruby for Kristen’s follow-up  \n\n## **Website Content and Navigation Improvements**\n\nThe team identified gaps in website navigation and content integration for AI offerings that affect user experience and lead capture.\n\n- The **AI readiness assessment landing page is not easily accessible** from the main site, limiting visitor discovery and engagement (12:00)  \n    - Ruby noted that the “Development and AI” page lacks clear CTAs or links to the readiness assessment, causing confusion for visitors seeking AI services  \n    - Nathalie proposed adding a clickable block on the assessments page and inserting an explanatory text module with a CTA on the development page to guide users to the assessment  \n    - Ruby emphasized the need to unify AI content and assets on the website, ensuring easy access to related blogs, PDFs, and landing pages to support paid marketing efforts  \n    - Nathalie will compile an inventory of all campaign assets and map them for better internal understanding and site integration  \n- The **Copilot readiness page remains unpublished due to pending approval**, blocking full content rollout (14:48)  \n    - Ruby will revisit her edits to tighten the AI content flow and improve linkage between the Copilot page and other AI assets  \n    - The team agreed to prioritize finalizing and publishing all AI-related pages to align with marketing campaigns and enhance site usability  \n\n## **Executive Reporting and Dashboard Development**\n\nLeadership seeks streamlined, clear reporting formats to better track marketing progress, requiring tailored dashboards for different executives.\n\n- Ruby reported that **senior leaders Mike, Jeff, and CFO Chris Cook want more direct insight into marketing activities**, including the option to join meetings periodically for process transparency (19:40)  \n    - They seek an easy-to-understand, at-a-glance reporting format summarizing key metrics such as leads, campaign progress, and keyword performance  \n    - Ruby highlighted that current dashboards, like Pulse, are too detailed and not executive-friendly, especially for Chris Cook who prefers minimalistic bullet summaries  \n    - Nathalie recommended scheduling a session with leadership to identify their exact key metrics needs and build a **real-time executive dashboard tailored for quick insights** (24:20)  \n- Colin Costigan agreed to build **two dashboards: one detailed for Jeff covering keyword tracking, tools (Ahrefs, Semrush), and overall marketing health, and a simpler one for Chris focused on cost metrics, ROI, MQL-to-SQL conversion, and site metrics** (26:55)  \n    - The plan includes integrating keyword tools into Data Box to present AI citation and ranking data clearly  \n    - This approach aims to satisfy varying leadership expectations while improving transparency and decision-making support  \n\n## **Process Coordination and Follow-up Actions**\n\nClear communication and task ownership were established to maintain momentum on key deliverables.\n\n- Nathalie will resend the delayed blog post to Samuel for final confirmation and track publishing status (10:15)  \n- Ruby will coordinate follow-ups with Kristen on high-priority leads, including the IT checkup request and AI readiness quiz submissions (06:00)  \n- Nathalie and Ruby will work together to update website navigation and content blocks related to AI readiness and Copilot materials (12:59)  \n- Colin and Ruby will lead dashboard design and metric selection sessions with leadership to finalize executive reporting formats (27:00)  \n- The team agreed to invite Mike and Jeff to join meetings biweekly, allowing them to observe marketing discussions and better understand decision criteria (20:40)  \n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**\n\nThe meeting reinforced the importance of aligning digital assets and reporting with broader business goals in AI and marketing.\n\n- The decision to publish AI-related content, including readiness assessments and Copilot pages, supports positioning the company as a leader in AI services (09:29)  \n- Enhancing the website’s navigation and content integration reflects a strategy to **convert paid campaign interest into measurable leads by improving user experience** (13:00)  \n- Leadership’s desire for tailored dashboards underscores the need to balance detailed marketing data with concise executive summaries to drive informed decisions and resource allocation (24:10)  \n- The use of industry-standard tools like Ahrefs and Semrush for keyword and SEO tracking signals a commitment to competitive monitoring and continuous improvement (27:30)  \n- Ruby’s insight about leadership’s limited familiarity with paid marketing history shapes the approach to education and reporting, ensuring clarity on campaign impacts and ROI (25:00)","outline":null,"keywords":["AI readiness assessment","account-based marketing (ABM)","lead nurturing","SEO content","executive dashboards","marketing metrics"],"overview":"- **Marketing Engagement:** December saw **81 points delivered**, with plans for **59 points** focused on campaign optimizations in January.  \n- **Lead Growth:** ABM campaign generated **245 leads**, with new entries from LinkedIn ads and nurture campaigns.  \n- **SEO Updates:** Three key pages approved for publishing; additional content pending to enhance visibility and user access.  \n- **Website Navigation Issues:** AI readiness assessment page is hard to find; improvements to content flow and CTAs are needed.  \n- **Executive Dashboard Needs:** Leadership requires clear, concise reporting; tailored dashboards to be developed for different executives.  \n- **Strategic Alignment:** Publishing AI content positions the company as an AI leader; focus on user experience to convert interest into leads.","action_items":"\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nSend Samuel the blog post and relevant pending content to confirm publication status (10:19)\nCompile and send Ruby the two specific leads and notes for follow-up with Kristen (11:01)\nAdd clickable blocks and text modules on the website’s Development and AI page to promote AI readiness assessment and related assets (13:09)\nCreate a list and mapping of all AI campaign assets and landing pages to ensure proper website integration and navigation (18:14)\n\n**Ruby Pontbriand**\nReach out again to the nurture campaign lead who requested the free IT checkup meeting for follow-up (06:11)\nCoordinate with Kristen to follow up with the AI quiz lead and send quiz results in PDF format (06:58)\nReview and provide feedback on website AI content and navigation; revisit prior edits and ensure Copilot page approvals progress (12:59)\nFacilitate invitation for clients Mike and Jeff to join bi-weekly meetings for enhanced visibility (20:50)\nWork with Nathalie and Colin on designing executive dashboards tailored for client leadership needs (24:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nLead the development of two distinct marketing dashboards – one comprehensive (for Jeff) and one simplified (for CFO Chris Cook) – incorporating key metrics such as cost per lead and MQL to SQL conversion (24:50)\nIntegrate keyword tracking tools like Ahrefs and Semrush into new dashboards for executive monitoring (27:20)\n\n**Samuel Bagnall**\nConfirm blog post publication status with Nathalie and continue monitoring content approvals (10:33)\nSupport dashboard requirements by clarifying content publishing progress and SEO strategy as necessary (09:34)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1746a3c5-04e9-4604-92e6-2994e83b69de","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
