INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: iCorps + New North Weekly',
  '## **Marketing Performance and Lead Management**

Marketing efforts delivered strong engagement last month and set a focused agenda for January.

- **81 marketing points were delivered in December**, including monthly management, the AI scorecard page, and launching the new ABM campaign (05:49)  
    - January plans include **59 points focused on campaign monitoring and optimizations** to improve results  
    - The ABM highly engaged lead list grew to **245 leads**, with new entries from LinkedIn paid ads and nurture campaigns  
    - **Kristen followed up on a lead requesting a free IT checkup meeting on January 15**, suggesting a second outreach to increase conversion chances  
    - The first LinkedIn submission for the AI readiness quiz was received; follow-up will include sending quiz results and offering a consultation  
    - A positive LinkedIn organic outreach response came from an attorney interested in the AI tool comparison sheet, providing a work email for follow-up  
    - December produced **47 MQLs with 6 converting to SQLs, yielding a 13% MQL-to-SQL conversion rate**  
- **SEO progress includes approval and imminent publishing of three key pages**, thanks to Samuel Bagnall’s coordination with Jeff (09:28)  
    - Additional pages pending include a blog post delayed for **approximately two months**, an AI-focused page on Microsoft Copilot, and two glossary definition pages  
    - Samuel will verify the blog post status and confirm publishing to close pending items  
    - Nathalie will consolidate and send campaign leads and notes to Ruby for Kristen’s follow-up  

## **Website Content and Navigation Improvements**

The team identified gaps in website navigation and content integration for AI offerings that affect user experience and lead capture.

- The **AI readiness assessment landing page is not easily accessible** from the main site, limiting visitor discovery and engagement (12:00)  
    - Ruby noted that the “Development and AI” page lacks clear CTAs or links to the readiness assessment, causing confusion for visitors seeking AI services  
    - Nathalie proposed adding a clickable block on the assessments page and inserting an explanatory text module with a CTA on the development page to guide users to the assessment  
    - Ruby emphasized the need to unify AI content and assets on the website, ensuring easy access to related blogs, PDFs, and landing pages to support paid marketing efforts  
    - Nathalie will compile an inventory of all campaign assets and map them for better internal understanding and site integration  
- The **Copilot readiness page remains unpublished due to pending approval**, blocking full content rollout (14:48)  
    - Ruby will revisit her edits to tighten the AI content flow and improve linkage between the Copilot page and other AI assets  
    - The team agreed to prioritize finalizing and publishing all AI-related pages to align with marketing campaigns and enhance site usability  

## **Executive Reporting and Dashboard Development**

Leadership seeks streamlined, clear reporting formats to better track marketing progress, requiring tailored dashboards for different executives.

- Ruby reported that **senior leaders Mike, Jeff, and CFO Chris Cook want more direct insight into marketing activities**, including the option to join meetings periodically for process transparency (19:40)  
    - They seek an easy-to-understand, at-a-glance reporting format summarizing key metrics such as leads, campaign progress, and keyword performance  
    - Ruby highlighted that current dashboards, like Pulse, are too detailed and not executive-friendly, especially for Chris Cook who prefers minimalistic bullet summaries  
    - Nathalie recommended scheduling a session with leadership to identify their exact key metrics needs and build a **real-time executive dashboard tailored for quick insights** (24:20)  
- Colin Costigan agreed to build **two dashboards: one detailed for Jeff covering keyword tracking, tools (Ahrefs, Semrush), and overall marketing health, and a simpler one for Chris focused on cost metrics, ROI, MQL-to-SQL conversion, and site metrics** (26:55)  
    - The plan includes integrating keyword tools into Data Box to present AI citation and ranking data clearly  
    - This approach aims to satisfy varying leadership expectations while improving transparency and decision-making support  

## **Process Coordination and Follow-up Actions**

Clear communication and task ownership were established to maintain momentum on key deliverables.

- Nathalie will resend the delayed blog post to Samuel for final confirmation and track publishing status (10:15)  
- Ruby will coordinate follow-ups with Kristen on high-priority leads, including the IT checkup request and AI readiness quiz submissions (06:00)  
- Nathalie and Ruby will work together to update website navigation and content blocks related to AI readiness and Copilot materials (12:59)  
- Colin and Ruby will lead dashboard design and metric selection sessions with leadership to finalize executive reporting formats (27:00)  
- The team agreed to invite Mike and Jeff to join meetings biweekly, allowing them to observe marketing discussions and better understand decision criteria (20:40)  

## **Strategic Alignment and Market Positioning**

The meeting reinforced the importance of aligning digital assets and reporting with broader business goals in AI and marketing.

- The decision to publish AI-related content, including readiness assessments and Copilot pages, supports positioning the company as a leader in AI services (09:29)  
- Enhancing the website’s navigation and content integration reflects a strategy to **convert paid campaign interest into measurable leads by improving user experience** (13:00)  
- Leadership’s desire for tailored dashboards underscores the need to balance detailed marketing data with concise executive summaries to drive informed decisions and resource allocation (24:10)  
- The use of industry-standard tools like Ahrefs and Semrush for keyword and SEO tracking signals a commitment to competitive monitoring and continuous improvement (27:30)  
- Ruby’s insight about leadership’s limited familiarity with paid marketing history shapes the approach to education and reporting, ensuring clarity on campaign impacts and ROI (25:00)',
  '2026-01-07 15:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send Samuel the blog post and relevant pending content to confirm publication status (10:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Compile and send Ruby the two specific leads and notes for follow-up with Kristen (11:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Add clickable blocks and text modules on the website’s Development and AI page to promote AI readiness assessment and related assets (13:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Create a list and mapping of all AI campaign assets and landing pages to ensure proper website integration and navigation (18:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Reach out again to the nurture campaign lead who requested the free IT checkup meeting for follow-up (06:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Kristen to follow up with the AI quiz lead and send quiz results in PDF format (06:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and provide feedback on website AI content and navigation; revisit prior edits and ensure Copilot page approvals progress (12:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Facilitate invitation for clients Mike and Jeff to join bi-weekly meetings for enhanced visibility (20:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Work with Nathalie and Colin on designing executive dashboards tailored for client leadership needs (24:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Lead the development of two distinct marketing dashboards – one comprehensive (for Jeff) and one simplified (for CFO Chris Cook) – incorporating key metrics such as cost per lead and MQL to SQL conversion (24:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Integrate keyword tracking tools like Ahrefs and Semrush into new dashboards for executive monitoring (27:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm blog post publication status with Nathalie and continue monitoring content approvals (10:33)","completed":false},{"text":"Support dashboard requirements by clarifying content publishing progress and SEO strategy as necessary (09:34)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect (2026-01-08 13:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '4995ddd4-5ee9-4673-9a9b-c773e431992a',
    '2026-01-08 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KE4R0W32V753C75ENKA47BQX',
    'Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
    '{"Nathalie Mintjens","Keenan Toward","Shane Billings"}'::text[],
    1594,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1',
    '{"id":"01KE4R0W32V753C75ENKA47BQX","title":"Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Account Strategy**\n\nResolving LinkedIn account access and branding is key to enable outreach and establish visibility.\n\n- **The main challenge is securing a LinkedIn account connected to the company for outreach**, as personal accounts are needed and business accounts can’t connect directly (03:41)  \n    - **Keenan Toward** is exploring options including using Brad’s LinkedIn account or creating a new account from a trusted contact, such as Shane’s son.  \n    - Brad’s account is branded with Pro Practice Solutions and A Grip On, which may align interests for shared use.  \n    - Natalie Mintjens will provide a clear explanation of the LinkedIn connection process to help Keenan and Brad make a decision by Monday.  \n    - This step is critical to start direct communication with prospects and leverage LinkedIn as a core outreach tool.\n\n- **LinkedIn outreach is currently automated and tied to client accounts only**, limiting flexibility (06:39)  \n    - The team has seen success with LinkedIn outreach but needs a working account to continue.  \n    - Shane Billings emphasized the importance of maintaining primary income while figuring out LinkedIn logistics, showing a cautious yet optimistic approach.  \n    - Keenan plans to finalize the LinkedIn account plan after leadership meetings and travel, aiming for clarity and momentum next week.\n\n## **Onboarding Package and Website Integration**\n\nAdding a tiered onboarding package to the website will address client adoption concerns and improve conversion.\n\n- **Keenan developed a tiered onboarding offer with 3 options: basic demo only, 30/60/90-day assistance, and a 90-day program with weekly then biweekly check-ins** (04:04)  \n    - This package directly responds to client concerns about rollout and team adoption raised during demos.  \n    - Natalie confirmed that adding this content to existing website pages will incur no additional development points, enabling quick publishing.  \n    - Keenan will send the onboarding content to Natalie by tomorrow for copywriting and placement.  \n    - This addition aims to build trust and show readiness to support clients through launch, improving demo-to-conversion rates.\n\n- **Website visitor trends are positive despite the holiday season, supporting the timing of these updates** (10:21)  \n    - Visitors increased by **26%**, bounce rate dropped nearly **7 points**, and engaged sessions rose **37%** in the past 30 days.  \n    - Traffic is up **115%**, driven mainly by email campaigns (ABM), indicating strong top-of-funnel activity.  \n    - The solution page saw a **75%** jump in visits, showing good targeting and interest.  \n    - Adding onboarding info is expected to help move visitors from browsing to taking action.\n\n## **Demo Update and Messaging Refinement**\n\nImproving the demo’s narrative flow and aligning messaging will enhance client engagement and sales conversations.\n\n- **Keenan and Shane agreed to refine the demo with a clearer story and key points to better support sales conversations** (17:50)  \n    - Shane estimates about **one hour** to update the demo system once the talk track is provided.  \n    - Keenan will draft an email outlining the desired demo narrative and key messages before their working session to maximize efficiency.  \n    - This update will help make demos more fluid and responsive to client concerns, supporting stronger conversions.  \n    - Shane and Keenan plan to spend focused time, possibly over a weekend, to complete these tweaks.\n\n## **Lead Engagement and Follow-up Strategy**\n\nThe team needs a clean communication process and targeted follow-up to convert warm leads into demos and sales.\n\n- **Keenan is holding off on outreach until onboarding and demo updates are live to present a unified message** (13:47)  \n    - A recent demo lead paused engagement due to staffing issues, showing the importance of timing and support readiness.  \n    - Keenan plans to follow up with stalled leads early next week to maintain momentum.  \n    - Shane highlighted the need to move prospects from top-of-funnel interest (clicks and visits) to bottom-of-funnel engagement with demos.  \n    - The team has a spreadsheet tracking lead activity, which will be used to prioritize outreach once messaging is refined.\n\n## **Marketing Spend and Website Analytics**\n\nOptimizing ad spend and monitoring website behavior will focus resources on channels with the best ROI.\n\n- **Paid ads on LinkedIn have become costly, with cost per click rising to about $60, prompting a review of budget allocation** (18:46)  \n    - Natalie will consult the paid media specialist to analyze this trend and recommend adjustments.  \n    - Shane emphasized directing spend toward email-driven traffic, which produces higher engagement at lower cost.  \n    - The team recognizes the need to be careful stewards of the $1,000 budget for paid media.\n\n- **Website analytics show users are researching more but hesitating to take contact actions, highlighting conversion gaps** (24:27)  \n    - Visits to the Contact Us form have declined during the holiday period, suggesting visitors consume info but delay inquiries.  \n    - Traffic sources include ABM emails and direct visits, indicating both campaign effectiveness and organic interest.  \n    - This pattern reinforces the need for clear onboarding messaging and a strong demo to nudge visitors to engage.  \n\n## **Operational and Access Challenges**\n\nResolving access to internal systems and clarifying role expectations remain ongoing operational priorities.\n\n- **Shane is currently unable to access the portal due to account issues, with a potential solution of deleting and re-adding his account being explored** (23:10)  \n    - Natalie will check with Colin and provide an update early next week.  \n    - This access is important for Shane to continue supporting sales and marketing operations.\n\n- **Keenan’s new role lacks clear weekly structure due to holidays and incomplete onboarding, delaying full productivity** (16:11)  \n    - Once the demo, onboarding, and LinkedIn outreach are set, he expects to better define his weekly activities and potentially use calendaring tools like Calendly.  \n    - This clarity will improve time management and responsiveness for client interactions.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn","Onboarding","Website Metrics","Demo","Paid Media","Client Engagement"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Account Access:** Securing a company-linked account is vital for effective outreach; exploring options for shared account use.\n\n- **Tiered Onboarding Package:** Introduced a three-tier onboarding offer to increase client adoption and improve conversion rates, ready for website integration.\n\n- **Positive Website Trends:** Visitor metrics improved, with a 26% increase and strong engagement, supporting onboarding content addition timing.\n\n- **Demo Update:** Refining the demo for clarity will enhance sales conversations; Keenan and Shane plan collaborative updates for efficiency.\n\n- **Lead Engagement Strategy:** Postponing outreach until updates are live; focused follow-ups planned for stalled leads to keep momentum.\n\n- **Marketing Spend Review:** Rising LinkedIn ad costs necessitate budget reevaluation; focus shifting to email traffic for better engagement and ROI.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nDiscuss LinkedIn account options with Brad and decide by next Monday (07:53)\nSend onboarding package content to Natalie by tomorrow for website integration (09:45)\nCompose and email the demo talk track narrative to Shane for system alignment (18:25)\nFollow up with demo client after New Year for engagement continuation (20:50)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nIntegrate the onboarding package content into website pages and provide copy for Keenan’s review (04:40)\nSend a brief explanatory paragraph about LinkedIn account connection benefits and requirements for Keenan and Brad (10:00)\nInvestigate paid media campaign cost rise with paid media specialist and report findings/recommendations (19:00)\nCoordinate with Colin to resolve Shane’s portal access issue and update him early next week (23:00)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nSupport Keenan to update the demo system based on talk track narrative, expecting about one hour of work (17:35)\nAssist with LinkedIn outreach options and backup plans for account usage (08:55)\nMonitor and advise on marketing effectiveness and funnel progression (00:00)\n"},"duration":26.56999969482422,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"Keenan Toward"},{"id":2,"name":"Shane Billings"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Shane.","index":0,"end_time":0.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"He says he''s wrapping up something.","index":1,"end_time":4.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.28,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He''ll join in a minute.","index":2,"end_time":6.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":3,"end_time":7.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.52,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I. I have a.","index":4,"end_time":9.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"A few questions and maybe you can give me some insight on what the best way is to handle this.","index":5,"end_time":13.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.32,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So in my new role, what.","index":6,"end_time":19.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What they told me in my new role versus what''s actually happening are completely different.","index":7,"end_time":24.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I was told.","index":8,"end_time":27.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.16,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The, the p. So my immediate supervisor who hired me knows I have this role with a grip on and that''s an issue.","index":9,"end_time":38.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.28,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But the rest of the company, I found out, does not know.","index":10,"end_time":41.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.11,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He did not tell them when he hired me.","index":11,"end_time":45.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.63,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so now we''re having trouble with the LinkedIn thing as far as branding that as a grip on putting a new position on there for myself.","index":12,"end_time":54.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.55,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So we can send from that.","index":13,"end_time":55.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.39,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What options do we have with that?","index":14,"end_time":57.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":60.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.95,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I know Shane is in the same position.","index":16,"end_time":63.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":62.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right.","index":17,"end_time":64.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We couldn''t.","index":18,"end_time":64.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":65.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.99,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Pretty.","index":20,"end_time":65.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Pretty much like one of us is.","index":21,"end_time":67.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.63,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Going to this weird space.","index":22,"end_time":69.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":67.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":70.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.71,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The thing is, LinkedIn is very good about detecting duplicate accounts.","index":24,"end_time":76.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ve.","index":25,"end_time":78.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I''ve had duplicate accounts deleted and they just won''t let you in.","index":26,"end_time":81.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And all the contacts that you create in the duplicate account just go away.","index":27,"end_time":85.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":28,"end_time":86.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like you can''t access them.","index":29,"end_time":87.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":86.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":30,"end_time":88.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So definitely wouldn''t recommend doing that.","index":31,"end_time":90.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is there privacy settings or something where I can keep it from being public, but you can still send from it?","index":32,"end_time":100.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.1,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"One of the things that we did, Keenan, and this was kind of tricky, is if Brad gives you his account, then you could pretend like you''re Brad and then say, oh, let me, Let me hook you up with my sales vp.","index":33,"end_time":118.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":101.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":34,"end_time":120.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But you have to get Brad''s accountant.","index":35,"end_time":123.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":121.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Brad shouldn''t mind, I''m thinking, because I don''t think he uses his LinkedIn account too much and it''s focused on dental.","index":36,"end_time":133.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":37,"end_time":135.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And he''s.","index":38,"end_time":137.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He could even put in there, I''m part owner or whatever he wants to put in of a grip on and pro practice solutions.","index":39,"end_time":145.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then if he gives you his password, then you might be able just to.","index":40,"end_time":149.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":145.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To kind of pirate his account.","index":41,"end_time":152.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Why is my camera working?","index":42,"end_time":155.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":153.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":43,"end_time":157.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So, Natalie, my understanding is that''s all we''re waiting for to get the LinkedIn stuff up and going.","index":44,"end_time":163.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.77,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Right.","index":45,"end_time":163.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.37,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Is a connection.","index":46,"end_time":164.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.65,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":47,"end_time":165.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":48,"end_time":166.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, so I''ll have that figured out by probably by next week.","index":49,"end_time":172.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.7,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m actually in Arizona right now with my initial in person meetings with this company and talking to all the leadership and everything.","index":50,"end_time":182.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So hopefully I''ll get a good feeling after I get out of here and get back home and Maybe we can use mine, but I''ll talk to Brad.","index":51,"end_time":191.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s another option as well.","index":52,"end_time":192.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.34,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I''ve got to come up with something there.","index":53,"end_time":195.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.41,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The only other thing I have for you today is.","index":54,"end_time":198.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So after the two meetings, both of the people I talked to both kind of shared the same concern, which was rollout and the number of team members that they have and how they would get this delivered to their teams.","index":55,"end_time":213.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.53,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so we put together like an onboarding package which is going to be a tiered base package.","index":56,"end_time":218.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.89,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So they''ll base, basically have three options of either having, you know, no onboarding assistance other than the basic demo and conversation.","index":57,"end_time":228.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They''ll have three tiered, 30, 60, 90 day option and then they''ll have another option that starts as weekly the first month, bi weekly the second month, and then a final call the third month in the 90 days.","index":58,"end_time":244.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.2,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And.","index":59,"end_time":245.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so I have that put together, but that''ll need to, that''ll need to be put on the website somehow because we''ve been talking about points and how that affects things.","index":60,"end_time":256.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.21,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"How does that fit into the 50 points that we have that we''re trying to operate within?","index":61,"end_time":264.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.41,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, so when we do small website tweaks like that, those actually don''t cost any points.","index":62,"end_time":270.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.45,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it would cost points to like when we create a whole new web page and develop it, but just adding new content onto pages we''ve already done, those are just adjustments that don''t have any points associated.","index":63,"end_time":282.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if you want, you could send over the onboarding packages that you do have.","index":64,"end_time":288.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":282.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I can put together a plan of like, which pages we can include them onto, come up with some copy, send that over to you for you to review.","index":65,"end_time":295.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''d be great.","index":66,"end_time":298.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s the, that''s the really the two things I have.","index":67,"end_time":300.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Shane, was there anything else we had for Natalie this morning that we needed to cover?","index":68,"end_time":304.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Just getting you on LinkedIn I think is the biggest challenge.","index":69,"end_time":309.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.51,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And you''re meeting with your management.","index":70,"end_time":311.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So, you know, obviously, Keenan, I totally respect that your main job to keep you employed is of utmost importance.","index":71,"end_time":322.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We don''t want to sacrifice that.","index":72,"end_time":324.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I feel the same way.","index":73,"end_time":325.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t want to sacrifice my main money income.","index":74,"end_time":331.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so I totally respect that.","index":75,"end_time":333.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And we''ll just have to figure out a way that we can do it.","index":76,"end_time":336.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s too bad.","index":77,"end_time":339.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.419,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is there any way to do it from the business account?","index":78,"end_time":343.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"No, the business account can''t connect with people directly.","index":79,"end_time":350.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I see, yeah.","index":80,"end_time":351.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":81,"end_time":355.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But yeah, that was what''s on our mind.","index":82,"end_time":358.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think we''ve had the most success with connecting through LinkedIn accounts?","index":83,"end_time":363.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":363.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you, Natalie, do you have people that do outreach in that way that are specific to.","index":85,"end_time":372.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I know some marketing companies.","index":86,"end_time":376.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just the outreach through LinkedIn and.","index":87,"end_time":379.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And that kind of thing?","index":88,"end_time":380.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.45,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":382.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you mean do we usually do outreach through LinkedIn?","index":90,"end_time":385.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"No.","index":91,"end_time":386.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Do you have people directly who do the outreach?","index":92,"end_time":388.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, no, it''s all automated, actually.","index":93,"end_time":391.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.41,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know that, but you still have to have an account.","index":94,"end_time":393.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, no, we only use, like, client accounts directly.","index":95,"end_time":398.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":399.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":97,"end_time":401.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And that''s the thing.","index":98,"end_time":403.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So if, like, I think so, it sounds like what you''re saying is Brad''s LinkedIn is branded with a grip on, is that right?","index":99,"end_time":409.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"It could be.","index":100,"end_time":410.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He''s the only one who is diary.","index":101,"end_time":413.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He works for himself, truly.","index":102,"end_time":414.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He doesn''t have a boss that he''s gotta make happy, really.","index":103,"end_time":418.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.87,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And he owns pro practice, portion of pro practice as well.","index":104,"end_time":422.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So it''s in his interest potentially to do this.","index":105,"end_time":425.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, do you think he''ll go for it?","index":106,"end_time":427.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.87,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I''ve been following him and he''s been sending stuff out for salt flats on there and he.","index":107,"end_time":437.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.08,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He has a salt flats Facebook as well.","index":108,"end_time":440.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.96,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I''ll chat with him.","index":109,"end_time":442.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.48,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll mention it to him today and.","index":110,"end_time":444.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":442.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll make that.","index":111,"end_time":446.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":444.92,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Make that decision by Monday.","index":112,"end_time":447.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I might get a better conversation today.","index":113,"end_time":451.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The unfortunate part about this new role is I actually haven''t talked to anybody because of the holidays.","index":114,"end_time":457.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.72,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I basically was hired and then it was like, here you go.","index":115,"end_time":459.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.24,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Go do things.","index":116,"end_time":460.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so hopefully today I''ll get a better feel for where they''re at and what I can do.","index":117,"end_time":467.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.56,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I was also kind of monitoring my LinkedIn this last week because I had seen people from the company jumping on there to check me out because they announced me on a call and sent out an email.","index":118,"end_time":476.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I just wanted to make sure we got through this first initial wave of things.","index":119,"end_time":482.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.149,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I was hoping that would calm down for next week.","index":120,"end_time":486.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So.","index":121,"end_time":486.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.11,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But like I said, I. I won''t have an idea until later today when we have all these meetings and everything.","index":122,"end_time":493.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So Brad may go for it, though.","index":123,"end_time":498.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That may.","index":124,"end_time":498.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.23,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That may be an option.","index":125,"end_time":499.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":498.63,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":126,"end_time":503.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s kind of the two that I can think of at this point that are realistic.","index":127,"end_time":507.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Unless we were to have, like you said, another account, whether that''s somebody else that we''ve used or some other way to make a business account that works, which.","index":128,"end_time":518.629,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That would make more sense to me.","index":129,"end_time":519.909,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":518.629,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I don''t know why LinkedIn doesn''t have that as an option.","index":130,"end_time":522.789,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.909,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Here''s an.","index":131,"end_time":523.309,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.789,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Here''s another option.","index":132,"end_time":524.749,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.309,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"My son is in college, he uses his LinkedIn account to.","index":133,"end_time":531.949,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.829,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To, you know, they don''t do anything with it.","index":134,"end_time":536.389,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.669,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He''s.","index":135,"end_time":536.829,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.389,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So he''s not working for anybody.","index":136,"end_time":538.269,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.829,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"He could be a sales rep, quote, unquote.","index":137,"end_time":541.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":542.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.26,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And we could take over his account so Brad doesn''t go for it.","index":139,"end_time":546.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Then what I could do is use my sons and.","index":140,"end_time":549.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And he wouldn''t care.","index":141,"end_time":552.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":142,"end_time":554.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":553.54,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll.","index":143,"end_time":555.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.579,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll talk to Brad.","index":144,"end_time":556.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll let you know once I talk to him, and I''ll let you guys know how I feel after this.","index":145,"end_time":561.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":556.18,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"These meetings as well.","index":146,"end_time":562.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.38,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I just wanted to make sure that we.","index":147,"end_time":564.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We have a plan for that.","index":148,"end_time":565.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Except that''s the piece that we need to get going, and then get the onboarding piece on the website is another thing.","index":149,"end_time":573.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So, Natalie, I''ll send that over to you by tomorrow.","index":150,"end_time":576.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.59,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m traveling back today and I have meetings all day, but I''ll get that to you by tomorrow.","index":151,"end_time":580.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":152,"end_time":583.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.67,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s really what I have now.","index":153,"end_time":585.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.19,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I am curious to see if visits on the website have changed at all, which we.","index":154,"end_time":591.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We''re not sending LinkedIn, so we''re not directing people there, so maybe there''s not too much.","index":155,"end_time":595.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.79,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But I''ll let you take it from there, Natalie.","index":156,"end_time":597.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.95,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":157,"end_time":599.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then one, One other thing I can.","index":158,"end_time":602.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Right after this, I can send you over like a.","index":159,"end_time":604.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.15,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Just a quick paragraph that might help you in your.","index":160,"end_time":607.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"When you meet with Brad, just to explain what we plan to do with the LinkedIn account, just so he''s clear on what it entails.","index":161,"end_time":615.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.55,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":162,"end_time":616.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That might help me too, maybe in my conversation.","index":163,"end_time":618.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.32,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So if you send that over, I can take a look.","index":164,"end_time":620.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.48,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":165,"end_time":622.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then in terms of website visitors, so I was taking a look at this yesterday, and it''s actually quite positive.","index":166,"end_time":630,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":624.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Usually we see quite a dip around the holiday period, like people on vacation, not really looking at vendors and stuff.","index":167,"end_time":635.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But things are positive across the board.","index":168,"end_time":638.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So visitors, this is looking at the past 30 days.","index":169,"end_time":641.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Visitors increased 26%, the bounce rate dropped nearly 7 points, and our engaged sessions on the website rose 37%.","index":170,"end_time":651.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this could be due to the new messaging that we have that we updated.","index":171,"end_time":655.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"ABM is driving a lot of these results.","index":172,"end_time":658.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Traffic grew 115%.","index":173,"end_time":663.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So mostly emails that people are clicking that are bringing them onto the website.","index":174,"end_time":668.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then if we have LinkedIn, we.","index":175,"end_time":670.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Could get over Christmas, no less.","index":176,"end_time":672.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":673.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Which is surprising.","index":178,"end_time":674.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, usually it slows down quite a bit.","index":179,"end_time":676.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.52,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''s positive.","index":180,"end_time":680.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The top of the funnel has always looked great.","index":181,"end_time":683.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, that is the concern.","index":182,"end_time":687.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But let''s Talk about that, Keep going, keep making us feel good.","index":183,"end_time":690.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then the solution page also jumps 75%.","index":184,"end_time":696.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So from what I can see, I mean it looks like we''re targeting the right people.","index":185,"end_time":700.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.97,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Once they get to the website, they are engaged, they''re jumping around a little bit, the bounce rate is decreasing.","index":186,"end_time":706.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.53,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think we uncovered, or Keenan uncovered something with those demos about people being concerned about how or the adoption or how they''re going to integrate this with their teams.","index":187,"end_time":716.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So adding that language to the website will probably help as well to get people to actually convert instead of just looking around.","index":188,"end_time":724.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, one, one other factor that we''re looking at right now as well as far as getting people to convert and get demos today is teams are still doing end of year wrap up and then new year kind of launch and kind of getting back into the office.","index":189,"end_time":741.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I imagine that anybody who has interest at this point is kind of in our same situation or my same situation.","index":190,"end_time":751.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.63,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''m experiencing now they''ve got to get back to the office, get everybody back from vacation, have the conversations of what they want to do.","index":191,"end_time":758.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I think, I mean that all sounds positive, that that''s all good.","index":192,"end_time":763.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.33,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And I do agree, I think that if we get this onboarding on there, it''s just another step that solidifies us as a company that''s prepared with a support strategy and a product that has the functionality and the backing for them to be able to launch.","index":193,"end_time":779.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.69,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"You know, I think another factor, if I''m completely honest in going into those demos was one of our clients had reached out to somebody previously, talked to somebody previously and went back to check the link and it wasn''t active.","index":194,"end_time":795.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that''s how I got involved with the one client.","index":195,"end_time":798.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so that''s probably not a good first experience.","index":196,"end_time":802.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.83,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"If I was in their situation, I would be concerned that there''s so much change, you know, while I''m trying to adopt a new product and, and the other gentleman, He, he went through everything that he wanted to talk about, talked about white labeling and then basically just stopped having conversations.","index":197,"end_time":827.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.91,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He didn''t even respond to the, the emails that I''ve sent him.","index":198,"end_time":830.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.82,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I am kind of curious about him.","index":199,"end_time":833.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.58,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I, I, I had a vibe from him during the call, fishing for information he could use to develop something himself because the one, the one guy''s title ended up when he logged on, said something about developer when he logged on and then he jumped off the call and so I was wondering if he had the guy with him and then kind of overseeing and overhearing things because I have not heard back from him.","index":200,"end_time":864.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.94,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So, you know, I think we solidify this.","index":201,"end_time":869.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":867.45,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We, we have the changes on the website, we get the onboarding protocol in there, we find a way to start communicating with people.","index":202,"end_time":876.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.93,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And that''s why I haven''t started reaching back out to people yet.","index":203,"end_time":881.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.13,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I want to make sure that we have a clean form of communication, a place they can go to view everything and see everything.","index":204,"end_time":888.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I also, at some point, Shane and I know this will take some organization from you and I and maybe a weekend or something, not a full weekend, but just some time over a weekend to make that demo kind of more fluid with our messaging.","index":205,"end_time":905.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no, happy to, Happy to be a part of that.","index":206,"end_time":909.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You just.","index":207,"end_time":910.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think, just grab me whatever.","index":208,"end_time":912.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I think those three things, to be honest with you, between the website changes, the onboarding program and a few tweaks to the.","index":209,"end_time":920.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":912.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The demo, and I feel very comfortable in approaching people with this.","index":210,"end_time":924.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.52,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So it''s really just getting the LinkedIn.","index":211,"end_time":929.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.36,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But so, so let''s, let''s.","index":212,"end_time":932.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":213,"end_time":934.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":933.68,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just those three things.","index":214,"end_time":935.119,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Do you need anything else, like links fixed or anything?","index":215,"end_time":938.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.119,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like, do you have a.","index":216,"end_time":940.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.32,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like if.","index":217,"end_time":941.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m just saying, like if.","index":218,"end_time":945.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So we''re creating a to do list here.","index":219,"end_time":947.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t want to miss anything.","index":220,"end_time":948.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":949.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":949.44,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I don''t think we have any links anymore because we''re using forms.","index":222,"end_time":953.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.48,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Correct.","index":223,"end_time":954.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.8,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Let''s double check.","index":224,"end_time":960.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.96,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":225,"end_time":965.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So these are all connected to our CRM, the forms.","index":226,"end_time":970,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":965.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, because that''s the other issue I was having with this is I still to this day don''t even know what a week looks like in this role because it hasn''t been active, everybody''s been on vacation and I.","index":227,"end_time":984.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":971.29,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"They''ve just had me doing random things.","index":228,"end_time":986.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So once I can determine that maybe calendly is an option again and I can manage calendars, but to this point I just, I didn''t have enough information about what my day would look like to try to allow a calendly to be open.","index":229,"end_time":1000.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.05,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":1002.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1001.54,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Sounds like we just need those three things.","index":231,"end_time":1010.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.98,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"A demo.","index":232,"end_time":1011.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1010.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What was the other two things?","index":233,"end_time":1013.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1011.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So we already did the website changes.","index":234,"end_time":1015.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.18,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":235,"end_time":1016.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.9,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"We need to put in the onboarding program somewhere on there and I''ll get that to Natalie tomorrow.","index":236,"end_time":1022.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":1023.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1022.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then make the determination with.","index":238,"end_time":1026.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1024.06,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Between LinkedIn accounts which one we''re going to use and get that started and then update the demo to make it more fluid to our talk track.","index":239,"end_time":1038.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yep.","index":240,"end_time":1039.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then I''ll send over a quick description of what connecting the LinkedIn account entails just for you and Brad so you can make that Decision.","index":241,"end_time":1050.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And can I have nights free?","index":242,"end_time":1053.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1052.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Usually like after six sometimes.","index":243,"end_time":1056.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1053.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So if you have nights for.","index":244,"end_time":1057.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You just have me.","index":245,"end_time":1058.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":246,"end_time":1059.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1058.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":247,"end_time":1060.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.42,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":248,"end_time":1061.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.86,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"How long do you think that would take, Shane?","index":249,"end_time":1062.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.46,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Well, I imagine you want to get the demo, the data, right, Correct?","index":250,"end_time":1068.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yes.","index":251,"end_time":1069.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.22,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":1070.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And it''s a narrative, so you''re almost telling a story as part of the.","index":253,"end_time":1074.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":254,"end_time":1077.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1077.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I would say an hour.","index":255,"end_time":1078.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.51,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because we''re just going to need to type in the right words into the system, into the demo system.","index":256,"end_time":1087.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s not going to take long.","index":257,"end_time":1088.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.07,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s the story you want to tell.","index":258,"end_time":1090.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.03,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So if you come in with a story saying, I imagine that this is the way that the demo is going to go from a dialogue standpoint, I''ll try to make the system match that way.","index":259,"end_time":1102.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s not too hard.","index":260,"end_time":1103.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1102.51,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":261,"end_time":1104.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.99,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So what I.","index":262,"end_time":1105.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.47,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"What I''ll do to make that easier for the both of us then is I''ll.","index":263,"end_time":1108.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.07,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"I''ll just compose an email of kind of the.","index":264,"end_time":1110.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.27,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"The talk track and the key points.","index":265,"end_time":1113.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.03,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yep.","index":266,"end_time":1114.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then that way we''ll have that to work off of.","index":267,"end_time":1116.989,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That way you can view that before we actually meet and we''ll kind of have an opportunity that works to eliminate wasting time when we get on a call.","index":268,"end_time":1125.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.989,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":269,"end_time":1127.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1126.56,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie.","index":270,"end_time":1128,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1127.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I noticed our cost per click went way up.","index":271,"end_time":1130.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s like, It''s.","index":272,"end_time":1132.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.52,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s like $60 now.","index":273,"end_time":1133.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.32,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let me open that up.","index":274,"end_time":1137.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"My thought was, is if we''re getting such good response from the emails, not such a good response from the.","index":275,"end_time":1150.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1143.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"From the.","index":276,"end_time":1153.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1152.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":277,"end_time":1154.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1154.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We just need to focus on where we''re getting the good response.","index":278,"end_time":1158.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"100 clicks for free versus 2 clicks for a hunt for, you know.","index":279,"end_time":1165.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1160.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":280,"end_time":1170.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.33,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Well, let me take this to my paid media specialist and we can take a look.","index":281,"end_time":1174.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.29,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know that these were paused for a couple of weeks.","index":282,"end_time":1177.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.93,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":283,"end_time":1178.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, please do.","index":284,"end_time":1179.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1178.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I.","index":285,"end_time":1180.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1179.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"A thousand dollars is a lot for us, right?","index":286,"end_time":1185.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1186.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And I know the very first demo that we ever got was from LinkedIn ads, so it seemed like it was working at the very beginning, but it slowed down a little bit and now we''re getting more engagement through the actual messaging.","index":288,"end_time":1201.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.13,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":289,"end_time":1203.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1203.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You guys give us a recommendation?","index":290,"end_time":1205.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1203.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just.","index":291,"end_time":1205.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":292,"end_time":1206.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You know.","index":293,"end_time":1206.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1206.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, as a steward of that thousand dollars, I have to be careful.","index":294,"end_time":1211.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I want you to feel the same way.","index":295,"end_time":1213.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1211.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":296,"end_time":1213.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.5,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Keenan, you didn''t hear back from the person you did the demo with?","index":297,"end_time":1219.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1215.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Have they responded at all?","index":298,"end_time":1220.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You still engaged with them?","index":299,"end_time":1222.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1220.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The one that was interested?","index":300,"end_time":1223.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"No.","index":301,"end_time":1226.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So she.","index":302,"end_time":1227.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.7,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She.","index":303,"end_time":1229.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1229.67,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Unfortunately, the day that we did the demo, found out she was gonna have to run an office Herself because they had two people quit.","index":304,"end_time":1237.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1229.99,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so since that I haven''t heard back.","index":305,"end_time":1240.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1237.75,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She answered that day when I talked to her beef after the demo.","index":306,"end_time":1244.829,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.87,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But the since then she has not answered again.","index":307,"end_time":1247.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.829,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"So I was gonna wait till the new year, kind of give her.","index":308,"end_time":1250.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1248.15,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":1250.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You know, some time and then maybe Monday reach back.","index":310,"end_time":1253.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.99,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe Monday reach back out to her and say, hey, you know, I''m back in the office.","index":311,"end_time":1257.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.56,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Was thinking about the conversation that we had and just wanted to follow up and see where she''s at and kind of go from there.","index":312,"end_time":1262.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.84,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, just.","index":313,"end_time":1265.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1264.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I know.","index":314,"end_time":1266.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1265.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just keep it front of mind.","index":315,"end_time":1267.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.12,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":316,"end_time":1269.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep, yep, yep, yep.","index":317,"end_time":1270.479,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Her.","index":318,"end_time":1272.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1272.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Her issue, I mean pretty directly was that they just.","index":319,"end_time":1276.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.6,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"She''s got too much on her plate and she said she''s never been fully staffed and she''s been in this role.","index":320,"end_time":1283.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.04,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"It''s pretty much, you know, just like Brad talks about.","index":321,"end_time":1286.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.61,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"He ends up running an office because they, they lose people all the time and is frankly the reason I left.","index":322,"end_time":1291.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Dental is too unstable and I was working six days a week and it just wasn''t worth the money.","index":323,"end_time":1299.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.93,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":324,"end_time":1300.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1300.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":325,"end_time":1301.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1300.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":326,"end_time":1302.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.69,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But yeah, I think that''s it for me.","index":327,"end_time":1307.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.97,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Me too.","index":328,"end_time":1310.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m excited about the top of the funnel.","index":329,"end_time":1314.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just got to get to the bottom.","index":330,"end_time":1316.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1318.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1317.56,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And now when, when you get those three things in, we do have a list of people who kind of click on those.","index":332,"end_time":1325.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":333,"end_time":1326.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because we have the spreadsheet, we might have to say, okay, how do we take the top of the funnel and pull them down through the bottom once we get those mess that messaging.","index":334,"end_time":1336.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1326.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":335,"end_time":1337.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That seems like the thing that we need to do before we start pulling.","index":336,"end_time":1340.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So we have a lot of data that hopefully we can transition and push to the bottom of the funnel.","index":337,"end_time":1347.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":338,"end_time":1351.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.73,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Well, and I think that''s going to be key for our time to get things ramped up.","index":339,"end_time":1356.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1352.25,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"And so yeah, I want to get, get these website changes done, get an update on the demo and then start reaching, reaching out to people and trying to pull them in directly.","index":340,"end_time":1367.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1358.25,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll say the demo or the website looks good.","index":341,"end_time":1371.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''re adding stuff but I don''t have any problems with what''s on there currently.","index":342,"end_time":1374.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So happy with it.","index":343,"end_time":1377.739,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Just gotta, just gotta keep moving.","index":344,"end_time":1380.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1377.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":345,"end_time":1381.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie, I''m still not able to get to the portal.","index":346,"end_time":1385.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1382.62,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s just my account.","index":347,"end_time":1386.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1385.78,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I have no idea why.","index":348,"end_time":1388.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1387.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I. Yeah, I don''t know why.","index":349,"end_time":1391.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1390.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, when you go there.","index":350,"end_time":1395.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.35,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, I am.","index":351,"end_time":1398.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is it possible to delete my account and re.","index":352,"end_time":1400.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Add me?","index":353,"end_time":1401.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1400.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, let me, let me check with Colin.","index":354,"end_time":1403.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"He''s.","index":355,"end_time":1404.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"He''s at A company off site today and tomorrow.","index":356,"end_time":1406.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.31,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":357,"end_time":1407.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I''ll likely have an answer for you early next week.","index":358,"end_time":1409.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":359,"end_time":1411.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, let''s keep.","index":360,"end_time":1413.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.39,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keep plugging.","index":361,"end_time":1414.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s keep going.","index":362,"end_time":1415.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Hopefully somebody bites and purchases and we''ll see.","index":363,"end_time":1420.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1415.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Anybody go back to the.","index":364,"end_time":1422.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1420.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"To that data?","index":365,"end_time":1423.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I wanted to look at one more thing.","index":366,"end_time":1425.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1423.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"How many people are looking at the Contact Us form?","index":367,"end_time":1427.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1425.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is that up or down?","index":368,"end_time":1428.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1427.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, let me share.","index":369,"end_time":1430.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.25,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Have to refresh.","index":370,"end_time":1455.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1456.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"There we go.","index":372,"end_time":1458.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There we go.","index":373,"end_time":1460.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What were you looking at before?","index":374,"end_time":1464.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1463.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because this is all down.","index":375,"end_time":1465.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1464.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":376,"end_time":1467.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I usually look at last 30 days.","index":377,"end_time":1469.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":378,"end_time":1470.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.32,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So what that tells me is that it was down during Christmas, but.","index":379,"end_time":1476.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, because what has it been, a month?","index":380,"end_time":1479.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1476.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"No, it hasn''t been a month since Christmas.","index":381,"end_time":1481.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, the dip.","index":382,"end_time":1483.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So it probably got a bump up over.","index":383,"end_time":1485.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s look at the last 30 days and see what it says.","index":384,"end_time":1488.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.76,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The 16th and the 12th.","index":385,"end_time":1494.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1494.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1494.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So you got more right up until Christmas than it did.","index":387,"end_time":1498.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1494.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1499.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.81,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Even on the 22nd.","index":389,"end_time":1500.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1499.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":390,"end_time":1504.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So the Contact Us that''s been going down.","index":391,"end_time":1507.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1513.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1512.57,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it looks like people are just doing a lot more informational research.","index":393,"end_time":1516.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.37,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like they''re reading all of the information on the pages but not clicking to take that next step to contact us, Right?","index":394,"end_time":1526.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1519.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yep, that''s what it looks like.","index":395,"end_time":1530.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":396,"end_time":1533.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What''s that?","index":397,"end_time":1535.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, never mind.","index":398,"end_time":1536.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1536.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Not set direct change by source.","index":399,"end_time":1542.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1537.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So that''s just if they Google it.","index":400,"end_time":1545.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1543.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So abm, that''s the email campaign, right?","index":401,"end_time":1549.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, Direct could also be that someone shares it with a colleague or something.","index":402,"end_time":1555.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1550,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So anything that.","index":403,"end_time":1557.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1556.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Anything that Google Analytics can''t directly track, they just bucket it under direct.","index":404,"end_time":1562.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1557.68,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Got it.","index":405,"end_time":1563.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1562.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They just type it in, is what you''re saying.","index":406,"end_time":1564.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1565.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Or like they pass it along through a message or something.","index":408,"end_time":1568.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":409,"end_time":1570.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1569.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Alrighty.","index":410,"end_time":1571.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1570.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, you know, Cool.","index":411,"end_time":1576.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1571.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t have anything else.","index":412,"end_time":1577.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1576.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":413,"end_time":1580.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, guys.","index":414,"end_time":1583.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.3,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":415,"end_time":1584.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1583.74,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":416,"end_time":1585.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1584.78,"speaker_name":"Keenan Toward"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":417,"end_time":1586.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1586.06,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":418,"end_time":1588.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1586.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Bye.","index":419,"end_time":1588.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"}],"dateString":"2026-01-08T13:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com,shane@agrippon.com,f.dominguez@agrippon.com,j.samstag@agrippon.com,monique.king@agrippon.com,david.reynolds@agrippon.com,keenan.toward@agrippon.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com","shane@agrippon.com","f.dominguez@agrippon.com","j.samstag@agrippon.com","monique.king@agrippon.com","david.reynolds@agrippon.com","keenan.toward@agrippon.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE4R0W32V753C75ENKA47BQX","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.88,"bullets":["Outlined three-step plan to strengthen outreach: fix demo, finalize LinkedIn, launch onboarding.","Nathalie confirmed new onboarding content won''t consume website development points budget.","Website metrics improved: visitor count up 26%, engaged sessions up 37%, bounce rate down 7 points.","Keenan identified adoption concern and built tiered onboarding options to address client feedback.","Shane raised cost-per-click concerns; Nathalie will consult paid media team for budget optimization."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I feel very comfortable in approaching people with this.","speaker":"Keenan Toward"},{"quote":"Visitors increased 26%, the bounce rate dropped nearly 7 points.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"I''m excited about the top of the funnel. Just got to get to the bottom.","speaker":"Shane Billings"}],"topics":["delivery","launch","risk","outreach","website","budget"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **LinkedIn Account Strategy**\n\nResolving LinkedIn account access and branding is key to enable outreach and establish visibility.\n\n- **The main challenge is securing a LinkedIn account connected to the company for outreach**, as personal accounts are needed and business accounts can’t connect directly (03:41)  \n    - **Keenan Toward** is exploring options including using Brad’s LinkedIn account or creating a new account from a trusted contact, such as Shane’s son.  \n    - Brad’s account is branded with Pro Practice Solutions and A Grip On, which may align interests for shared use.  \n    - Natalie Mintjens will provide a clear explanation of the LinkedIn connection process to help Keenan and Brad make a decision by Monday.  \n    - This step is critical to start direct communication with prospects and leverage LinkedIn as a core outreach tool.\n\n- **LinkedIn outreach is currently automated and tied to client accounts only**, limiting flexibility (06:39)  \n    - The team has seen success with LinkedIn outreach but needs a working account to continue.  \n    - Shane Billings emphasized the importance of maintaining primary income while figuring out LinkedIn logistics, showing a cautious yet optimistic approach.  \n    - Keenan plans to finalize the LinkedIn account plan after leadership meetings and travel, aiming for clarity and momentum next week.\n\n## **Onboarding Package and Website Integration**\n\nAdding a tiered onboarding package to the website will address client adoption concerns and improve conversion.\n\n- **Keenan developed a tiered onboarding offer with 3 options: basic demo only, 30/60/90-day assistance, and a 90-day program with weekly then biweekly check-ins** (04:04)  \n    - This package directly responds to client concerns about rollout and team adoption raised during demos.  \n    - Natalie confirmed that adding this content to existing website pages will incur no additional development points, enabling quick publishing.  \n    - Keenan will send the onboarding content to Natalie by tomorrow for copywriting and placement.  \n    - This addition aims to build trust and show readiness to support clients through launch, improving demo-to-conversion rates.\n\n- **Website visitor trends are positive despite the holiday season, supporting the timing of these updates** (10:21)  \n    - Visitors increased by **26%**, bounce rate dropped nearly **7 points**, and engaged sessions rose **37%** in the past 30 days.  \n    - Traffic is up **115%**, driven mainly by email campaigns (ABM), indicating strong top-of-funnel activity.  \n    - The solution page saw a **75%** jump in visits, showing good targeting and interest.  \n    - Adding onboarding info is expected to help move visitors from browsing to taking action.\n\n## **Demo Update and Messaging Refinement**\n\nImproving the demo’s narrative flow and aligning messaging will enhance client engagement and sales conversations.\n\n- **Keenan and Shane agreed to refine the demo with a clearer story and key points to better support sales conversations** (17:50)  \n    - Shane estimates about **one hour** to update the demo system once the talk track is provided.  \n    - Keenan will draft an email outlining the desired demo narrative and key messages before their working session to maximize efficiency.  \n    - This update will help make demos more fluid and responsive to client concerns, supporting stronger conversions.  \n    - Shane and Keenan plan to spend focused time, possibly over a weekend, to complete these tweaks.\n\n## **Lead Engagement and Follow-up Strategy**\n\nThe team needs a clean communication process and targeted follow-up to convert warm leads into demos and sales.\n\n- **Keenan is holding off on outreach until onboarding and demo updates are live to present a unified message** (13:47)  \n    - A recent demo lead paused engagement due to staffing issues, showing the importance of timing and support readiness.  \n    - Keenan plans to follow up with stalled leads early next week to maintain momentum.  \n    - Shane highlighted the need to move prospects from top-of-funnel interest (clicks and visits) to bottom-of-funnel engagement with demos.  \n    - The team has a spreadsheet tracking lead activity, which will be used to prioritize outreach once messaging is refined.\n\n## **Marketing Spend and Website Analytics**\n\nOptimizing ad spend and monitoring website behavior will focus resources on channels with the best ROI.\n\n- **Paid ads on LinkedIn have become costly, with cost per click rising to about $60, prompting a review of budget allocation** (18:46)  \n    - Natalie will consult the paid media specialist to analyze this trend and recommend adjustments.  \n    - Shane emphasized directing spend toward email-driven traffic, which produces higher engagement at lower cost.  \n    - The team recognizes the need to be careful stewards of the $1,000 budget for paid media.\n\n- **Website analytics show users are researching more but hesitating to take contact actions, highlighting conversion gaps** (24:27)  \n    - Visits to the Contact Us form have declined during the holiday period, suggesting visitors consume info but delay inquiries.  \n    - Traffic sources include ABM emails and direct visits, indicating both campaign effectiveness and organic interest.  \n    - This pattern reinforces the need for clear onboarding messaging and a strong demo to nudge visitors to engage.  \n\n## **Operational and Access Challenges**\n\nResolving access to internal systems and clarifying role expectations remain ongoing operational priorities.\n\n- **Shane is currently unable to access the portal due to account issues, with a potential solution of deleting and re-adding his account being explored** (23:10)  \n    - Natalie will check with Colin and provide an update early next week.  \n    - This access is important for Shane to continue supporting sales and marketing operations.\n\n- **Keenan’s new role lacks clear weekly structure due to holidays and incomplete onboarding, delaying full productivity** (16:11)  \n    - Once the demo, onboarding, and LinkedIn outreach are set, he expects to better define his weekly activities and potentially use calendaring tools like Calendly.  \n    - This clarity will improve time management and responsiveness for client interactions.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn","Onboarding","Website Metrics","Demo","Paid Media","Client Engagement"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Account Access:** Securing a company-linked account is vital for effective outreach; exploring options for shared account use.\n\n- **Tiered Onboarding Package:** Introduced a three-tier onboarding offer to increase client adoption and improve conversion rates, ready for website integration.\n\n- **Positive Website Trends:** Visitor metrics improved, with a 26% increase and strong engagement, supporting onboarding content addition timing.\n\n- **Demo Update:** Refining the demo for clarity will enhance sales conversations; Keenan and Shane plan collaborative updates for efficiency.\n\n- **Lead Engagement Strategy:** Postponing outreach until updates are live; focused follow-ups planned for stalled leads to keep momentum.\n\n- **Marketing Spend Review:** Rising LinkedIn ad costs necessitate budget reevaluation; focus shifting to email traffic for better engagement and ROI.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nDiscuss LinkedIn account options with Brad and decide by next Monday (07:53)\nSend onboarding package content to Natalie by tomorrow for website integration (09:45)\nCompose and email the demo talk track narrative to Shane for system alignment (18:25)\nFollow up with demo client after New Year for engagement continuation (20:50)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nIntegrate the onboarding package content into website pages and provide copy for Keenan’s review (04:40)\nSend a brief explanatory paragraph about LinkedIn account connection benefits and requirements for Keenan and Brad (10:00)\nInvestigate paid media campaign cost rise with paid media specialist and report findings/recommendations (19:00)\nCoordinate with Colin to resolve Shane’s portal access issue and update him early next week (23:00)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nSupport Keenan to update the demo system based on talk track narrative, expecting about one hour of work (17:35)\nAssist with LinkedIn outreach options and backup plans for account usage (08:55)\nMonitor and advise on marketing effectiveness and funnel progression (00:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"5874f6f1-019d-4593-9642-ee0fc4f3096f","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
