INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **LinkedIn Account Strategy**

Resolving LinkedIn account access and branding is key to enable outreach and establish visibility.

- **The main challenge is securing a LinkedIn account connected to the company for outreach**, as personal accounts are needed and business accounts can’t connect directly (03:41)  
    - **Keenan Toward** is exploring options including using Brad’s LinkedIn account or creating a new account from a trusted contact, such as Shane’s son.  
    - Brad’s account is branded with Pro Practice Solutions and A Grip On, which may align interests for shared use.  
    - Natalie Mintjens will provide a clear explanation of the LinkedIn connection process to help Keenan and Brad make a decision by Monday.  
    - This step is critical to start direct communication with prospects and leverage LinkedIn as a core outreach tool.

- **LinkedIn outreach is currently automated and tied to client accounts only**, limiting flexibility (06:39)  
    - The team has seen success with LinkedIn outreach but needs a working account to continue.  
    - Shane Billings emphasized the importance of maintaining primary income while figuring out LinkedIn logistics, showing a cautious yet optimistic approach.  
    - Keenan plans to finalize the LinkedIn account plan after leadership meetings and travel, aiming for clarity and momentum next week.

## **Onboarding Package and Website Integration**

Adding a tiered onboarding package to the website will address client adoption concerns and improve conversion.

- **Keenan developed a tiered onboarding offer with 3 options: basic demo only, 30/60/90-day assistance, and a 90-day program with weekly then biweekly check-ins** (04:04)  
    - This package directly responds to client concerns about rollout and team adoption raised during demos.  
    - Natalie confirmed that adding this content to existing website pages will incur no additional development points, enabling quick publishing.  
    - Keenan will send the onboarding content to Natalie by tomorrow for copywriting and placement.  
    - This addition aims to build trust and show readiness to support clients through launch, improving demo-to-conversion rates.

- **Website visitor trends are positive despite the holiday season, supporting the timing of these updates** (10:21)  
    - Visitors increased by **26%**, bounce rate dropped nearly **7 points**, and engaged sessions rose **37%** in the past 30 days.  
    - Traffic is up **115%**, driven mainly by email campaigns (ABM), indicating strong top-of-funnel activity.  
    - The solution page saw a **75%** jump in visits, showing good targeting and interest.  
    - Adding onboarding info is expected to help move visitors from browsing to taking action.

## **Demo Update and Messaging Refinement**

Improving the demo’s narrative flow and aligning messaging will enhance client engagement and sales conversations.

- **Keenan and Shane agreed to refine the demo with a clearer story and key points to better support sales conversations** (17:50)  
    - Shane estimates about **one hour** to update the demo system once the talk track is provided.  
    - Keenan will draft an email outlining the desired demo narrative and key messages before their working session to maximize efficiency.  
    - This update will help make demos more fluid and responsive to client concerns, supporting stronger conversions.  
    - Shane and Keenan plan to spend focused time, possibly over a weekend, to complete these tweaks.

## **Lead Engagement and Follow-up Strategy**

The team needs a clean communication process and targeted follow-up to convert warm leads into demos and sales.

- **Keenan is holding off on outreach until onboarding and demo updates are live to present a unified message** (13:47)  
    - A recent demo lead paused engagement due to staffing issues, showing the importance of timing and support readiness.  
    - Keenan plans to follow up with stalled leads early next week to maintain momentum.  
    - Shane highlighted the need to move prospects from top-of-funnel interest (clicks and visits) to bottom-of-funnel engagement with demos.  
    - The team has a spreadsheet tracking lead activity, which will be used to prioritize outreach once messaging is refined.

## **Marketing Spend and Website Analytics**

Optimizing ad spend and monitoring website behavior will focus resources on channels with the best ROI.

- **Paid ads on LinkedIn have become costly, with cost per click rising to about $60, prompting a review of budget allocation** (18:46)  
    - Natalie will consult the paid media specialist to analyze this trend and recommend adjustments.  
    - Shane emphasized directing spend toward email-driven traffic, which produces higher engagement at lower cost.  
    - The team recognizes the need to be careful stewards of the $1,000 budget for paid media.

- **Website analytics show users are researching more but hesitating to take contact actions, highlighting conversion gaps** (24:27)  
    - Visits to the Contact Us form have declined during the holiday period, suggesting visitors consume info but delay inquiries.  
    - Traffic sources include ABM emails and direct visits, indicating both campaign effectiveness and organic interest.  
    - This pattern reinforces the need for clear onboarding messaging and a strong demo to nudge visitors to engage.  

## **Operational and Access Challenges**

Resolving access to internal systems and clarifying role expectations remain ongoing operational priorities.

- **Shane is currently unable to access the portal due to account issues, with a potential solution of deleting and re-adding his account being explored** (23:10)  
    - Natalie will check with Colin and provide an update early next week.  
    - This access is important for Shane to continue supporting sales and marketing operations.

- **Keenan’s new role lacks clear weekly structure due to holidays and incomplete onboarding, delaying full productivity** (16:11)  
    - Once the demo, onboarding, and LinkedIn outreach are set, he expects to better define his weekly activities and potentially use calendaring tools like Calendly.  
    - This clarity will improve time management and responsiveness for client interactions.',
  '2026-01-08 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Discuss LinkedIn account options with Brad and decide by next Monday (07:53)","completed":false},{"text":"Send onboarding package content to Natalie by tomorrow for website integration (09:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Compose and email the demo talk track narrative to Shane for system alignment (18:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with demo client after New Year for engagement continuation (20:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Integrate the onboarding package content into website pages and provide copy for Keenan’s review (04:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Send a brief explanatory paragraph about LinkedIn account connection benefits and requirements for Keenan and Brad (10:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Investigate paid media campaign cost rise with paid media specialist and report findings/recommendations (19:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Colin to resolve Shane’s portal access issue and update him early next week (23:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Support Keenan to update the demo system based on talk track narrative, expecting about one hour of work (17:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist with LinkedIn outreach options and backup plans for account usage (08:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and advise on marketing effectiveness and funnel progression (00:00)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
