    '{"id":"01KE4R0W33605Y1KNBM1P1Q1Y5","title":"Ricoh // New North: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Branding and Visual Assets Refinement**\n\nThe team is finalizing visual assets with minor adjustments to improve usability and brand consistency.\n\n- **Roz confirmed the logo issues are minor and fixable, with most visuals ready for flexible use across templates** (00:00)  \n    - Images featuring mail batches are intended for postal optimization contexts, not detailed traceability use, per Roz’s explanation.  \n    - Linnea emphasized the importance of realistic use cases, noting that commercial printers would avoid leaving mail haphazardly in offices.  \n    - Roz clarified that images will be edited and cropped to avoid clutter and maintain professionalism in final layouts.  \n    - The visuals are mostly lifestyle shots rather than raw, unedited images, supporting broader brand storytelling.\n\n- **Color consistency issues in the Process Director brochure were identified as a file transfer glitch, prompting a new file-sharing approach** (03:59)  \n    - Roz and Lou traced the red color skew to transferring via Google platforms and are moving to a dedicated transfer folder to avoid this.  \n    - Natalie will upload files directly to the folder once Lou is granted access, aiming to stabilize color integrity before final reviews.  \n    - Kevin has already expressed satisfaction with the brochure’s current look, supporting continued minor content polishing.  \n    - Roz plans to send the Process Director battle card next for template clean-up, with sales guide updates forthcoming.\n\n- **Linnea and Roz confirmed a unified new look and feel across all sales and marketing assets** (16:49)  \n    - Info Print Manager will debut the new visual style shortly, with content currently under review by Vishnu.  \n    - PowerPoints and battle cards have been combined or updated to reduce redundant materials and streamline sales messaging.  \n    - This consolidation aims to improve sales team usability and reduce cognitive load, a priority to Roz to \"not lose her mind.\"\n\n- **A request to refresh and improve customer event visuals for Latin America is underway, with design support offered by Roz’s team** (34:20)  \n    - Linnea shared concerns about brand color adherence and readability challenges in current graphics lifted from US assets.  \n    - Roz confirmed the team can rework colors and backgrounds for better clarity and printing efficiency once original files arrive.  \n    - The deliverable includes redesigned banner images and potentially agenda templates with adjusted saturation to avoid over-inking in print.  \n    - This work is planned as a quick turnaround to maintain brand standards and enhance regional event presentation.\n\n## **Video Content Strategy and Localization Challenges**\n\nVideo updates focus on streamlining messaging and improving global usability by removing embedded text.\n\n- **Roz decided to remove on-screen text and icons from the Optimizer solution overview video to simplify localization** (08:25)  \n    - The embedded English text conflicted with voiceover, complicating translation for global markets like Italy and Germany.  \n    - Roz prefers voiceover with subtitles as a more flexible approach to multilingual video content.  \n    - Linnea requested visuals still convey key steps without text for viewers watching without sound; Roz confirmed GUI animations will suffice.  \n    - This shift reflects a strategy to reduce localization costs and improve video adaptability.\n\n- **Video refreshes include updated intros, hardware shots, and refined transitions to modernize the solution suite’s presentation** (14:09)  \n    - Roz integrated VC80000 Ricoh hardware footage to enhance authenticity and product recognition.  \n    - The team plans similar updates for Info Print Manager and RPD once new GUIs are ready, awaiting Miriam’s design changes.  \n    - The new video style aligns with updated PowerPoint and brochure templates, creating a consistent brand story across media.  \n    - Roz praised the animation work done by the creative team and requested minor timing adjustments to key transitions for clarity.\n\n- **Natalie and Lou will continue refining the video content and testing file transfers using the new folder system** (16:36)  \n    - The goal is to finalize videos quickly and ensure color and content integrity across platforms.  \n    - Roz will grant Lou access to the transfer folder to streamline file sharing and reduce technical glitches disrupting workflows.  \n    - Creative Cloud was proposed as an alternative transfer method if issues persist, reflecting openness to new tools improving collaboration.  \n    - This process improvement is designed to speed up final approvals and reduce technical frustrations.\n\n## **Learning Management System (LMS) and Training Content Development**\n\nThe team is expanding internal and customer-facing training with a focus on scalability and resource efficiency.\n\n- **Linnea outlined a strategic shift to increase customer-facing training amid limited internal bandwidth** (18:09)  \n    - Internal sales classes have been built using existing beautiful assets, but now there is pressure to replicate for customers.  \n    - Two separate portals (internal and customer) now exist, improving usability and branding for each audience.  \n    - Linnea seeks collaboration to speed up content creation without reinventing the wheel, balancing quality and resource limits.  \n    - Roz acknowledged the time-intensive nature of video editing and content polishing, highlighting a need for additional help.\n\n- **Roz demonstrated the customer-facing Learn Upon portal, showcasing video libraries and course catalog features** (23:08)  \n    - The portal supports tracking completed courses and offers resources, which aligns with Linnea’s vision of a holistic learning center.  \n    - Course content includes scripted and edited videos distilled from longer technical recordings, ensuring clarity and accessibility.  \n    - Natalie confirmed the ability to create standardized templates and intros to streamline future video productions and maintain brand consistency.  \n    - Roz suggested partial delegation of editing tasks, such as adding intros and polishing transitions, to alleviate workload.\n\n- **The team discussed potential outsourcing of voiceover recording to speed production and improve quality** (30:19)  \n    - Roz shared experience with AI text-to-speech tools but acknowledged human voiceovers remain time-consuming yet valuable.  \n    - Natalie offered support via podcast production experience to hire voice talent and stitch scripts with recordings, reducing Roz’s burden.  \n    - Linnea emphasized the importance of planning for increased training content demand and exploring scalable workflows.  \n    - Roz and Natalie agreed to collaborate on workflow optimization, balancing content creation speed with quality.\n\n- **Additional design tasks for admin workshop assets are underway, with Roz’s team ready to assist** (32:22)  \n    - Linnea proposed quick banner image edits, which Roz confirmed are nearly complete and can extend to other collateral like notebooks.  \n    - Vector files for hero images now exist, enabling flexibility in resizing and repurposing across formats.  \n    - The team aims to maintain visual cohesion and brand alignment across all training and marketing materials.  \n    - This approach supports a more integrated go-to-market strategy using consistent assets.\n\n## **Customer Engagement Data Management Exploration**\n\nThe group explored options for securely managing customer discovery data outside traditional CRMs.\n\n- **Linnea introduced a current challenge: capturing and managing 30-minute customer discovery calls data efficiently** (40:51)  \n    - The US team collects structured info pre-briefing but lacks a dynamic, shared tool that integrates with CRM systems.  \n    - Salespeople often use Excel, but this creates data silos and lacks real-time updates, posing risks to accuracy.  \n    - Linnea sought suggestions for a secure, accessible system permitting controlled data entry and dynamic updates.  \n    - Roz ruled out Creative Cloud for this use, citing its design focus and lack of data management features.\n\n- **Potential platforms discussed included SharePoint, Confluence, Insight360, and Microsoft tools, each with limitations** (42:29)  \n    - Confluence is restricted to limited users, conflicting with the need for wide seller access.  \n    - Insight360, an internal customer engagement tool, currently lacks external or broader integration for this purpose.  \n    - Microsoft To Do and similar apps were considered but may not align with needs beyond task management.  \n    - Roz cautioned against Asana due to potential overload and lack of data governance controls.\n\n- **The team agreed further research is needed, with Natalie offering to assist in exploring suitable tools** (43:11)  \n    - Linnea emphasized urgency but stressed the solution should avoid portal stagnation and manual replacements.  \n    - Roz highlighted data security and access control as critical factors for selecting any platform.  \n    - The ongoing dialogue reflects a strategic focus on improving sales and customer data workflows to increase efficiency.  \n    - This initiative aims to support sales readiness and customer engagement quality without adding complexity.\n\n## **Process and File Management Improvements**\n\nFile transfer and collaboration processes are being optimized to reduce technical issues and improve efficiency.\n\n- **The current file transfer issues causing color shifts in marketing materials are attributed to Google platform glitches** (04:08)  \n    - Roz and Lou tested multiple export approaches, confirming the need to avoid Google Docs or Drive for final files.  \n    - Moving to a dedicated transfer folder with direct designer access aims to prevent file corruption and color skew.  \n    - Natalie will coordinate testing of files once Lou is added to the folder, targeting stable workflows.  \n    - Creative Cloud was identified as a possible alternative, pending further evaluation.\n\n- **Roz and Linnea highlighted internal file sharing practices favoring Teams and SharePoint for design collaboration** (40:20)  \n    - The team is open to adopting new tools if they reduce confusion and improve version control.  \n    - Roz’s preference for Microsoft environments reflects existing infrastructure alignment and user familiarity.  \n    - The focus is on minimizing friction points that delay approvals and cause repeated work.  \n    - Effective file management is seen as foundational to maintaining brand quality and accelerating deliverables.\n\n- **Efforts to integrate vector files for hero images across collateral will simplify asset reuse and reduce production time** (33:29)  \n    - The team encountered challenges with certain images (e.g., Info Print Manager) that delayed design progress.  \n    - Converting key images to vector format enables scaling without quality loss and supports diverse output formats.  \n    - This technical upgrade reflects a commitment to long-term efficiency and brand consistency.  \n    - Roz plans to leverage this capability to extend branding elements across multiple platforms and media.\n\n## **Team Collaboration and Support**\n\nThe meeting reinforced strong inter-team collaboration with shared responsibilities and resource planning.\n\n- **Roz expressed appreciation for the creative team’s work and encouraged continued support in editing and voiceover tasks** (16:34)  \n    - She welcomed offers to delegate polishing steps to alleviate workload for video and content finalization.  \n    - Linnea committed to planning and resource allocation to handle increasing content demands effectively.  \n    - Natalie offered professional podcast and voiceover services support, enhancing production quality.  \n    - This collaborative approach aims to sustain quality while scaling output efficiently.\n\n- **Linnea and Roz coordinated on upcoming deliverables and asset handoffs to maintain momentum** (39:24)  \n    - Key deliverables include updated videos, images, and brochures, shared through the new transfer folder system.  \n    - Roz will grant Lou access promptly to ensure smooth communication and file exchange.  \n    - The team agreed to monitor technical issues closely and pivot file sharing methods as needed.  \n    - Clear communication and accountability were emphasized to keep projects on track.\n\n- **Team members shared informal appreciation and morale boosters, reflecting a positive working culture** (46:18)  \n    - Linnea thanked Colin for branded swag, reinforcing team identity and motivation.  \n    - Roz encouraged open communication, inviting colleagues to reach out with questions or support needs.  \n    - The friendly tone and mutual respect support ongoing collaboration despite workload pressures.  \n    - This cultural strength underpins the team’s ability to adapt and deliver high-quality results.","outline":null,"keywords":["Process Director","LearnUpon","Video Production","File Transfer","Customer Training","VIP Event Graphics"],"overview":"- **Visual Assets Finalization:** Team is making minor adjustments to visuals for usability and brand consistency across templates.  \n- **Color Consistency Fixes:** New file-sharing approach will improve color integrity after glitches were traced to Google platforms.  \n- **Unified Sales Assets:** All sales materials will adopt a new look to improve usability and streamline messaging for the sales team.  \n- **Video Content Refresh:** Simplifying videos by removing on-screen text will enhance localization and reduce expenses across global markets.  \n- **Training Content Expansion:** Focus on customer-facing training with potential outsourcing options for voiceover recording to speed production.  \n- **Data Management Solutions:** Discussions ongoing to find a secure tool for managing customer discovery call data outside traditional CRMs.","action_items":"\n**Roz Regan**\nAdd Lou Bogani to the transfer folder to improve direct file sharing and solve color skew issues for brochure (05:00)\nContinue internal review and finalize the Process Director brochure content with Lisa and Linnea (06:00)\nSend Process Director battle card to the team to clean up template and content placement by next day (07:00)\nReview and finalize Optimizer video removing English text overlays, ensure voiceover and visuals support global usage (08:00)\nCheck and confirm font type (Frutiger) on video titles and coordinate slowing balloon transitions for better visibility (13:00)\nAwait updated Predictive Insight GUI from Miriam for video development (15:00)\nShare LearnUpon portal overview and discuss access options with Linnea and Natalie to explore editing support (23:00)\nFinalize admin workshop email banner and consider extending design across collateral using vector files (32:00)\nAssist in redesigning VIP event graphics for Latin America branding once original files are received (37:00)\nPrepare and share updated video, images, and brochure via new transfer folder and coordinate Creative Cloud fallback (39:00)\nCollaborate with Natalie and Linnea to explore feasible tools/platforms for customer discovery data sharing, avoiding spreadsheet chaos (40:00)\n\n**Linnea Wolken**\nProvide original VIP event graphics and agenda template to Roz for redesign (36:00)\nCoordinate follow-up with Roger and CEC team on Insight360 tool and CRM limitations related to customer discovery data entry (40:00)\nShare further details about customer and internal class training requirements and strategic alignment with marketing assets (18:00)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nAssist in uploading fixed brochure files to transfer folder and coordinate test uploads (06:00)\nSupport voiceover hiring and audio editing for internal training videos (32:00)\nConduct research on suitable platforms for locked-down customer data sharing (43:00)\n\n**Lou Bogani**\nAccept transfer folder access and download finalized brochure files (06:00)\nSupport design team with recoloring VIP event graphics (36:00)\n"},"duration":48.0099983215332,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Roz"},{"id":1,"name":"Roz"},{"id":2,"name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"id":3,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":4,"name":"Lou Bogani"}],"sentences":[{"text":"From the last round, just the logo was a bit weird and I know it''s kind of part of that AI generation thing, so I felt that that could be addressed pretty quickly.","index":0,"end_time":9.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But otherwise I thought these were workable in a variety of different places, depending on what we''re talking about, of course.","index":1,"end_time":18.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.52,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":2,"end_time":18.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.56,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But yeah, and I, I, yeah, I.","index":3,"end_time":22.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Test drove a couple of them in the template and they look just fine.","index":4,"end_time":25.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, so just a few alterations and I think we''ll be good here with this.","index":5,"end_time":30,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25.52,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":6,"end_time":30.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, Roz, just a quick comment on this one.","index":7,"end_time":33.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":30.88,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"So if this is for rpd, I think you said, my only concern is like one of the key things we talk about RPD is traceability, trackability.","index":8,"end_time":41.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":33.2,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"And to see a bunch of mail just, you know, and I don''t know if they''re printed or what they are, but immediately I was worried about, you know, that, that kind of mindset they have where it isn''t something that just sits on someone''s desk.","index":9,"end_time":55.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":41.599,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"But.","index":10,"end_time":55.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":55.08,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Right.","index":11,"end_time":56.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.04,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So this case.","index":12,"end_time":57.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.28,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So, yeah, so this is something that we could crop or not.","index":13,"end_time":62.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I was thinking more along the lines of postal, like optimization.","index":14,"end_time":67.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So you, you have like these large pieces of, of, you know, of large postal.","index":15,"end_time":74.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I don''t know what you call them.","index":16,"end_time":75.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Batches, if you will, for lack of a better word, going out the door.","index":17,"end_time":79.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So that''s kind of where I was going with this one.","index":18,"end_time":83.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.92,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But honestly, I think I would be using this more in a perspective so you wouldn''t see as much.","index":19,"end_time":89.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So these are pretty, these images are pretty raw for what we would use them for.","index":20,"end_time":92.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":89.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"There''s definitely like editing involved when.","index":21,"end_time":95.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.94,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Because I was thinking, like, I''ve been in the printer where they might have a desk like this, but it''s in a warehouse situation.","index":22,"end_time":102.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.9,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"So they''re taking things to put into the mail versus having them on someone''s desk in an office.","index":23,"end_time":108.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":102.74,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"So I''m just letting you know, my.","index":24,"end_time":110.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.58,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Thought process, it''s all tracing a thing.","index":25,"end_time":112.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":110.1,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know how you''d image, you know, the piece level, trackability, linear, which is, I know where you''re, I.","index":26,"end_time":120.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.25,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Think where you''re going need to be that.","index":27,"end_time":122.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":120.53,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"It''s just again, people wouldn''t take envelopes like RPD people, commercial printers.","index":28,"end_time":127.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.53,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Yeah, all the time.","index":29,"end_time":128.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127.09,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"But like, for things that are regulated and things like that, I just don''t.","index":30,"end_time":134.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":128.69,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Wouldn''t see this happening.","index":31,"end_time":136.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":134.69,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"But just again, it''s the use.","index":32,"end_time":137.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.13,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"If you zoom in, that''s fine too.","index":33,"end_time":139.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.85,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, it''s more the, it''s more the use of the thing.","index":34,"end_time":143.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.29,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We went more with lifestyle shots on this as well.","index":35,"end_time":147.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.03,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And there was really just a few of them that kind of show a desk with a.","index":36,"end_time":151.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"You know, with this on it.","index":37,"end_time":152.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.31,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Natalie, if you could go down to that one, that.","index":38,"end_time":155.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.23,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"That I think the desk setting one right below.","index":39,"end_time":157.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.19,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, that one right there.","index":40,"end_time":159.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.63,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Like something like this, we would use maybe a little bit bigger where it shows, like, you know, stuff on a desk with that up on it.","index":41,"end_time":166.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.47,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We did something similar, I want to say, with.","index":42,"end_time":169.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.58,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"I think it was Optimizer, where we did a similar kind of image.","index":43,"end_time":172.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But again, I use this one as an example on one of the.","index":44,"end_time":176.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.14,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It doesn''t bother me because, again, not having just male haphazardly sitting around.","index":45,"end_time":184.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.46,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":46,"end_time":185.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":184.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And even with this one, I was using it in the template, like our PowerPoint template, and I was cropping it a little bit as well.","index":47,"end_time":191.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, as much.","index":48,"end_time":193.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.54,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So when we.","index":49,"end_time":194.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.74,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, just when we do these, we try to give them a bit of breathing space so that cropping can happen and, you know, so you don''t have, like, things overlapping because, you know, like.","index":50,"end_time":203.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.78,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"On our paper, like.","index":51,"end_time":205.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.92,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Oh, my gosh.","index":52,"end_time":205.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.24,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":53,"end_time":207.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":206.36,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"No, so I was thinking more like design elements overlapping so they don''t get.","index":54,"end_time":212.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.64,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"It doesn''t get too busy.","index":55,"end_time":213.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.08,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So.","index":56,"end_time":213.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.4,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, totally.","index":57,"end_time":214.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":213.72,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":214.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Take them with a.","index":59,"end_time":215.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.76,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"With a grain of salt.","index":60,"end_time":216.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.44,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"But we.","index":61,"end_time":216.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.32,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We rarely use them just as you see them.","index":62,"end_time":218.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.72,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"There''s usually some kind of editing involved, so a base, if you will.","index":63,"end_time":223.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.84,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"So anyways, yes, I think that these are coming along quite nicely.","index":64,"end_time":227.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.8,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Just like I said, there was a few little minor things that just needed to be cleaned up and I think.","index":65,"end_time":233.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.16,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"We''Ll be good to go on this.","index":66,"end_time":234.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.34,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":67,"end_time":236.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.98,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"Yeah, cool.","index":68,"end_time":238.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.42,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And then for the process director brochure.","index":69,"end_time":241.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":239.7,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is the one that you said sent back.","index":70,"end_time":244.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":242.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And the grays were okay, but the reds were skewed.","index":71,"end_time":247.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know.","index":72,"end_time":248.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":247.78,"speaker_name":"Linnea Wolken"},{"text":"It was so weird.","index":73,"end_time":249.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.26,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And they were.","index":74,"end_time":250.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.38,"speaker_name":"Roz"},{"text":"And they 