    '{"guillesantana","Colin Costigan","MaximilianRabeler","Colin Costigan","Axel Völker"}'::text[],
    1286,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KE098Y6FN6G6ZBHD9SMEKW9H","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Launch and Feedback**\n\nThe team agreed to finalize the ABM campaign and aimed to launch it next week, pending feedback on lists and email content.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan emphasized the goal to get the campaign live next week** and requested feedback on the email content, contact lists, and ABM plan to avoid delays (07:49).  \n    - The email sequence is currently only in English but will be translated into German after message approval, as Axel Völker confirmed (10:17).  \n    - Colin proposed building the landing page after email content is locked, including a dropdown for users to specify interest areas like RFPs or skills management, to gather actionable insights (18:58).  \n    - Ads copy and designs are nearing completion and will be shared the same day for review (20:30).  \n    - Max Rabeler will begin reviewing materials immediately, with Axel aiming to provide feedback by early next week to stick to the timeline (20:48).\n\n- **Max Rabeler and Axel Völker identified issues with the contact lists and segmentation** that needed addressing before launch (08:20).  \n    - Max found some companies incorrectly classified as IT services or consulting, recommending removal of non-relevant firms to sharpen targeting (09:18).  \n    - The original CSV was hard to read, but Colin provided a cleaned Google Sheet version to improve review efficiency (08:38, 20:19).  \n    - Max suggested that the differentiation between German, Austrian, and Swiss targets might be overemphasized but agreed it was useful for potential compliance or policy segmentation (11:04).  \n    - Job titles appear aligned with decision-makers, but Max raised concern that skill and CV management roles were missing from buyer personas, which Axel acknowledged as a gap in current targeting (13:33).\n\n## **Target Audience and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team refined buyer personas and messaging to focus on the most relevant decision-makers and product features.  \n\n- **The ABM plan prioritizes resource management roles but lacks direct targeting for skill and CV management, a core pain point identified by Axel Völker** (13:14).  \n    - Colin explained that messaging references skill management but asked for any additional job titles to ensure complete filter coverage (14:01).  \n    - Max noted that the current personas mainly cover resource managers, operations leaders, and sales managers, but might miss roles involved in RFP and skills workflows (13:45).  \n    - Axel suggested sales operations and pre-sales roles could be relevant but cautioned against refocusing now, as the RFP feature is the least developed and lacks customer references (17:38).  \n    - The team discussed keeping RFP-related content in emails initially to gather market feedback but agreed to focus mainly on proven features like skills and resource management (18:44).\n\n- **Regional segmentation between Germany, Austria, and Switzerland was maintained for flexibility despite some overlap in audience traits** (11:47).  \n    - Colin noted that having this segmentation allows quick message adjustments if compliance or policy differences arise in these regions (12:08).  \n    - Max pointed out some of the cultural distinctions described may apply broadly across DACH countries but agreed it was helpful to remain prepared for differentiation (11:04).  \n    - The inclusion of Swiss companies like Abraxas, which focus heavily on public sector RFPs, was kept to address specific market segments (16:01).\n\n## **Product Feature Focus and Prioritization**\n\nThe group agreed to concentrate on established features and cautiously approach less mature offerings to optimize campaign impact.  \n\n- **Axel Völker stressed that the RFP feature is the least complete and lacks customer validation, recommending a primary focus on skills and resource management in marketing** (18:21).  \n    - The rationale is to avoid confusing prospects with incomplete solutions and to strengthen messaging around proven capabilities (18:37).  \n    - Colin supported this but suggested retaining RFP messaging initially to test customer interest and capture possible leads (18:44).  \n    - Offering a service interest dropdown on the landing page will provide direct feedback on customer priorities and help refine future messaging (18:58).  \n    - This phased approach balances market learning with resource allocation efficiency.\n\n## **Operational Readiness and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team identified key process adjustments to improve campaign execution and collaboration.  \n\n- **Max and Axel encountered issues with data formats and list management that slowed progress, prompting a move to Google Sheets for easier collaboration** (08:38, 20:19).  \n    - Max said the original CSV was hard to convert and read, making it difficult to review contacts and titles (08:38).  \n    - Colin responded by sharing a Google Sheet version to streamline updates and comments (20:19).  \n    - They agreed to handle company removals and title clarifications directly in Teams chat to keep the list clean and targeted (09:18).  \n    - Axel, being under the weather, delegated initial review to Max to maintain momentum and promised to catch up by early next week (20:48).\n\n- **The team planned a review and translation workflow for the email sequences to ensure language appropriateness and customer resonance** (10:17).  \n    - Axel and Max will verify the English messages for tone and relevance before translating to German (10:28).  \n    - This two-step review aims to reduce rework and accelerate campaign launch (10:39).  \n    - Colin highlighted that capturing localized messaging nuances will support better engagement in DACH markets (11:47).  \n    - The process reflects a balance of speed and quality given resource constraints.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe campaign is poised to launch next week, contingent on feedback and final adjustments.  \n\n- **Colin set a clear deadline to finalize the campaign by the following week to capitalize on market timing and internal resource availability** (07:49).  \n    - Immediate feedback on email content, contact lists, and ads is required to avoid delays (07:49).  \n    - Max will start reviewing materials promptly, with Axel aiming to complete his review by early next week despite illness (20:48).  \n    - Ads and design assets will be sent out the same day for review, keeping all collateral aligned (20:30).  \n    - The team agreed to monitor campaign response closely and adjust messaging or targeting as needed based on early results (18:44).\n\n- **Colin’s presence at a leadership meeting during the call underscores campaign priority and alignment with broader business goals** (04:03).  \n    - The campaign reflects a strategic push to engage resource management buyers with proven product features (07:49).  \n    - The inclusion of a feedback mechanism on the landing page aims to inform ongoing product marketing and development priorities (18:58).  \n    - The team’s collaborative approach balances speed with accuracy to maximize launch impact.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","contact lists","email content","resource management","RFP targeting","regional segmentation"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Launch:** Finalize and launch ABM campaign next week, pending feedback on email content and contact lists.\n\n- **Email and Translation:** Email sequence only in English; will translate to German after approval to ensure clarity.\n\n- **Target Audience Issues:** Review and correct contact lists; focus on relevant decision-makers and job titles for better targeting.\n\n- **Prioritize Features:** Focus on skills and resource management in marketing; RFP feature remains less developed and lacks validation.\n\n- **Collaboration Improvements:** Shift to Google Sheets for easier management; streamline feedback process to enhance campaign execution.\n\n- **Launch Timeline:** Clear deadline set for next week; monitor initial responses closely for potential adjustments in messaging.","action_items":"\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview the updated IT services and consulting contact lists, suggest companies to exclude, and provide comments in Teams chat (09:18)\nReview ABM email sequence and campaign plan documents for customer resonance and feedback over the weekend (10:39)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nReview email content, ABM plan, and contact list materials, despite current health issues, aiming for feedback availability early next week (07:14)\nEvaluate the inclusion of RFP messaging in campaigns based on potential client inquiries and internal readiness (18:44)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare ad copy and design materials once finalized to support the campaign launch (20:30)\nMonitor Wi-Fi and connection stability during meetings due to current hotel location (07:49)\nConsolidate feedback from the team, update lists and email content accordingly for campaign readiness (09:23)\n\n**General Team**\nCoordinate translations of finalized email content into German for effective regional outreach (10:17)\nBuild landing page with options for prospect interest selection to gather insights on service focus areas (18:58)\n"},"duration":21.43000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"guillesantana"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Axel Völker"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Morning.","index":0,"end_time":217.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.44,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":219.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw your message about Noetic.","index":2,"end_time":222.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.56,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I''ll take a look.","index":3,"end_time":224.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.64,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":4,"end_time":225.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":5,"end_time":225.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would, but I have.","index":6,"end_time":228.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After this I''m going back into the leadership meeting.","index":7,"end_time":232.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":8,"end_time":233.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":232.83,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Are you in a hotel right now?","index":9,"end_time":234.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.43,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I am right now, yeah.","index":10,"end_time":236.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I thought it was close to you.","index":11,"end_time":239.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":237.71,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"It''s like two and a half hours.","index":12,"end_time":242.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":13,"end_time":243.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.67,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"But it''s a.","index":14,"end_time":244.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a two day, so.","index":15,"end_time":245.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":16,"end_time":248.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.03,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Hey, Max.","index":17,"end_time":249.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":18,"end_time":250.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s quite snowy outside.","index":19,"end_time":253.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.23,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":20,"end_time":255.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No public transports are available here.","index":21,"end_time":258.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.79,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"How''s your week been?","index":22,"end_time":262.649,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.849,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it was very cold actually here, but.","index":23,"end_time":267.689,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.329,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Good morning, gia.","index":24,"end_time":291.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Morning.","index":25,"end_time":293.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.52,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"It.","index":26,"end_time":309.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, you know if the rest of.","index":27,"end_time":350.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your team is joining or.","index":28,"end_time":351.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":350.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is writing some tease messages?","index":29,"end_time":356.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.54,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Tina.","index":30,"end_time":361.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.75,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":31,"end_time":411.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":32,"end_time":412.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":33,"end_time":434.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":434.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, Axel.","index":34,"end_time":436.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":35,"end_time":436.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going okay.","index":36,"end_time":438.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":437.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Are you busy?","index":37,"end_time":442.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.38,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m a bit sick actually.","index":38,"end_time":445.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":443.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I''m at home.","index":39,"end_time":447.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":446.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I understand that feeling.","index":40,"end_time":450.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like I can''t shake whatever''s going around.","index":41,"end_time":452.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So how is it right on your side?","index":42,"end_time":457.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":455.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, things are good.","index":43,"end_time":460.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, did you know was Patina joining or.","index":44,"end_time":463.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":461.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can go ahead and get started.","index":45,"end_time":465.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":464.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we can get started.","index":46,"end_time":469.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":47,"end_time":470.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":469.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"By the way, I''m in a hotel.","index":48,"end_time":472.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":471.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right now, so if my wi fi messes up, I will try to get back as soon as possible.","index":49,"end_time":476.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, really just wanted to go over any feedback you guys had on the lists, the email content, the ABM plan itself.","index":50,"end_time":485.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":476.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s any feedback there would like to chat through it.","index":51,"end_time":488.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":486.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I want to get this campaign live next week.","index":52,"end_time":490.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":492.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":492.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t managed to look at it yet.","index":54,"end_time":496.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":493.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":55,"end_time":497.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Max, have you looked at it or Bettina?","index":56,"end_time":499.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":497.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":57,"end_time":499.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":499.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This IT services list somehow came up yesterday evening.","index":58,"end_time":503.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.55,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":59,"end_time":503.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.55,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I. I was a bit surprised when you asked for that in the teams chat and I just figured out a few minutes ago where it lays.","index":60,"end_time":513.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":504.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Well, I''d sent.","index":61,"end_time":516.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was a CSV file but I could not transform that into a table.","index":62,"end_time":522.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":518.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it was hard to read.","index":63,"end_time":523.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":522.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because when I looked into the chat mind and open the campaign thing.","index":64,"end_time":530.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.96,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":65,"end_time":532.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.96,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It got added yesterday evening.","index":66,"end_time":534.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.44,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, I sent that about a week ago.","index":67,"end_time":538.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have to.","index":68,"end_time":540.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I did not have a look into this IT services document, but for the IT consulting I have a few companies to take out.","index":69,"end_time":553.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.52,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay, now should I can just paste them?","index":70,"end_time":557.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, you just put those in teams.","index":71,"end_time":560.199,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can easily remove them.","index":72,"end_time":562.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.199,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So wait, So it''s mainly.","index":73,"end_time":569.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.04,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"There are a few clients which are already clients and a few companies which are just too far away from our.","index":74,"end_time":580.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":75,"end_time":583.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":76,"end_time":584.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":583.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For example, the two is a streaming platform, so it''s not it.","index":77,"end_time":590.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.71,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":78,"end_time":592.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wonder why they classify themselves as IT services and IT consulting.","index":79,"end_time":596.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay then for the, for the email sequence.","index":80,"end_time":600.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.27,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean I don''t know whether those texts are helpful or not.","index":81,"end_time":606.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I cannot, I do not have the knowledge for that.","index":82,"end_time":608.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.45,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I mean they are all in English obviously.","index":83,"end_time":611.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.21,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But do we plan to also translate them and send them in German?","index":84,"end_time":616.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":611.89,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll send them in German.","index":85,"end_time":618.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":617.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we have to check if the message is the right one and then we can translate them.","index":86,"end_time":624.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":618.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I have not found the time.","index":87,"end_time":627.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":624.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":88,"end_time":629.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":628.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I just know because that''s probably the best thing to do in my opinion.","index":89,"end_time":635.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.5,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":90,"end_time":639.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.46,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Maybe you can check with Max Inaugural also because I was actually sick all week or since Wednesday so I didn''t get a lot of stuff done.","index":91,"end_time":647.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":639.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I can take a look.","index":92,"end_time":650.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":649.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe over the weekend we can also.","index":93,"end_time":653.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":650.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe Max, you can take a look if that would resonate with our customers.","index":94,"end_time":660.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":656.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And check this.","index":95,"end_time":662.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":662.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Max Naga.","index":96,"end_time":663.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":662.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":97,"end_time":665.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":664.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":98,"end_time":666.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.17,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And for this, for the ABM campaign document.","index":99,"end_time":670.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.57,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean it''s clear most of it just few questions like there are some places where you distinguish between German, Austrian and Swiss people.","index":100,"end_time":684.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.89,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Is that somehow for just to.","index":101,"end_time":688.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":686.1,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"To give examples or is it actually planned to have any to distinguish regarding how you approach them?","index":102,"end_time":697.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Because I think maybe Swiss is a bit different because they''re not in the European Union.","index":103,"end_time":702.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But I think Germany and Austria there is not that much of a difference in my opinion.","index":104,"end_time":707.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.46,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":708.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":707.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So our research told us that most things are largely the same with those two audiences or with the three audiences in the docks region.","index":106,"end_time":714.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":708.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I like to have the differentiation so that if there is, let''s say there''s a compliance or a new policy or anything that comes out, we already have the ability to segment and change messages based on that location.","index":107,"end_time":727.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":108,"end_time":729.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":728.92,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, because let me just quickly find the example.","index":109,"end_time":733,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.56,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Here.","index":110,"end_time":741.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.92,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So you say German firms emphasize process, rigor and documentation completeness.","index":111,"end_time":746.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.72,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Austrian consultancies, value relationship continuity and proven track records.","index":112,"end_time":751.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":747.08,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think both is true for both countries.","index":113,"end_time":754.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.8,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Just gotcha.","index":114,"end_time":756.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.81,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":115,"end_time":757.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.97,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So yeah, I was just wondering whether there''s any.","index":116,"end_time":760.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.01,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And then regarding the target group or target people, buyer Personas.","index":117,"end_time":767.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.77,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"This is really resource management focused in my opinion.","index":118,"end_time":773.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.65,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"It''s always about stuffing directly or indirectly.","index":119,"end_time":778.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Is that.","index":120,"end_time":779.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.81,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean I wasn''t part of the.","index":121,"end_time":782.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.58,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Of the talks last year until mid of December.","index":122,"end_time":786.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.34,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So I don''t know what to discuss before is that.","index":123,"end_time":789.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.02,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean there is no RFP and there''s no skill CV management included.","index":124,"end_time":794.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.86,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, skill and CV management is what most people come to us first.","index":125,"end_time":802.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":794.66,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":803.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.9,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"And that''s why I''M wondering why there is no one in the target group.","index":127,"end_time":808.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.3,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I think there should be at least in the mails.","index":128,"end_time":810.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":808.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You mean?","index":129,"end_time":811.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":810.88,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean I''m referring to buyer Personas from the ABM plan document.","index":130,"end_time":818.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"That''s head of resource management, director of operations, delivery manager and sales management leaders.","index":131,"end_time":825.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.76,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":825.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":825.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With skill management, there''s typically not a person.","index":133,"end_time":829.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":825.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Isn''t that resource managers or HR people.","index":134,"end_time":835.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":830.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I don''t know from the Personas, I think maybe that''s okay.","index":135,"end_time":838.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":835.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But in the messaging we should have some good management.","index":136,"end_time":840.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":838.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, the messaging references it.","index":137,"end_time":842.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the.","index":138,"end_time":843.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":842.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that was a question that I brought up last Friday when I had sent over the list was if there were any other titles to add into the filters or if there was even any like.","index":139,"end_time":851.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I did add in some like German titles as well and that expanded the list a bit.","index":140,"end_time":855.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":851.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that''s why I was looking to see if there was anything else that you guys wanted to add in there for a title.","index":141,"end_time":859.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":855.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can check and haven''t read because the list was really hard to check.","index":142,"end_time":866.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":862.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This CSV.","index":143,"end_time":867.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":866.26,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think you sent that now as a spreadsheet, right?","index":144,"end_time":871.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":868.06,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":145,"end_time":872.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":871.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a Google sheet.","index":146,"end_time":873.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":872.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you checked that and updated it?","index":147,"end_time":877.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":876.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Max, sounds like you have looked at it.","index":148,"end_time":879.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":877.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sorry, you''re talking really quiet.","index":149,"end_time":883.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":879.98,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Have you looked at.","index":150,"end_time":889.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":888.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have you reviewed the list with the contacts?","index":151,"end_time":893.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":889.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":894.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":893.69,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":153,"end_time":894.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":894.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And you made some comments or something to that.","index":154,"end_time":896.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":894.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"List into the chat?","index":155,"end_time":899.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":898.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, mainly companies who can be taken out.","index":156,"end_time":903.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.93,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, I think for the job titles it was fine, I guess.","index":157,"end_time":911.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean, as far as I noticed, we are also looking for people who are able to make decisions in their companies.","index":158,"end_time":919.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.42,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So you have to target.","index":159,"end_time":921.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.74,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, which we can.","index":160,"end_time":924.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":923.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We wanted to also target the people that are feeling the pain the most so that we start the conversation within their firm and then give them resources about Desi Dollop.","index":161,"end_time":937.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":924.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So at least from what I know, it''s every.","index":162,"end_time":942.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.23,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Every usual company uses English subtitles.","index":163,"end_time":946.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.23,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":164,"end_time":948.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":947.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, most of them did.","index":165,"end_time":950.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But when I added in some German translations, it did expand the list a bit.","index":166,"end_time":954.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":950.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":167,"end_time":959.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":958.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":962.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.71,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Also I guess so buyer Personas.","index":169,"end_time":967.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":962.19,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"These are also the people we would target for RFP marketing.","index":170,"end_time":972.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.85,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Right.","index":171,"end_time":973.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.69,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Because in the.","index":172,"end_time":976.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":974.61,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"In the company''s list there''s Abraxas.","index":173,"end_time":978.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.33,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Alexis is a company we had already.","index":174,"end_time":982.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.45,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We already had contact to them a few times, I think last year, two years ago, I don''t know.","index":175,"end_time":988.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.37,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Bettina and I decided to keep them in the list because this targets different people than we did.","index":176,"end_time":995.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":990.08,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But they are like biggest depending on view.","index":177,"end_time":1001.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":996.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"But they are a Swiss company mainly for public things.","index":178,"end_time":1005.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.6,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"So RFP is a big thing for them and when we had demos with them they also tried to push that topic.","index":179,"end_time":1013.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.08,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Not so I''m not sure whether there''s any difference for RFP targeting.","index":180,"end_time":1024.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1013.68,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I''m not sure what you mean by RFP targeting.","index":181,"end_time":1029.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1027.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The buyer Personas.","index":182,"end_time":1032.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1031.45,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Is there any role?","index":183,"end_time":1038.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.09,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We are not targeting but which would be.","index":184,"end_time":1042.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.53,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"I mean Axel is mainly to you the question what do you think are the people in public companies which have the pain, which can make decisions?","index":185,"end_time":1057.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah, there are these functionality.","index":186,"end_time":1060.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1058.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we want to refocus on that now.","index":187,"end_time":1064.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1060.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s most.","index":188,"end_time":1064.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1064.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because there is.","index":189,"end_time":1067.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1064.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We''re not really an RP automation tool at the moment.","index":190,"end_time":1072.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1067.8,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s more skills.","index":191,"end_time":1074.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1073,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think it''s maybe sales pre sales people.","index":192,"end_time":1077,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1074.52,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I don''t know sales operations.","index":193,"end_time":1081.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1079.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"In the document.","index":194,"end_time":1086.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.4,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We also say we want to.","index":195,"end_time":1087.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.24,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We want to go to the market with this.","index":196,"end_time":1092.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1089.48,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Like we have three, three big.","index":197,"end_time":1096.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Let''s call it features.","index":198,"end_time":1097.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.31,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"We have scale, CD management, we have resource management, we have this RFP flow.","index":199,"end_time":1101.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1097.47,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Yeah but the RFP feature is not.","index":200,"end_time":1103.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1101.35,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is the least complete basically it''s not.","index":201,"end_time":1105.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1103.11,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We don''t have any references and I''m not sure if you want to.","index":202,"end_time":1108.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1105.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If that makes a lot of sense to focus on that or we should first go with what is established and proven and working.","index":203,"end_time":1116.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1108.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":204,"end_time":1117.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1117.35,"speaker_name":"MaximilianRabeler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":205,"end_time":1120.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1120.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you want to remove the RFP content from the emails.","index":206,"end_time":1123.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1120.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have to check.","index":207,"end_time":1125.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1124.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can try.","index":208,"end_time":1126.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1126.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I mean we can see if you get a lot of feedback on that.","index":209,"end_time":1130.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1126.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"We can just leave it in.","index":210,"end_time":1131.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1130.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s also an interesting learning.","index":211,"end_time":1133.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1131.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe you can leave it in and see if we get replies on that.","index":212,"end_time":1137.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1134.049,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":213,"end_time":1139.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1138.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was thinking about.","index":214,"end_time":1140.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1139.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once we get your feedback on the emails we can build the landing page just so we don''t waste any revision rounds there.","index":215,"end_time":1147.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1140.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I was even thinking about having a dropdown dedicated to like the.","index":216,"end_time":1151.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1147.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The thing that they''re most interested in as a service.","index":217,"end_time":1153.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we have kind of an.","index":218,"end_time":1155.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1154.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Indicator of like, are you looking to use this for RFPs, for skills management, for CV management, everything.","index":219,"end_time":1161.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so.","index":220,"end_time":1166.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll also be sending over ad copy and ad designs today.","index":221,"end_time":1170.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1166.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you''ve been under the weather so whenever you have a chance just take a look at the.","index":222,"end_time":1175.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1171.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The emails and everything in the chat or where''s.","index":223,"end_time":1178.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1175.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where''s the.","index":224,"end_time":1178.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1178.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I sent them in the chat last Friday.","index":225,"end_time":1181.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1179.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are in the SharePoint.","index":226,"end_time":1183.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1182.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll try to check that later.","index":227,"end_time":1187.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1184.74,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m actually going to check that.","index":228,"end_time":1188.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1187.54,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Once you have the other under Documents General and then the Doc ABM campaign.","index":229,"end_time":1199.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1193.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Folder I renamed One of the file names was too long for Excel to open, so I had to rename that, but somehow that copied it.","index":230,"end_time":1207.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1199.22,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So now the exact thing that.","index":231,"end_time":1208.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1207.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Twice.","index":232,"end_time":1209.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1208.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":233,"end_time":1210.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":234,"end_time":1210.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":235,"end_time":1211.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, the ABM plan.","index":236,"end_time":1213.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1211.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I have the email sequence and I have to Excel with the.","index":237,"end_time":1216.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1213.49,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s all I have.","index":238,"end_time":1218.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1217.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":1219.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I sent you the.","index":240,"end_time":1220.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Google Drive version because you were having issues with the CSV.","index":241,"end_time":1223.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1221.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s in our teams chat.","index":242,"end_time":1225.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":1226.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1226.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yes.","index":244,"end_time":1227.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1226.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But where''s the.","index":245,"end_time":1227.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1227.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where.","index":246,"end_time":1228.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1227.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where are the ads?","index":247,"end_time":1228.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1228.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which document that.","index":248,"end_time":1230.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1228.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''ll be sending those today.","index":249,"end_time":1231.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1230.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That.","index":250,"end_time":1231.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re.","index":251,"end_time":1231.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re just putting some finishing touches on the designs.","index":252,"end_time":1233.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":253,"end_time":1234.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1233.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":1235.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1234.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":255,"end_time":1237.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1236.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":256,"end_time":1240.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1240.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so once you guys are able to provide feedback there, then, I mean, we can make changes pretty quickly and.","index":257,"end_time":1245.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get this campaign live.","index":258,"end_time":1247.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1245.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, I''m a bit behind.","index":259,"end_time":1249.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1248.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe, Max, you can start reviewing it and give feedback and I''ll try to do that maybe by beginning of next week, but we can start next week.","index":260,"end_time":1258.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1249.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":261,"end_time":1261.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":262,"end_time":1263.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1261.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, that''s pretty much all from our side, so.","index":263,"end_time":1266.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1263.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Axel, I hope you feel better, Max.","index":264,"end_time":1269.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1266.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Weather warms up a little.","index":265,"end_time":1271.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1270.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":266,"end_time":1273.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1273.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great weekend, everyone.","index":267,"end_time":1277.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1275.959,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great chatting with you.","index":268,"end_time":1278.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1277.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You too.","index":269,"end_time":1278.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1278.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":270,"end_time":1279,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1278.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bye.","index":271,"end_time":1279.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1279.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2026-01-09T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com,rabeler@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KE098Y6FN6G6ZBHD9SMEKW9H","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.78,"bullets":["Colin requested feedback on email copy and contact lists to launch ABM campaign next week.","Team identified incorrect companies and suggested removals from IT consulting/contact lists.","Axel confirmed German emails are planned; translation pending due to illness and time constraints.","Discussion clarified inclusion of RFP content is tentative pending feedback and performance.","Ad copy and designs to be shared today; launch goal remains early next week."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''m a bit sick actually. So I''m at home.","speaker":"Axel Völker"},{"quote":"I want to get this campaign live next week.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We can try. I mean we can see if you get a lot of feedback on that.","speaker":"Axel Völker"}],"topics":["campaign","content","translation","targeting"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Launch and Feedback**\n\nThe team agreed to finalize the ABM campaign and aimed to launch it next week, pending feedback on lists and email content.  \n\n- **Colin Costigan emphasized the goal to get the campaign live next week** and requested feedback on the email content, contact lists, and ABM plan to avoid delays (07:49).  \n    - The email sequence is currently only in English but will be translated into German after message approval, as Axel Völker confirmed (10:17).  \n    - Colin proposed building the landing page after email content is locked, including a dropdown for users to specify interest areas like RFPs or skills management, to gather actionable insights (18:58).  \n    - Ads copy and designs are nearing completion and will be shared the same day for review (20:30).  \n    - Max Rabeler will begin reviewing materials immediately, with Axel aiming to provide feedback by early next week to stick to the timeline (20:48).\n\n- **Max Rabeler and Axel Völker identified issues with the contact lists and segmentation** that needed addressing before launch (08:20).  \n    - Max found some companies incorrectly classified as IT services or consulting, recommending removal of non-relevant firms to sharpen targeting (09:18).  \n    - The original CSV was hard to read, but Colin provided a cleaned Google Sheet version to improve review efficiency (08:38, 20:19).  \n    - Max suggested that the differentiation between German, Austrian, and Swiss targets might be overemphasized but agreed it was useful for potential compliance or policy segmentation (11:04).  \n    - Job titles appear aligned with decision-makers, but Max raised concern that skill and CV management roles were missing from buyer personas, which Axel acknowledged as a gap in current targeting (13:33).\n\n## **Target Audience and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team refined buyer personas and messaging to focus on the most relevant decision-makers and product features.  \n\n- **The ABM plan prioritizes resource management roles but lacks direct targeting for skill and CV management, a core pain point identified by Axel Völker** (13:14).  \n    - Colin explained that messaging references skill management but asked for any additional job titles to ensure complete filter coverage (14:01).  \n    - Max noted that the current personas mainly cover resource managers, operations leaders, and sales managers, but might miss roles involved in RFP and skills workflows (13:45).  \n    - Axel suggested sales operations and pre-sales roles could be relevant but cautioned against refocusing now, as the RFP feature is the least developed and lacks customer references (17:38).  \n    - The team discussed keeping RFP-related content in emails initially to gather market feedback but agreed to focus mainly on proven features like skills and resource management (18:44).\n\n- **Regional segmentation between Germany, Austria, and Switzerland was maintained for flexibility despite some overlap in audience traits** (11:47).  \n    - Colin noted that having this segmentation allows quick message adjustments if compliance or policy differences arise in these regions (12:08).  \n    - Max pointed out some of the cultural distinctions described may apply broadly across DACH countries but agreed it was helpful to remain prepared for differentiation (11:04).  \n    - The inclusion of Swiss companies like Abraxas, which focus heavily on public sector RFPs, was kept to address specific market segments (16:01).\n\n## **Product Feature Focus and Prioritization**\n\nThe group agreed to concentrate on established features and cautiously approach less mature offerings to optimize campaign impact.  \n\n- **Axel Völker stressed that the RFP feature is the least complete and lacks customer validation, recommending a primary focus on skills and resource management in marketing** (18:21).  \n    - The rationale is to avoid confusing prospects with incomplete solutions and to strengthen messaging around proven capabilities (18:37).  \n    - Colin supported this but suggested retaining RFP messaging initially to test customer interest and capture possible leads (18:44).  \n    - Offering a service interest dropdown on the landing page will provide direct feedback on customer priorities and help refine future messaging (18:58).  \n    - This phased approach balances market learning with resource allocation efficiency.\n\n## **Operational Readiness and Process Improvements**\n\nThe team identified key process adjustments to improve campaign execution and collaboration.  \n\n- **Max and Axel encountered issues with data formats and list management that slowed progress, prompting a move to Google Sheets for easier collaboration** (08:38, 20:19).  \n    - Max said the original CSV was hard to convert and read, making it difficult to review contacts and titles (08:38).  \n    - Colin responded by sharing a Google Sheet version to streamline updates and comments (20:19).  \n    - They agreed to handle company removals and title clarifications directly in Teams chat to keep the list clean and targeted (09:18).  \n    - Axel, being under the weather, delegated initial review to Max to maintain momentum and promised to catch up by early next week (20:48).\n\n- **The team planned a review and translation workflow for the email sequences to ensure language appropriateness and customer resonance** (10:17).  \n    - Axel and Max will verify the English messages for tone and relevance before translating to German (10:28).  \n    - This two-step review aims to reduce rework and accelerate campaign launch (10:39).  \n    - Colin highlighted that capturing localized messaging nuances will support better engagement in DACH markets (11:47).  \n    - The process reflects a balance of speed and quality given resource constraints.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe campaign is poised to launch next week, contingent on feedback and final adjustments.  \n\n- **Colin set a clear deadline to finalize the campaign by the following week to capitalize on market timing and internal resource availability** (07:49).  \n    - Immediate feedback on email content, contact lists, and ads is required to avoid delays (07:49).  \n    - Max will start reviewing materials promptly, with Axel aiming to complete his review by early next week despite illness (20:48).  \n    - Ads and design assets will be sent out the same day for review, keeping all collateral aligned (20:30).  \n    - The team agreed to monitor campaign response closely and adjust messaging or targeting as needed based on early results (18:44).\n\n- **Colin’s presence at a leadership meeting during the call underscores campaign priority and alignment with broader business goals** (04:03).  \n    - The campaign reflects a strategic push to engage resource management buyers with proven product features (07:49).  \n    - The inclusion of a feedback mechanism on the landing page aims to inform ongoing product marketing and development priorities (18:58).  \n    - The team’s collaborative approach balances speed with accuracy to maximize launch impact.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","contact lists","email content","resource management","RFP targeting","regional segmentation"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Launch:** Finalize and launch ABM campaign next week, pending feedback on email content and contact lists.\n\n- **Email and Translation:** Email sequence only in English; will translate to German after approval to ensure clarity.\n\n- **Target Audience Issues:** Review and correct contact lists; focus on relevant decision-makers and job titles for better targeting.\n\n- **Prioritize Features:** Focus on skills and resource management in marketing; RFP feature remains less developed and lacks validation.\n\n- **Collaboration Improvements:** Shift to Google Sheets for easier management; streamline feedback process to enhance campaign execution.\n\n- **Launch Timeline:** Clear deadline set for next week; monitor initial responses closely for potential adjustments in messaging.","action_items":"\n**Maximilian Rabeler**\nReview the updated IT services and consulting contact lists, suggest companies to exclude, and provide comments in Teams chat (09:18)\nReview ABM email sequence and campaign plan documents for customer resonance and feedback over the weekend (10:39)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nReview email content, ABM plan, and contact list materials, despite current health issues, aiming for feedback availability early next week (07:14)\nEvaluate the inclusion of RFP messaging in campaigns based on potential client inquiries and internal readiness (18:44)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare ad copy and design materials once finalized to support the campaign launch (20:30)\nMonitor Wi-Fi and connection stability during meetings due to current hotel location (07:49)\nConsolidate feedback from the team, update lists and email content accordingly for campaign readiness (09:23)\n\n**General Team**\nCoordinate translations of finalized email content into German for effective regional outreach (10:17)\nBuild landing page with options for prospect interest selection to gather insights on service focus areas (18:58)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7fd1061e-83ce-4318-92e0-33353a9af08b","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
