    '{"id":"01KEFG031W66M2WS5653CG29H5","title":"WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting 1/8/2026","summary":{"notes":"## **Landing Page and SEO Strategy**\n\nThe team confirmed that keyword-specific landing pages are driving better engagement and conversions than generic pages.\n\n- **The new AdRoll landing page generated its first conversion** and received **eight clicks across all creatives**, showing balanced performance among ads (07:55)  \n    - This validates focusing on keyword-specific pages over general contact pages to boost user interest  \n    - The team plans to continue creating landing pages targeting top keywords like **cross docking, pallet restacking, temporary warehousing, and lumber services**  \n    - This approach aligns with SEO goals to match user search intent and improve Google Ads efficiency  \n    - Success will be measured by conversion rates and lead quality on new pages  \n\n- **SEO optimization of existing pages is proposed to align content with Google Ads keywords**, enhancing organic search relevance (10:01)  \n    - Updating headlines and body text to reflect popular search terms can amplify visibility  \n    - Andrew has expressed interest in improving SEO, making this a priority for upcoming website updates  \n    - This strategy supports broader efforts to increase brand awareness and organic traffic  \n    - The team will evaluate which existing pages to prioritize based on keyword performance  \n\n## **Google Ads and Holiday Campaign Management**\n\nMaintaining steady ad spend and bidding during the holidays prevented competitor-driven cost spikes and preserved campaign efficiency.\n\n- **Google Ads delivered 12 leads this week at a cost per conversion of $15**, including a lead from the targeted geofenced Costco area, indicating strong local brand awareness (07:55)  \n    - Competitors often increase bids during holidays expecting others to cut back, but the team kept budgets steady to defend traffic share  \n    - This proactive approach prevented cost per lead increases and maintained stable traffic volumes  \n    - The geo-fenced lead searched directly for the brand name, showing top-of-mind recall from previous campaigns  \n    - This highlights the effectiveness of location-based ads in reinforcing brand presence  \n\n- **Holiday bid management ensured no cost inefficiencies despite competitive pressures**, with no observed traffic or CPL fluctuations (06:20)  \n    - The team continuously adjusted bids to avoid overspending during traditionally low volume periods  \n    - This vigilance supports sustained ROI through volatile seasonal market behavior  \n    - The approach demonstrates a strong competitive defense mindset in campaign operations  \n    - Maintaining spend levels rather than cutting budgets was key to this success  \n\n## **Geofencing and Targeting Expansion**\n\nExpanding geofencing to additional distribution hubs could further enhance localized targeting and lead generation.\n\n- **The team suggested targeting 3 to 5 additional major distribution hubs**, including competitors’ facilities or 3PL centers, to broaden geographic reach (10:01)  \n    - This approach aims to replicate success seen in the Costco area geofence campaign  \n    - Expanding location-based ads could increase brand exposure in key logistics clusters  \n    - The decision requires client input on whether to pursue this extended targeting  \n    - Such expansion would need careful budget and frequency management to avoid ad fatigue  \n\n- **Current geofencing campaigns have reached frequency caps**, necessitating new locations to maintain fresh impressions and avoid audience saturation (10:01)  \n    - This ensures ongoing engagement without diminishing returns from repetitive ads  \n    - The team will monitor frequency metrics closely before scaling  \n    - This tactic supports sustained lead flow from high-value geographic segments  \n    - It reflects a data-driven approach to audience management  \n\n## **Product and Event Planning**\n\nDecisions on swag items for the upcoming Women’s Conference are pending, with budget and minimum order constraints influencing choices.\n\n- **The team is leaning toward ordering purse hooks over travel kits** for swag, citing cost and minimum order size as key factors (13:08)  \n    - Travel kits were deemed too expensive and impractical given minimum order requirements of 100 units  \n    - Ordering 50 units was preferred but not feasible under current vendor policies  \n    - The purse hook offers a more cost-effective and suitable option for events  \n    - Final approval and design selection await client feedback to move forward  \n\n- **Planning for the Women’s Conference swag design and order should start promptly** to meet event timing in February (13:08)  \n    - Early decisions will enable timely production and delivery  \n    - The team commits to sharing pricing and sample options for client review  \n    - This effort supports brand presence and engagement at high-profile industry events  \n    - Coordination with the client ensures alignment on style and budget  \n\n## **Meeting Scheduling and Strategic Planning**\n\nAdjusting the meeting schedule aims to allow a more comprehensive discussion of yearly plans and priorities with key stakeholders.\n\n- **A longer meeting on January 22nd is proposed to review annual goals and focus areas with Don, Andy, and the client team** (14:31)  \n    - The preferred time shift to 10:30 AM is suggested to avoid conflict with accounting meetings  \n    - This session will cover strategic planning, resource allocation, and campaign priorities for the year  \n    - The extended format supports deeper alignment and decision-making among stakeholders  \n    - Scheduling flexibility reflects commitment to thorough planning and collaboration  \n\n- **Meeting coordination will be confirmed with Bailey and other participants to ensure attendance and agenda coverage** (14:31)  \n    - Clear communication and calendar management are priorities to avoid conflicts  \n    - This meeting is seen as critical for setting the tone and direction for upcoming initiatives  \n    - Follow-up emails will include questions and topics to prepare participants in advance  \n    - The team values this opportunity for open dialogue and comprehensive review","outline":null,"keywords":["Cross Docking","Lumber Services","Google Ads","Landing Pages","Geofencing","SEO Optimization"],"overview":"- **Landing Page Success:** New AdRoll landing page has driven eight clicks, confirming keyword-specific pages boost engagement and conversions.  \n- **SEO Strategy Update:** Optimization of existing pages to align with Google Ads keywords is a priority, aiming to increase organic visibility.  \n- **Google Ads Performance:** Ads produced 12 leads at $15 per conversion, maintaining cost efficiency despite holiday competition pressures.  \n- **Geofencing Expansion Proposal:** Targeting 3-5 new distribution hubs could enhance localized lead generation, pending client input on budget and frequency.  \n- **Swag Planning for Conference:** Team favors purse hooks over travel kits for cost-effectiveness; decisions need prompt approval before February event.  \n- **Extended Meeting Scheduling:** A longer meeting on January 22 is proposed for reviewing annual goals, requiring coordination for stakeholder attendance.","action_items":"\n**Nina Belina**\nSend email with all questions for client feedback regarding landing page content and potential new topics (14:53)\nCommunicate with stakeholders to confirm Women’s Conference swag item preferences and minimum order logistics (13:10)\nCoordinate with Bailey and team to confirm if 10:30 AM start for Jan 22 meeting is feasible and finalize scheduling (14:45)\n"},"duration":15.329999923706055,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi.","index":0,"end_time":12.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":13.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":12.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I hope you had a great holiday and a really nice beginning of the new year.","index":2,"end_time":21.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bailey is traveling today, so I''ll be the one to take you through the meeting and to tell you what we''ve been working on.","index":3,"end_time":31.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me share my screen just a little quick.","index":4,"end_time":35.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this time we will go through our general, general agenda, the project updates and what we''ve been working on and some things that we need your input on.","index":5,"end_time":58.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Our project updates are the Cross Docking versus Lumber services landing page.","index":6,"end_time":65.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I sent you the page by email a few weeks ago.","index":7,"end_time":71.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what we need from you is to tell us if you want anything changed or if you need that, if you think that something needs to be added or if it''s okay the way that it is and if it''s fine, we can add it to the resources page and then start working on a new landing page.","index":8,"end_time":90.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In regards to the keywords that we have currently in our Google Ads, for some other things that we''ve been doing during the month we had keyword landing, we had first lead from the landing page that we created for Adroll which was specifically dedicated to the keywords that we were bidding on Google Ads.","index":9,"end_time":125.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":90.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So keywords that were popular for our service, which means that it''s working really well and that people are responding more to having keyword specific landing page rather than just a general contact Us page.","index":10,"end_time":145.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For the holiday campaign management, we manage spend and bids during the holiday weeks to maintain efficiency.","index":11,"end_time":157.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Why this is important because sometimes during the holidays we notice that other companies and competitors tend to tend to bid on traffic so they raise their budgets to access more traffic traffic because they expect other companies to tone their budgets down.","index":12,"end_time":178.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":157.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We managed to avoid that and avoid being increasing any.","index":13,"end_time":185.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi Christine.","index":14,"end_time":192.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hello.","index":15,"end_time":196.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Did Andy ever make it in?","index":16,"end_time":198.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, I was just recording the meeting for him.","index":17,"end_time":201.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":199.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I can present it to you because I feel that will be a lot more natural.","index":18,"end_time":205.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":19,"end_time":206.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.219,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":208.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So let me start from the beginning.","index":21,"end_time":210.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":208.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just a moment.","index":22,"end_time":212.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for this week we went through all of the things that we''ve been working on in December and some of the things I already mentioned in the emails.","index":23,"end_time":224.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"While for some things that are more related to the holiday season when it comes to Google Ads and AdRoll.","index":24,"end_time":233.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for the cross docking versus lumper services we created the landing page and I sent you the document.","index":25,"end_time":241.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s mostly related to the SEO with either cross docking or Lamper services.","index":26,"end_time":249.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the keywords that people search when they search for we fixed fright or search for services that are related to VFX fright and most of the content is related to either cross docking or how to access different kinds of services.","index":27,"end_time":270.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What''s the difference what''s the difference between Lumber services and cross docking?","index":28,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because we notice that people sometimes aren''t sure what''s what and it will give us a better management of how we of our CPL and how we just rank in Google when it comes to people who are looking for these services.","index":29,"end_time":292.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"When you have time just go through the text and see if you think if anything needs to be changed or if it''s fine the way that is.","index":30,"end_time":303.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If it is and if it''s okay, then we will just add it to the resources page and then we can also work on other landing pages or just improving the SEOs on the ones that we we have on two other things we noticed that the new landing page for AdRoll, the one that we created that''s keyword specific that we used as a Contact us page for the AdRoll campaigns, generated its first conversion, which is great because it means that people are more interested in seeing something that relates to their search terms rather than just the regular contact us page.","index":31,"end_time":343.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And also it gives us a little bit more backing to, you know, just making it more keyword specific when it comes to the website for the holiday campaign management we managed to spend and the bids during the holiday weeks.","index":32,"end_time":358.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And as I mentioned previously, why this is important because sometimes we notice that during the holiday season companies usually kind of tone down, tone down their advertising because they don''t expect a lot of people to be thinking about services during the holidays and then competitors try to outbid the traffic during that time.","index":33,"end_time":380.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we were just making sure that none of this affects the efficiency of the campaigns and it worked really well.","index":34,"end_time":386.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not, we saw nothing, no, no new changes in traffic or costs per lead on that.","index":35,"end_time":394.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that went really well during the holidays for the Google Ads.","index":36,"end_time":400.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, hold on, hold on.","index":37,"end_time":401.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So did we advertise less during the holidays?","index":38,"end_time":404.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":402.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no, we didn''t.","index":39,"end_time":406.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But usually what happens is that competitors expect for other companies to, you know, spend a little bit less during the holidays and then they up their, their, their budgets for just to buy the traffic during the holidays.","index":40,"end_time":420.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is why we try to actively always manage the all the campaigns even during the holiday season and not just let them, you know, just, you know, stay as they are and think, oh, nothing will happen during the holidays.","index":41,"end_time":435.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So this is one, one of the.","index":42,"end_time":436.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Things during the holidays.","index":43,"end_time":438.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I just wanted to make sure.","index":44,"end_time":439.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no, we did nothing different from when from the budget perspective.","index":45,"end_time":444.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s just something that we need to kind of Be mindful of when it comes to competitors and people who try to outbid the traffic.","index":46,"end_time":453.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so for Google Ads, our conversion this week was 12 leads and the cost per conversions were $15.","index":47,"end_time":462.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We tracked a lead that was located in the same area as the Costco geo fenced area that we had for the other campaign.","index":48,"end_time":474.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And which means it''s really good that the location based ads are showing a really good brand list awareness segment because the person who was the lead from the geo fencing area searched for vfix right as the brand name.","index":49,"end_time":495.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So they didn''t search for a keyword, they actually searched for vfx right.","index":50,"end_time":500.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it means that it stayed top of mind from the geofencing campaigns which is really rate and then the top converting keywords were cross docking, pallet restacking and temporary warehousing and lumber services.","index":51,"end_time":514.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are some of the keywords that we can keep in mind for any additional landing pages.","index":52,"end_time":520.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For Agile we saw one conversion and as I said that one conversion came from the new landing page and eight clicks across all types of creative.","index":53,"end_time":531.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So all of the creatives were working really well.","index":54,"end_time":534.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There was no one creative that was better than the others and but it''s still the beginning of the year and hopefully this will all move even faster.","index":55,"end_time":546.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But as I said it''s really good to see that the new landing page is working really well when it comes to matching the keywords and the search terms that people are looking for.","index":56,"end_time":557.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Then for the emergency card Downloads we saw 19 downloads from December 7th to January 7th.","index":57,"end_time":564.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So which is really good during the holiday season and it''s somewhere in the average that we usually see during these months for data analytics and observations for the suggestions since I mentioned that the geofencing campaign stayed with people even after we reallocated budgets and managed it a little bit differently since as I said we we already kind of had the maximum frequency of which we were showing the same ads to the same people in the same area.","index":58,"end_time":601.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Something that can also be done is that we can potentially find three to five other major distribution hubs so for example either competitors of Costco or three PL centers and then geofence them next.","index":59,"end_time":615.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But that''s something for you to decide if it''s something that would interest you.","index":60,"end_time":619.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for SEO optimization, so similarly to how now we are writing landing pages that are relevant to the search terms that people are searching for, we can also do an SEO optimization of existing pages.","index":61,"end_time":634.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So to update update any headlines or body of landing pages to match the terms from our Google Ads more clearly, which is something also that we can do and you can think about it if it''s something that, that you''d find interesting because I know that Andrew mentioned that he''s interested in SEO and improving the website a little bit.","index":62,"end_time":657.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for the items that we are working on, we are exploring additional geofencing options for ads.","index":63,"end_time":664.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We are keeping with the Google Ad Optimization, as I mentioned previously, to watch out what competitors are doing and to keep an open eye on things and adjusting the daily spend to ensure that we are not neither overspending or underspending during the lower volume periods.","index":64,"end_time":686.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s.","index":65,"end_time":687.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That has to do with just the holiday, holiday period.","index":66,"end_time":693.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we have to keep in mind that there are competitors still active, but also that we keep our budget the way that it is during this time.","index":67,"end_time":701.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And for the new landing page suggestion, one of the keywords that sponsors track out with warehouse temp services.","index":68,"end_time":711.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s also one of the topics that we can write about.","index":69,"end_time":715.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But as I mentioned previously in one of the emails, I don''t know if you remember it, I sent some of the questions that if you could answer maybe from your sales calls or talking just to people who are interested in the service, what would be something that they mentioned they are interested in when it comes to freight services?","index":70,"end_time":737.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then maybe we can also write about that in any new pages.","index":71,"end_time":742.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":72,"end_time":745.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So yeah.","index":73,"end_time":746.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And items that need to review for the Women''s Conference swag, we since we''re in the month of January and I think that if I remember correctly it starts in February, it would be good to start working on the design for the SWAG items.","index":74,"end_time":765.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So sorry.","index":75,"end_time":768.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If you can look at the, the pricing and the, the items and choose which one do you prefer?","index":76,"end_time":775.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":768.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That would be great.","index":77,"end_time":776.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can start with this design.","index":78,"end_time":778.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":776.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, I''m not sure what we''re going to do about that because I''ve never really gotten an answer on that either.","index":79,"end_time":784.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I will put it in front of them and have them take a look at it.","index":80,"end_time":788.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m not sure what we''re gonna do that.","index":81,"end_time":791.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The designs look great though.","index":82,"end_time":792.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":83,"end_time":794.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because one of them is like a travel kit.","index":84,"end_time":796.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Another one is purse hook.","index":85,"end_time":798.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So whichever one, we''re not doing the travel kit.","index":86,"end_time":800.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''re definitely not doing that.","index":87,"end_time":802.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The purse hook would be the thing we''d go with if we''re going to do it.","index":88,"end_time":806.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know the travel kit was way too expensive.","index":89,"end_time":808.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''re just kind of looking at.","index":90,"end_time":810.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you know, because there''s a minimum order, I mean I would like to order just 50 of them, but I think you have to order 100.","index":91,"end_time":817.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":818.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or maybe, you know, to have it for some, you know, event for another as well.","index":93,"end_time":824.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, let me.","index":94,"end_time":826.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me run that by them again.","index":95,"end_time":827.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":826.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I do.","index":96,"end_time":829,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t want to.","index":97,"end_time":829.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, I hate to cut everything short because I know you were already mid meeting by the time I got here and I apologize for that.","index":98,"end_time":836.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no.","index":99,"end_time":836.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I do have another meeting at 11:30 that I have to make, so.","index":100,"end_time":840.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":837,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":101,"end_time":841.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":840.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just one more thing to mention.","index":102,"end_time":843.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":841.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bailey asked if on the meeting for the 22nd it would be possible to make it an long and just to go through everything with you and Don and Andy when it comes to, you know, what are your plans for this year and what would you like to focus on?","index":103,"end_time":858.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me take a look at that.","index":104,"end_time":861.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because.","index":105,"end_time":862.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Unfortunately, you guys are conflicting with.","index":106,"end_time":868.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":870.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bi weekly accounting team meeting.","index":108,"end_time":876.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, you know, we do need to do that at 11:30 on Thursday.","index":109,"end_time":880.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Could we maybe start at 10:30?","index":110,"end_time":882.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":880.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I will tell Bailey and we will see if we can make it work.","index":111,"end_time":889.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I''m sure that we can find the time.","index":112,"end_time":891.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":113,"end_time":892.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":891.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, That''ll work.","index":114,"end_time":893.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, just stop sharing my screen so I can see you.","index":115,"end_time":900.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But.","index":116,"end_time":901.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that would be all.","index":117,"end_time":903.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I will also put all the questions in the email.","index":118,"end_time":906.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when you have time, just let me know.","index":119,"end_time":908.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What are your thoughts?","index":120,"end_time":909.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":908.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":121,"end_time":910.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes, thank you.","index":122,"end_time":911.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":910.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That reminder will be good.","index":123,"end_time":912.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll see you and get to it.","index":124,"end_time":914.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":125,"end_time":915.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":126,"end_time":917.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":916.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Have a nice week.","index":127,"end_time":917.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You as well.","index":128,"end_time":918.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":129,"end_time":919.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.85,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2026-01-08T19:05:39.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEFG031W66M2WS5653CG29H